name: stack velocity ellipticity azimuth
description: Estimation of the velocity ellipticity azimuth for all layers to the current depth.

name: feature dip
description: Dip computed on a general feature surface by measuring the difference in attribute values between two points compared to the horizontal distance between the points.

name: partial density
description: Apparent density of a component (fluid, gas, etc.) in the presence of other components. The sum of the partial densities equals total density.

name: receiver orientation phi
description: Vertical angle of downhole receiver, measured from the x-y plane.

name: thomsen delta
description: Thomsen's delta anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between vertical and moveout Compressional velocities.

name: seismic flag
description: Flag indicating that the object or data pertains to seismic techniques or was derived from seismic data.

name: file system name
description: Name of computer operating system component which deals with data file storage, e.g. NFS (Unix), RMS (VMS).

name: well test type
description: The type of test conducted on a Well.

name: well production control mode
description: Describes what controls the production flow of the well (e.g. constant wellhead pressure, constant flowrate)

name: i c6h14 concentration
description: Concentration of iso-Hexane (i-C6H14).

name: language
description: Name of spoken or written language, such as English, Spanish, French, Mandarin, Russian, Chichimeq...

name: tube upset type
description: Type of upset in tube or body

name: velocity
description: The rate of change of the displacement of a body in time.

name: area per volume
description: Change in area per unit volume

name: county name
description: Name of a County or Parish

name: silicon dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of silicon to total dry weight

name: net reservoir gross thickness ratio
description: Ratio of Net_Reservoir_Thickness to Gross_Thickness

name: heat capacity
description: The amount of heat required to raise the temperature of a unit volume of a given material by one degree.

name: wet gas critical temperature
description: The highest temperature at which the gas can exist as a liquid and above which its vapor cannot be liquefied regardless of the amount of pressure (Wet gas - mixture of free gas plus condensate)

name: liquid viscosity
description: The viscosity of a liquid at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: last static pressure depth
description: Depth at which last reservoir pressure data were recorded

name: tool speed
description: Speed of the tool; logging speed.

name: oil acoustic velocity
description: Sound velocity of live oil at reservoir pressure and temperature. Typical value is 1000 m/s.

name: bandwidth rating bias wavenumber
description: Bandwidth rating bias in depth domain. See Bandwidth_Rating_Bias

name: publication date
description: Date of publication of a document.

name: liquid molar density
description: Number of moles of a liquid material per unit volume.

name: net reservoir core porosity point match
description: Average porosity in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from core data by point-match method.

name: drill hole opener reamer type
description: Generic type of tool i.e. standard, bull nose hole opener, underreamer, LHO (Large Hole Opener with rollers),roller reamer, 3-Point Roller Reamer, 6-Point Roller Reamer

name: rheology model
description: Mathematical model describing how the shear stress relates to the shear rate i.e. how a fluid flows and is deformed in response to applied stresses. Most popular model are Newtonian, Bingham Plastic and Power-Law

name: oil production volume per lateral length per no of fractures
description: Normalized oil cumulative per lateral length per number of fractures

name: micro cylindrically focused resistivity
description: A measurement of the resistivity of the formation, by a cylindrically focused tool, within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: implementation code
description: Catalog code of the Implementation of a Representation

name: nom flowrate
description: Nominal Flow Rate

name: start age code
description: The code of the earliest geologic or geochronologic age associated with an event or item, such as an earth layer, a fossil or pollen type.

name: daily prognosis
description: Description of activities and events anticipated during the next 24 hours.

name: energy half z
description: Characterization of relative distribution of energy in a layer, computed as the fractional displacement (depth or time) into an interval (layer, bed) where half of the energy is above, half below.

name: ellipsoid ecc2
description: Ratio derived from semi-major and semi-minor axes to define degree to which ellipsoid shape departs from the spherical. [1 - b**2/a**2]

name: mu rho
description: Product of Shear modulus and density, MR

name: product name
description: Official product name.

name: east west line
description: Indicates whether the East or West boundary line of the survey area has been used as a reference for East_West_Distance values.

name: computation mask
description: Application-specific mask for the computation options (one Anadrill example: 0001 - Torque and Drag, 0010 - BHA Tendency, 0100 - Bit Side Forces, 1000 - Buckling, 10000 - Yield Stress)

name: well test model
description: Type of well test: e.g. Conventional, Horizontal, Interference, etc.

name: ideal receiver position 0 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal receiver position 0.

name: net reservoir hc porosity thickness
description: Total Net Reservoir hydrocarbon porosity-thickness for all zones; that portion of Net_Reservoir_Porosity_Thickness which is hydrocarbon-filled.

name: inductive reactance
description: The component of electrical impedance due to inductance.

name: multi use property
description: Property whose meaning can only be interpreted within the context of its use; for example, the meaning of Max_Value requires a context to determine a type of measurement.

name: lessor bonus
description: Bonus payed to lessor for signing

name: nom outside diameter
description: Nominal (approximate, for naming purposes only) outside diameter of an equipment item.

name: effective porosity
description: The porosity available to free fluids, excluding non-connected porosity and space occupied by bound water.

name: invasion diameter
description: The diameter to which drilling mud filtrate has invaded porous and permeable rock around the borehole.

name: sand volume fraction
description: Volume fraction of sand as calculated, measured or inferred from formation properties.

name: shallow induction conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by an induction log, which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: hole inside diameter
description: The effective inside diameter of a Well; may be of the Borehole, Casing or Tubing.

name: boiling point
description: The temperature at which fractions of a liquid boil.

name: to conn number
description: Indicates which end or connection number (1 or 2 for tubulars, 3 for a hydraulic T,...) of the "To" equipment in a From_To equipment connection. The description of the "To" connection number is needed in some cases for equipment item which is last in the connection chain. When no ambiguity exists, the From_Conn_Number is the preferred property.

name: concentration 1
description: Concentration or proportion of first component in mixture or other composition.

name: fluid type
description: The type of fluid. Usually associated with a formation, a reservoir, borehole, etc.

name: ideal source position 2 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal source position 2.

name: specific surface area per volume
description: The characteristic of a porous media which is the internal surface area of the medium per unit volume.

name: specific acoustic impedance
description: The specific acoustic impedance is a ratio of acoustic pressure to specific flow, or flow per unit area, or flow velocity.

name: velocity at z0
description: (Instantaneous) Velocity at surface reference z=0 (z is time or depth).

name: cost charge type
description: Indicates whether the cost allocation is valid for the start (Start), end (End) of activity or at a given date (User)

name: coord sys transform code
description: Code for a coordinate system transform method.

name: closure
description: Indicates whether the boundary of a spatial object is Open or Closed?

name: mass per volume per length
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per volume per length that acts as a parent for other property instances

name: bed type
description: The general physical and structural character or pattern of beds and their contacts within a rock mass; e.g., cross-bedding and graded bedding; homogenous, wave ripples, planar cross beds.

name: gas formation volume factor
description: Ratio of gas volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions to the gas volume at surface (stock tank) conditions. Normally abbreviated Bg.

name: resistivity
description: The property of a material which resists the flow of electrical current. The ratio of electric-field intensity to current density. The reciprocal of conductivity.

name: perforation length
description: Length of the portion of the perforation which extends from the casing beyond the cement sheath and into the reservoir. It includes the casing thickness and the cement sheath thickness.

name: interval inline dip
description: Estimation of the inline dip for a layer.

name: coring method
description: The type of method used to acquire a core sample; e.g. Rotary Conventional, Rotary Sponge, Sidewall Mechanical, etc.

name: attenuation
description: Loss in energy or reduction in sensitivity. In seismic work, loss in acoustic energy due to absorption, reflection, etc. which occurs between any two points of travel.

name: ash volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of ash with respect to the total volume.

name: max water flowrate
description: Maximum water flowrate

name: ideal sample shift 0
description: Fractional sample shift associated with ideal position 0

name: calibrator type
description: Type of device used to calibrate the sensor or tool.

name: matrix compressional slowness
description: Acoustic slowness of a compressional wave in a given material or matrix.

name: wave azimuth
description: Azimuth of the direction from which the waves are coming.

name: rotation gradient
description: A measure of the rotation of an object per unit length; e.g., flowmeter rotation per length of pipe, pipe rotation per unit length (for stuck pipe applications.

name: oil production volume per perforation length
description: Normalized oil cumulative per perforation length

name: model name
description: Name of a model or version of some entity; for equipment, it may coincide with the trade name.

name: interval anisotropic axis 2 inline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 2 inline direction for a layer.

name: oil viscosity
description: The viscosity of oil at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: diameter restriction
description: Description of the change in diameter within a well or a borehole.

name: plastic viscosity
description: Apparent viscosity of the Bingham Plastic model : Slope of the curve shear stress vs. shear rate (rheogram). Model equation is Shear_Stress = Yield_Stress + Plastic_Viscosity times Shear_Rate.

name: flowrate per length
description: Change in flowrate per length

name: propped bottom depth
description: Bottom Depth of proppant laden slurry volume during the propagation of an hydraulic fracture considered along the well bore..

name: absorption cross section
description: A measure of the probability that absorption will take place when a particle intersects a localized phenomenon (typically a nucleus)

name: hole deviation
description: Angle between the borehole axis and the vertical (also known as the Drift Angle and, in the drilling industry, Inclination).

name: treatment rate
description: Total flowrate pumped downhole in a well treatment activity

name: force
description: An agency or influence that if applied to a free body results chiefly in an acceleration of the body and sometimes in elastic deformation and other effects.

name: max gauge count
description: Maximum number of Gauges possible with this type of Equipment

name: pore pressure safety factor
description: Amount by which borehole pressure should normally exceed pore pressure, to allow for uncertainty in pore pressure estimation.

name: volumetric heat capacity per temperature
description: Extensive heat capacity per volume and per temperature, see Volumetric_Heat_Capacity_Per_Temperature

name: producing thickness
description: Total flowing thickness along the Borehole ("Hp")

name: peak trough delta depth
description: Depth difference between peak and trough where peak occurs first in increasing depth

name: screen tension type
description: Type of screen tension (deck tensioned or factory pretensioned)

name: up load
description: Upward load exerted on an equipment item.

name: potential difference per power drop
description: Change in voltage drop per change in power

name: mud conductivity out
description: The electric conductivity of mud coming out of the hole, usually measured in the ditch before the shale shakers

name: absolute permeability water
description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with water.

name: blade length
description: Length of blade measured along spiral; used for drill stabilizer blades.

name: term
description: Term of an agreement. Usually in years

name: band low frequency
description: Lower limit of frequency band (range)

name: phone number
description: Telephone number

name: free pipe signal
description: Signal value in free (uncemented) pipe; used to calibrate and interpret cement bond measurements

name: capacitive reactance
description: The component of electrical impedance due to capacitance: Xc = 1 /(2 pi F C), where F is the frequency and C is the capacitance.

name: tube drift diameter
description: Drift diameter of tube or body of equipment item.

name: bale xi
description: Bale's xi, the shear wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout shear wave velocities.

name: projection scale reduction
description: A number by which the scale along a designated meridian, great circle, or parallel is reduced or enlarged during the projection process to reduce the scale error elsewhere in the projection.

name: radioactivity
description: The measure of intensity of radiation from a material relative to a standard level of intensity.

name: packer type
description: Type of packer; supplier type like Dowell Model 21. No simple type description available but the supplier identification.

name: dip classification
description: Classification information for the dips as dip color (RGB), shape, or type

name: temperature out
description: The temperature of the output material

name: nominal receiver correction
description: Nominal correction vector to receiver position

name: nom max outside diameter
description: Nominal maximum outside diameter, such as for a pilot hole.

name: manual control flag
description: Flag indicating whether the activity is/was controlled manually by the user (1) or automatically by the system or application (0)

name: stab to bottom conn 2
description: Length from the mid-point of the second stabilizer to the bottom connection of the tool

name: uwi
description: The unique Identifier given to a well or a borehole specified in a given naming system. This identifier can be granted by either an official regulatory commission such as the API 12/14 digits, the Canadian Petroleum Association (CPA) or by any organization (user, customer), described in Well.Naming_System.

name: annulus volume
description: The volume of the portion of the borehole which lies between the borehole wall and the casing.

name: total geometric spreading
description: The total effect of geometric spreading along ray. Factor giving the reduction in seismic amplitude (less than 1) due to spreading of the wave between two points. Includes both spherical divergence and cylindrical divergence.

name: gel mass concentration
description: Ratio between solid additive mass and fluid volume

name: fracture element height
description: Height of fracture element

name: rayleigh velocity
description: The velocity of a Rayleigh wave (type of seismic wave propagated along the free surface of a semi-infinite medium.

name: aperture time
description: The time interval which contains the data used in a calculation, usually specified as the start and end times for the aperture.

name: polyol concentration
description: Polyol Concentration per fluid Volume (Polyol are glycol-glycerol alcohol derivatives)

name: thermal transmissibility
description: Thermal transmissibility, thermal conductivity multiplied by length

name: sensor azimuth
description: The azimuth of a sensor on a logging device, used to determine the orientation of the device.

name: total porosity
description: The total volume fraction of a rock which is occupied by fluid; includes all forms of porosity, including that occupied by bound fluids, and is independent of rock and fluid materials and of environmental effects

name: h2s flag
description: Indicates that hydrogen sulfide (H2S) has been detected.

name: component 3 name
description: Name of third component in a mixture or composition.

name: fault block
description: Index of a fault block in an earth model

name: fault detection source
description: The source of the data used to detect faults (e.g., Seismic data, Structural analysis, Dipmeter log data, etc.)

name: accuracy
description: The extent to which a measurement approaches the true value of a quantity; usually expressed as a fraction of the true value or, for instrumentation, full scale.

name: sensor temperature
description: Temperature of a specific sensor.

name: potassium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of potassium to total dry weight

name: silt volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of silt with respect to the total volume.

name: top true vertical thickness depth
description: True Vertical Thickness Depth of Top of Interval

name: remote file
description: Name of file on remote host

name: net reservoir porosity
description: Average porosity in the Net Reservoir portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: blocking method type
description: Blocking method

name: net pay cutoff absent fraction
description: Fraction of the summation interval for which data to apply "Net_Pay" cutoff criteria are unavailable (including the fraction for which "Net" or "Net_Reservoir" criteria are unavailable); used as a coarse indicator of the reliability of the summation results.

name: solids control cone diameter
description: Largest Inner Diameter of a Cone

name: elevation cdp
description: Surface elevation at a CDP with respect to mean sea level.

name: flag
description: An indicator of which of two or more conditions exist, or of which option has been selected. Most flags are binary in nature with a Yes/No possibility.

name: true scale latitude
description: Latitude at which scale is true, as with a standard parallel.

name: gas production volume per length
description: The measure of gas volume per linear displacement

name: c7plus plus molecular weight
description: Molecular weight of Heptane (C7H14) and heavier component concentration in crude oil. Typical value: 110-130

name: porosity type
description: The porosity type usually of a core sample or in either a carbonate or clastic rock formation (e.g. Intercrystal, Breccia, Vuggy, etc.),

name: source line z
description: Z-coordinate of position in a source line.

name: bad hole flag
description: Flag indicating that the hole is in poor condition (e.g. oversize or overly rugose)

name: conn 1 drift diameter
description: Drift diameter of tool joint/connection 1

name: fill top depth
description: Measured depth of the top of the fill. (Fill : unwanted material, formation sand, proppant, gravel pack failure, workover debris ... filling up the wellbore)

name: heat release rate
description: The quantity of heat released in a material per unit time. Also known as mixing power.

name: node type
description: The type of (topological) Node, as used in the Region submodel.

name: secondary porosity
description: The additional porosity created by chemical changes, specially fissures, fractures, solution vugs and dolomitization.

name: temperature in
description: The temperature of the input material.

name: atomic weight
description: The average relative weight of an element referred to some element taken as a standard; basis may be hydrogen with an atomic weight of 1, oxygen with an atomic weight of 16, or carbon with an atomic weight of 12.

name: matrix specific gravity
description: Specific gravity of the rock matrix. Typical value is 2.7 .

name: activation temperature
description: Temperature at which recording should begin

name: mineral conductivity
description: Mineral Conductivity

name: threshold
description: The value of a property which signals some change in state or behavior of a material, process or algorithm.

name: library doc file
description: Name of file containing documentation for (software) library.

name: sequence number
description: Number used to identify or index an element in a sequence.

name: min delay time
description: Minimum Delay Time

name: ideal sample shift 1
description: Fractional sample shift associated with ideal position 1

name: ideal source position 0 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal source position 0.

name: operating system version
description: Version of computer Operating System

name: dead volume
description: Volume of material remaining in a container after normal emptying procedure, and thus not available for use.

name: postal address
description: Location to which postal correspondence may be sent for a person, business or other entity.

name: conn 2 type
description: Type of the bottom or second standard tool connection.

name: neutron scatter cross section
description: The macroscopic scattering cross section, i.e. the effective cross sectional area where a neutron will scatter rather than being absorbed by a nucleus.

name: cell count
description: Number of cells

name: tracking window top
description: Interval above the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type while tracking

name: dimensionless fracture conductivity
description: Ratio of fracture conductivity (fracture permeability x average width) to the (matrix permeability x fracture half_length) product. Standard industry acronym : "FCD", S.P.E. preferred form "CfD".

name: kb source dz
description: Z coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: gas to liquid ratio rate
description: Gas to liquid ratio rate

name: activity type
description: The type of an Activity performed on a Well, a Region, or an Earth subsurface component, e.g. Drilling, Seismic, Logging, etc.

name: record length
description: Total record length in bytes, such as for a seismic trace header.

name: client
description: The code of a client, usually that of a Service, Contractor, Vendor or E and P company

name: mass fraction
description: The ratio of the mass of a component to the total mass.

name: completion skin
description: Skin effect due the completion of the producing interval. It does not include the effect of partially completed interval (plugged perf or bad localization), but it does include Gravel Pack skin.

name: reservoir mass density
description: Reservoir mass density

name: integrated slowness
description: Total acoustic travel time over a wellbore interval as computed by integrating acoustic slowness from a sonic log (Compressional_Slowness) over the interval.

name: height
description: The distance from the bottom to the top of something standing upright. Also, the extent of elevation above a level.

name: geometrical factor
description: A geometry-dependent weighting factor used to characterize how different media in the neighborhood of a sensor participate in the sensor measurement.

name: zone length
description: The length of a zone, usually along the borehole.

name: pressure drop correlation type
description: Pressure drop correlation (e.g., Dun-Ros, Cullender, etc. )

name: projection cs type
description: The type of a Projection coordinate system, e.g. Lambert, UTM, State Plane, etc.

name: line style
description: Line drawing style, such as pattern of dots and dashes.

name: standard oil flowrate
description: Oil flow rate at standard condition when a sample is taken

name: migrated time interpretation
description: Seismic travel time interpretation based on migrated sections; typically represented as a grid.

name: interval anisotropic axis 1 inline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 1 inline direction for a layer.

name: standing oil flag
description: Indicates if there is standing, motionless oil

name: mud flow out
description: The mud flow out of the hole

name: net pay clay volume fraction
description: Average clay volume fraction in the net pay portion of the zone interval (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: mwd tool code
description: Specific code of a tool used for Measurement While Drilling.

name: stab to bottom conn 3
description: Length from the mid-point of the third stabilizer to the bottom connection of the tool

name: api pin conn size
description: API pin connection size

name: oil flowrate per lateral length
description: Change in oil flowrate per lateral length

name: gas flowrate per number of fractures
description: Normalized gas flowrate per number of fractures

name: 1 minute gel test deflection
description: The maximum reading (deflection) taken from a direct-reading viscometer after the fluid has been quiescent for 1 minutes.

name: bit profile
description: Profile of the bit (PDC type bit)

name: color normal light
description: The color of a hydrocarbon show under normal incident light.

name: hole rotation friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient between open hole and drill string in rotation

name: drillstring drive torque
description: Torque applied to the drillstring, measured at the rotary table or top-drive.

name: final transfer temperature
description: Final temperature of shipping bottle

name: borehole status
description: A property indicating current status of a Borehole: Producing, Abandoned, etc. Related to the Petroleum Information (PI) codes.

name: weight on bit
description: The downward force exerted by the drillbit on the formation being drilled.

name: geologic age
description: The geochronologic age of an item or event, such as an earth layer. This is usually the average age in millions of years (Ma).

name: ideal receiver position 2 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal receiver position 2.

name: local coord sys name
description: Name of a local coordinate system.

name: neutron porosity
description: Porosity as measured with an neutron logging device.

name: grain density
description: The density of a unit volume of a mineral or other rock material at zero porosity. Sometimes called Matrix Density.

name: nmr porosity
description: Apparent formation porosity as measured with an nuclear magnetic logging device.

name: gross cutoff absent fraction
description: Fraction of the summation interval for which data to apply "Initial" cutoff criteria are unavailable; used as a coarse indicator of the reliability of the summation results.

name: titanium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Titanium with respect to total.

name: degree of confidence
description: The degree of confidence associated with any event or feature related to or detected, for example a geologic feature in/on the Earth (high, low, etc)

name: battery life
description: Battery Life

name: multi valued flag
description: Boolean indicating if the Horizon has multiple Z values for a single X,Y location.

name: critical oil saturation
description: The value of oil saturation at which oil will begin to flow, as oil saturation is increased.

name: wellbore tortuosity amplitude angle
description: Amplitude translated as an inclination of the sinusoidal function fitting the survey station points and simulating a real well path

name: gel concentration
description: Concentration of gelled fluid (fracturing gel, gelled acid ...)

name: horizontal mobility
description: A measure of the ease with which a fluid can be moved horizontally in a specific medium (i.e. rock). The ratio of the effective horizontal permeability and the viscosity of the fluid.

name: bit depth
description: Depth of the drillbit

name: material addition count
description: Number of packaging units of chemicals added to the drilling fluid. (e.g., Add 5 sacks of Barite C100 100lb/sack to the drilling fluid)

name: conn 2 drift diameter
description: Drift diameter of tool joint/connection 2

name: constraint code
description: Key Attribute of Object which constrains the Property values. For example, the Domain Attribute in the String_Enum_Cat used to constrain a string-valued Property.

name: time dip
description: Dip computed on a time surface by measuring the difference in seismic times between two points compared to the horizontal distance between the points.

name: bit rotation speed
description: Rotational speed of the Drill Bit

name: cost per mass
description: Amount of money per unit of mass

name: source line rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of position in a source line.

name: wellhead connection type
description: Type of wellhead connection (flange, tree- saver ..); data must identity the mechanical item unambiguously to allow a hydraulic connection e.g. Studded Flange API BX150-15000 psi.

name: diff pressure gauge type
description: Sensor used to acquire gas differential pressure across orifice plate

name: rat hole bottom depth
description: Bottom depth of the section of the borehole running from the tester valve to the effective bottom of the well

name: element code
description: Code of the Element type that participates in this collection. If NULL, any type is allowed in the collection.

name: residual oil saturation
description: The fraction or percentage of oil remaining following the liberation of gases from the reservoir.

name: bend 2 bend 3 angle
description: Angle between the planes defined by the second and third bends in the equipment string.

name: reservoir liquid productivity index
description: Ratio of reservoir fluid flow rate to pressure drop.

name: interval thomsen sigma
description: Interval value of Thomsen's sigma anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between Vertically polarized Shear (SV) velocities in the vertical direction and moveout SV velocity, for each layer.

name: consistency index
description: The k parameter in the Power-Law and Herschel-Bulkley rheological models. The Power_Law model is "Shear_Stress=k times (Shear_Rate at the power of n)". The unit of k is traditionally lbf.sec^n/ft^2 or Pa.s^n.

name: api approx weight
description: API approximate weight of one section

name: thermal conductance
description: The quantity of heat that passes in a unit time through a plate of particular area and thickness when its opposite faces differ in temperature by one kelvin

name: error
description: The deviation of a measurement from the true value; usually expressed as an absolute quantity rather than as a fraction; the unit quantity is determined by that of the data.

name: h2s service flag
description: Specifies whether equipment is for H2S service or not

name: integrated transit time
description: Acoustic transit time computed by integrating acoustic slowness measurements (from a sonic log) over a depth interval.

name: oil production volume per number of fractures
description: Normalized oil cumulative per number of fractures

name: c2h6 concentration
description: Concentration of C2H6 by volume. Typical value in natural gas 6%.

name: potassium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Potassium with respect to total.

name: model fit error
description: Generic property for a measure of how well the actual data fit a model of the expected values and/or distribution of data. Standard measures include Standard Deviation, Variance, Chi-Square.

name: fluid sample origin
description: General location from which a fluid sample was taken (test line, mud pit)

name: tube nom inside diameter
description: Nominal inside diameter of body or actual inside diameter tube (for API spec. drill pipe)

name: nom weight
description: Nominal (approximate, for naming purposes only) weight of an equipment item.

name: connector type
description: Type of casing or tubing connector according to that particular thread manufacturer; e.g., 8 RD STandC, 8 RD LTandC, Buttress, Hydril F J-P, Atbrad FL-3S, etc.

name: interval transit time
description: The travel time of a wave over a unit distance, hence the reciprocal of wave velocity.

name: liquid flux per area
description: Liquid flux per area

name: function name
description: Name of a software program function.

name: production history flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not this Flow Period is part of the Production History; i.e., set for Production History, not set for Test History

name: z acceleration
description: Acceleration along the Z-axis.

name: avg density
description: Average value of the material density.

name: gamma ray data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a gamma ray logging measurement.

name: platform type
description: The type of a platform.

name: mud flowrate
description: The rate at which mud, or drilling fluid, is being pumped into, or output from, a borehole or some storage unit.

name: screen motion
description: An indicator of the current state of the movement induced by the vibrator(s) of a shale shaker screen

name: z gravity
description: Strength of the z-axis component of the gravitational field at some location; used to correct total z-axis acceleration of a logging tool to compute actual tool movement.

name: potassium concentration
description: Concentration of Potassium by weight.

name: rheometer deviation
description: Vector of deviation angles of the rheometer related to the vector of given Angular Velocity

name: hole sliding friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient between open hole and drill string in sliding (translation only) operating mode

name: occurrence order
description: The order of occurrence of a particular item.

name: component 1 name
description: Name of first component in a mixture or composition.

name: pressure point setup
description: Identifies the location of the fluid whose pressure is being recorded.

name: measure point offset
description: Distance from the Measure Point to the Reference Plane for the assembly or tool; a positive value indicates that the Measure Point is above the Reference Plane.

name: c7plus concentration
description: Concentration of Heptane and hydrocarbons heavier than Heptane; typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.5%

name: oil sampling point
description: The location where oil samples are taken on the separator

name: surface type
description: The type of an Earth surface in the subsurface Earth structure, e.g. Fault, Horizon, Boundary, etc.

name: data focus type
description: Indicates how the entity set to be used as the starting point of a query is formed.

name: scale x
description: Scale factor in X dimension

name: standpipe pressure
description: Mud pressure at the stand pipe manifold, just before the flexhose connecting to the swivel.

name: publication title
description: Title of publication of a document.

name: mass per energy
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per energy that acts as an abstract parent for other property instances

name: sulfur dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of sulfur to total dry weight

name: cation exchange capacity
description: A measure of the extent to which a substance will supply exchange cations.

name: dimensionless
description: An abstract dimensionless property whose sole purpose is to be specialized into other dimensionless properties. A dimensionless property

name: packaging type
description: Type of Packaging or container used for products, such as Drum, Sack, Bulk, Pieces, Pallets

name: pressure squared
description: Pressure squared

name: flushed zone conductivity
description: The conductivity of the zone immediately behind the mudcake and which is considered to be flushed by mud filtrate, i.e., it is considered to have all mobile formation fluids displaced from it.

name: screen mesh size
description: Size of the mesh (usually expressed in inches) use to filter particles.

name: end age code
description: The code of the latest (most recent) geologic or geochronologic age associated with an event or item, such as an earth layer, a fossil or pollen type.

name: top vertical section
description: Top "depth" of an interval along a Vertical Section (VSCT) index.

name: tie point time quality
description: Measure of the significance of a mis-tie computed on a correlation basis.

name: micro lateral resistivity
description: Resistivity measurement using a "lateral" electrode arrangement with a very shallow investigation radius (1-2 inches into the formation).

name: geodetic datum point
description: Name of Origin of Geodetic Datum

name: acoustic quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from an acoustic survey.

name: dry gas gravity
description: The ratio of the molecular weight of the dry gas to that of air (Dry gas = free gas without condensate)

name: service date
description: The date on which a service was performed.

name: velocity gradient in depth
description: First derivative of velocity versus depth

name: companion data
description: Collection to hold miscellaneous competitor data in any form (parameters, arrays, ...), not described in the Data Model

name: mass per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per time that acts as a parent for other property instances

name: carbon oxygen ratio
description: Ratio of relative abundance of Carbon to that of Oxygen; important for hydrocarbon detection and saturation determination because it is independent of salinity.

name: field name
description: Name given to a field; may be a company-specific or regulatory name.

name: discontinuity type
description: The type of discontinuity: a detectable interruption in the material which may or may not have undesirable connotations (e.g. crack, lap, seam, pit, lamination, etc.)

name: perforation gun standoff
description: Standoff of Perforation Gun

name: magnetic flux density
description: A vector quantity symbolized by B and given in terms of the force produced on a small element of length which is carrying an electric current. B relates to the magnetizing force by a constant called the Magnetic Permeability.

name: max operating pressure
description: Maximum pressure which an equipment can withstand without permanent damage at standard temperature.

name: transient final flowrate
description: Flowrate at Transient End Time (qend)

name: geographic location
description: Geographical location, either the nearest city or geographical spot or a free text telling where the location is.

name: drill bit type
description: Generic type of the drill bit, such as Roller Cone or PDC.

name: sampling bottle type
description: Type of sampling bottle

name: rp66 parameter code
description: Code or Identifier of this type of RP66 Parameter object.

name: representation object
description: Object instance name where Representation may be found if not specified.

name: relative reflection intensity
description: Measure of energy reflected from a surface relative to the energy reflected under specific, standard conditions.

name: cumulative equivalent time
description: Cumulative Equivalent Operating Time, called Cumulative Time Usage or CTU.

name: water wettability index
description: Relative affinity of a mineral surface for water.

name: plane angle unit
description: Unit for Plane Angle data

name: downhole annulus pressure
description: The pressure in the annulus as measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: power
description: The time rate at which work is done or energy emitted or transferred.

name: vertical permeability
description: A permeability oriented vertically perpendicular to the bedding plane of the stratum. Usually abbreviated as Ky.

name: shape factor
description: A geometrical factor (Ca) characteristic of the reservoir areal drainage shape (e.g. circle or square) and the well location (e.g. centered).

name: base fluid type
description: The type of the base fluid usually used in chemical mixing, such Oil or Water.

name: vapor oil-gas ratio
description: The volume fraction of vaporized oil component in the gas phase.

name: perforation pressure condition
description: Pressure condition in the well at the time of perforating; may be Underbalanced (pressure in formation higher than in borehole) or Overbalanced (pressure in borehole higher than in formation.

name: ideal receiver position 1
description: Idealized receiver position 1

name: array laterolog conductivity
description: Formation conductivity as measured by a laterolog device capable of taking measurements at various combinations of resolution, depth of investigation, azimuth; such surveys allow detailed investigation of the invasion profile.

name: interwell distance
description: Inter-well distance for a horizontal interference test

name: total flowrate
description: Sum of the flowrates coming from different sources

name: directional permeability
description: An oriented permeability within a porous media, expressed either as horizontal (along the bedding plane of the stratum) or vertical (perpendicular to the bedding plane of the stratum), or within a coordinate system.

name: specific activity (of radioactivity)
description: Radioactive activity per unit mass

name: cement bond index
description: The ratio of acoustic wave attenuation in a zone of interest to that measured in a well-cemented section of casing, used as an indication of the quality of a casing cement job.

name: overburden gradient
description: The pressure gradient resulting from the pressure of the geology overburden

name: array conductivity
description: Formation conductivity as measured by a device capable of taking measurements at various combinations of resolution, depth of investigation, azimuth; such surveys allow detailed investigation of the invasion profile.

name: stretch
description: The amount of elongation observed in an object as a result of its being placed under tension.

name: neutron time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a neutron sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: survey bearing
description: The horizontal angle of an object, measured as a departure from some datum direction, such as North or South. Representations typically indicate the datum and the direction of measurement, such as [N 26.46(deg) W].

name: reservoir fluid compressibility
description: Compressibility of the reservoir fluid

name: transient initial flowrate
description: Flowrate at start of Transient

name: incident angle
description: The angle which the raypath of an incident ray makes with the perpendicular to the interface. In an isotropic medium, it is the same as the angle that a wavefront makes with the interface.

name: container code
description: Code of containing object

name: sampling bottle number
description: Sample bottle number

name: standard deviation
description: Statistical standard deviation from the mean value for some data; normally abbreviated a lowercase sigma; the unit quantity is determined by that of the data.

name: gas saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a formation contains gas.

name: test depth
description: Depth at which a formation test is performed; normally taken to be measured depth.

name: compressional slowness
description: The time it takes for a compressional wave to traverse a fixed distance; reciprocal of Compressional_Velocity.

name: max storage temperature
description: Maximum Storage Temperature

name: bulk addition mode
description: Describes how the bulk material was added to the mixture.

name: acceleration
description: The rate of variation of velocity with time.

name: mis tie phase correction
description: Phase correction to apply to line to compensate for differences in Tie_Point_Phase_Shift

name: riser tension
description: Tension of the marine riser

name: def display type
description: Default type of display used for a data object, such as an Array.

name: heat
description: Energy that causes substances to rise in temperature, fuse, evaporate, expand, or undergo any of various other related changes.

name: time uncertainty
description: Uncertainty of a time measurement.

name: report date
description: Date (time) when report was completed or issued.

name: general weather description
description: Description of current weather conditions.

name: compressible fluid productivity index
description: Productivity index for a compressible fluid, as a flow rate per pressure squared
quantity: PWLS:volume per time per pressure per pressure

name: conn 1 inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of tool joint/connection 1

name: filter slope
description: Base property for filter slope measurements
quantity: PWLS:logarithmic power ratio per frequency interval

name: toolface time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and the point at which the toolface measurement is taken reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: choke working pressure
description: Working pressure of the choke box which allow for the well fluid flow to be controlled by varying the flow cross-sectional area

name: discriminator 2 cutoff
description: Cutoff value for second discriminator

name: transit time srd
description: Transit time with respect to seismic reference datum

name: calcium concentration
description: Calcium concentration (Water Based Mud and water phase for Oil Based Mud)

name: surface area
description: Measure of the two-dimensional extent of the surface of some object.

name: flushed zone obmf saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a flushed zone around the borehole contains oil based mud filtrate.

name: unit quantity code
description: Code of a Unit Quantity in the SDM/OSDD Units model

name: flow direction
description: Indicates the flowing mode of a well completion; typically Injector or Producer.

name: msl receiver correction
description: Correction vector to receiver position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: resistive inclusion contrast
description: Conductivity contrast between resistive inclusions and the surrounding rock

name: fault distortion type
description: The type of distortion associated with a fault plane, e.g. Rollover, Drag, etc.

name: tool measure point offset
description: Distance from the Measure Point to the Tool Reference Plane (most often the bottom tool make-up plane); a positive value indicates that the Measure Point is above the Reference Plane. [Traditionally stored in Parameter MPOI on LIS/DLIS tapes.]

name: liquid density
description: Liquid density

name: gas production volume
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity GasProductionVolume, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: spacing y
description: Spacing in Y dimension; may be expressed as an absolute spacing with units or as a proportion of some reference X Spacing.

name: co2 concentration
description: Concentration of Carbon Dioxide (CO2)

name: frame bulk modulus
description: The bulk modulus of the solid frame of the rock. The solid frame of the rock includes the porosity but not the content of the pore spaces.

name: voltage sweep rate
description: Voltage Sweep Rate

name: filter cake thickness quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data representing mud filter cake thickness.

name: time
description: 1) The measured or measurable period during which an action, process, or condition exists or continues. 2) The point or period when something occurs. 3) A fixed moment or hour for something to happen, begin, or end. 4) A historical period.

name: phosphorus dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of phosphorus to total dry weight

name: intermediate time level
description: Seismic line dependent adjustment to achieve a continuous, line independent reference surface

name: sale number
description: Sale number of lease purchase

name: min non net thickness
description: It is common in an interbedded reservoir for sands thinner than a certain cutoff thickness (Min_Net_Thickness) to be discarded as non net or non pay in a ResSum type analysis. However, a thick sand may have two closely spaced shale stringers, such that they create the effect of a thin sand separated from thick sands above and below by thin shale beds. In this case, if the shale beds are thinner than a second thickness threshold (Min_Non_Net_Thickness), the thin sand would be counted as net or pay.

name: liquid gas ratio
description: Volume ratio of liquid (oil + water) to gas in a volume of fluid.

name: instantaneous amplitude
description: Amplitude component of an analytic seismic trace, when decomposed into amplitude and phase components (absolute value).

name: well to boundary distance y
description: The distance between the well trajectory and the adjacent reservoir boundary in the Y direction.

name: fracture half length
description: The length of one wing of a fracture, from the bore hole to one of its ends.

name: avg reservoir pressure
description: The average pressure (somewhere in the reservoir) between the borehole pressure and external boundary pressure.

name: standard temperature
description: Temperature considered to be "standard", for rates and volumes reported to be measured at Standard Conditions.

name: polarization azimuth
description: Shear energy polarization azimuth angle measured clockwise from grid north.

name: differential speed
description: The differential speed between the bowl and the conveyor of a centrifuge.

name: bound water saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a formation contains bound water.

name: tvd computation method
description: Method of defining the wellbore trajectory based upon directional survey data; includes curve fitting to the survey points and extrapolating beyond them.

name: live trace flag
description: Indicator if trace is live or dead.

name: tubular type
description: The type of a Tubular used in some activity or installed in and part of the well structure, e.g. Casing, Production Tubing, etc.

name: expansion factor
description: A factor that accounts for the change in gas density due to pressure changes, as across an orifice.

name: rock embedment strength
description: Force required to push a 1/8 inch diameter sphere 1/16 in into the rock. (Lab test). Value ranges from 5 to 20 kpsi for chalk, 40 to 100 kpsi for sandstones, 50 to 200 for Dolomites.

name: z magnetometer
description: Magnetic Field Strength along the Z-axis.

name: nom borehole diameter
description: Nominal inside diameter of a borehole; often referred to a "bit size".

name: qhse report count
description: Number of QHSE reports issued for the reporting period

name: sensor start time
description: Start time (t0) as observed by downhole or surface sensors, measured as elapsed time since the Time Reference.

name: conductance
description: The readiness with which a material conducts electric current; the inverse of resistance. Also, the product of conductivity and thickness.

name: subsea equipment type
description: Type of subsea equipment installed in facility or used in activity.

name: amplitude phase complex
description: Signal Amplitude and Phase represented as a complex number in polar coordinates, in the form Ae^jP. The first component A is the amplitude; the second component P is the phase in degrees.

name: country code
description: Catalog-controlled code of a Country.

name: energy half time
description: Time, within a specified interval, at which half the energy of the interval occurs

name: depth of returns
description: The depth from which drilled cuttings or gas are being received

name: reference pressure
description: Reference Pressure, as for a PVT computation

name: well projection type
description: Characterizes the way a well borehole is projected onto a cross section.

name: electron density
description: Electron density. Gamma-gamma logging techniques respond to electron density, which is near bulk density for most formation types.

name: material addition depth increment
description: The depth increment at which the material addition takes place (e.g., Add 5 sacks of Barite C100 100lb/sack to the drilling fluid each 500 ft)

name: undisturbed zone dissolved salt volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of dissolved salt in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: accuracy description
description: Textual description of the data related to accuracy.

name: fracture toughness
description: Measure of the rock resistance to crack propagation (Hydraulic Fracturing). Must not be confused with tensile strength. Obtained by compressing a slice of core with a central hole. Expressed as Pressure times square root of length.

name: optical density
description: Measure of light absorption by a material: for a given wavelength, Optical Density = -log(Transmittance); generally measured as an absorption spectrum for different wavelengths of light.

name: bioturbation type
description: The type of Bioturbation: the mixing of sediments by burrowing organisms.

name: mud resistivity
description: Resistivity of Drilling Fluid, also known as mud.

name: part number
description: Identifier used for accounting or purchasing purpose to identify an equipment item.

name: interval thomsen gamma
description: Interval value of Thomsen's gamma anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between Horizontally polarized Shear (SH) velocities in the vertical and horizontal directions, for each layer.

name: drill slot cluster type
description: Generic type of drill slot cluster such as template and pad

name: tool azimuth
description: Angle measured clockwise from North to the horizontal projection of the radius passing through the tool angle reference point. One of Tool_Azimuth or Relative_Bearing must be present

name: apparent water resistivity
description: Apparent resistivity of connate (formation) water, generally from logs; such estimates require correction before they can be used quantitatively.

name: avg flowrate
description: Average Flowrate on a given period of time

name: smoothing mode
description: Mode to use while smoothing horizon picks (automatic, manual).

name: availability
description: An indicator of the degree to which data, a product or a service is available for use; used to classify E and P data in order to support filtering of non-essential data from output.

name: mud filtrate phenolphthalein alkalinity pf
description: The volume ratio of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid (Pf_Titration_Volume) to mud filtrate volume, API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis.

name: id
description: A system generated number that uniquely identifies an data item (Entity, Property, Representation, ...) within certain system imposed limitations on the uniqueness.

name: water flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of water component of fluid.

name: molar absorptivity
description: The degree to which a solution absorbs light or other particle beam

name: shale density
description: The density of shale cuttings

name: min borehole diameter
description: Minimum borehole diameter

name: dolomite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of dolomite with respect to the total volume.

name: thermal gradient
description: The rate of change of temperature with length.

name: gauge count
description: Number of gauges

name: nmr dct2 map
description: Map of volume fractions for different diffusion coefficients (DC) and different transverse relaxation times (T2); normally represented as a 2d map of volume fraction values indexed by DC components along the y-axis and T2 components along the x-axis.

name: perforation type
description: The method used to open the production in the borehole. Examples are: Bullet, Jet, Combination, Open Hole, etc.

name: circulation loss rate
description: Rate of loss of drilling fluid to the formation, due to mud density exceeding formation fracture pressure gradient, and/or to drilling through a highly permeable formation.

name: volumetric photoelectric factor
description: A lithology indicator computed from bulk density and Photoelectric Factor; often expressed in an approximation unit barns/cc.

name: color distribution
description: A descriptive remark with respect to the distribution of a color within the area of a rock surface; e.g. solid, spotty, streaky.

name: separator gas capacity
description: Gas separator capacity at maximum working pressure and 1 minute retention time at low liquid level

name: ellipsoid b
description: Length of the semi-minor axis of the reference ellipsoid.

name: kick tolerance volume
description: Estimate of the volume of a kick (influx of fluid into the wellbore) at bottom hole conditions which can be shut in and circulated out without breaking the formation

name: gas gravimeter type
description: Type of instrument used to measure gas gravity

name: hgs concentration
description: High gravity solids Concentration

name: aperture
description: The size of any opening in an otherwise solid wall or surface. The size of a window that limits the information affecting a measuring device. Also used in processing (e.g., seismic migration or deconvolution.)

name: pressure rate
description: A measure of the rate at which pressure varies per time; e.g., slider pressure correction.

name: axial length
description: The length associated with the longest dimension of an object. This corresponds to the height of a cylinder, or the longest axis of a rectangle.

name: spectral gamma radiation intensity
description: Intensity of gamma radiation represented as a function of wavelength.

name: mud conductivity in
description: The electric conductivity of mud going into the hole, usually measured in the active circulating pit

name: breakout torque
description: Torque required to break out a pipe or casing connection

name: sonic time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a sonic sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: net pay gross thickness ratio
description: Ratio of Net_Pay_Thickness to Gross_Thickness

name: electric dipole moment
description: A measure of the overall polarity of a system, indicated by the separation of all charges present.

name: section length
description: Length of one section, such as the nominal length of one section of a streamer.

name: carbon dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of carbon to total dry weight

name: h2s concentration
description: Concentration of H2S generally measured in ppm. H2S concentration is critical in evaluating the corrosion of metal (e.g. coiled tubing) under stresses.

name: eccentering azimuth offset
description: Offset in azimuth due to eccentering; used to convert azimuth values with respect to an eccentered position into azimuth values relative to center.

name: fann test pressure
description: The pressure at which the Fann test was performed.

name: vaporization heat
description: The energy required to transform a given mass of a substance into a gas.

name: interval shear compressional velocity ratio
description: Value of shear-compressional velocity ratio in interval

name: vertical size
description: The size of any object as measured vertically

name: interval thomsen delta
description: Interval value of Thomsen's delta anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between vertical and moveout Compressional velocities, for each layer.

name: metamorphic volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of metamorphic rock with respect to the total volume.

name: cross section
description: A measure of the probability that a specific process will take place when a particle intersects a localized phenomenon (typically a nucleus)

name: liquid flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of liquid component of fluid.

name: intrinsic safety flag
description: When set, indicates that the equipment has been certified for use in a hazardous area. Equipment so certified has been examined by a National Certifying Authority and, where necessary, tested and found to comply with the requirement of a standard specification for the appropriate concept.

name: permeability axial path
description: Permeability measured along the length of a core cylinder.

name: specific heat capacity per temperature squared
description: The square of the change in specific heat capacity with temperature
quantity: PWLS:specific heat capacity per temperature squared

name: centralizer code
description: Centralizer Code

name: surface gas flowrate
description: Gas flowrate (surface conditions)

name: isotope ratio
description: The isotope ratio is a value that puts into relation a measured isotope quantity versus another isotope of the same component and compares it to a standard

name: frame shear modulus
description: The shear modulus of the solid frame of the rock. The solid frame of the rock includes the porosity but not the content of the pore spaces.

name: max y
description: Maximum Y Coordinate for region

name: drill bit grade wear
description: Drill Bit wear grading in percentage.

name: central meridian
description: The meridian on a graticule that is the axis of symmetry for the geometric properties of the graticule displayed on a map projection.

name: s wave angle
description: S-wave angle

name: drill survey tool type
description: Generic type of survey tool such as single shot, multi shot, gyro.

name: salinity
description: Concentration of the total salts in solution (Na, K, Cl, So4, ..).

name: cement bond amplitude
description: A measure of acoustic wave amplitude used for cement bond evaluation.

name: volumetric heat transfer coefficient
description: Coefficient of heat transfer between a porous medium and a fluid

name: rotation sense
description: Describes the sense of the axis system rotation specified by {ROTATION_1,ROTATION_2,ROTATION_3}. Most commonly used are "X_Y_Z" and "Z_NEWX_NEWZ".

name: core type
description: Identifies the type of core sample, such as Main, Plug, Slab, Sidewall, etc.

name: productivity ratio
description: Productivity ratio (actual productivity index divided by ideal (zero skin) productivity index)

name: msl receiver dz
description: Z coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: interval time
description: The time difference between two reflection events. It may vary due to velocity changes in different media, or changes in thickness of strata, or changes following erosion or structural deformation.

name: chemical product type
description: The type of a Chemical Product used in various types of activities, usually those provided by Dowell-Schlumberger

name: mass spectrum abundance
description: The abundances of the molecular constituents of a material; may be represented as voltage of a flame ionization detector, amount relative to a standard solution or actual mass quantities.

name: stripper friction load
description: Amount of friction between the coiled tubing and the packoff assembly. It is not the hydraulic pressure within the Stripper.

name: equipment test pressure
description: Recommended pressure the equipment is tested when inspected or certified

name: ramping method
description: Method to ramp (tapering) the time window, e.g., Hamming, Hanning...

name: sample number
description: The number assigned to a formation or fluid sample.

name: gas flowrate
description: Rate of flow of gas

name: semi minor axis
description: Length of semi-minor axis of an ellipse; in geodetic work, of a reference ellipsoid.

name: tubular string offset
description: The distance from the mid-point of the sub tubular equipment to the bottom of the super tubular equipment where the sub tubular equipment is attached.

name: bed set type
description: The type of bed grouping

name: crossflow coefficient
description: Characterization of the flow in the reservoir from one layer to another layer, usually known as "Omega" in Reservoir Dynamics

name: plus tolerance
description: Amount of positive tolerance on a measurement value; the unit quantity is determined by that of data value.

name: semi major axis
description: Length of semi-major axis of an ellipse; in geodetic work, of a reference ellipsoid.

name: undisturbed zone gas volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of gas in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: wind velocity
description: Velocity of the wind

name: coal dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of coal to total dry weight

name: medium laterolog resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation.

name: processing window length depth
description: Length of processing window in depth domain

name: kinematic viscosity
description: The dynamic viscosity of a fluid divided by the density of the fluid.

name: phase shift resistivity
description: Formation resistivity as measured by the phase shift of a high frequency electromagnetic wave (hundreds of KHz to several MHz, 1.1 GHz in the case of Schlumberger's EPT tool); these measurements are typically sharp (good vertical resolution) and have good dynamic range, but their depth of investigation is less than that of measurements based on attenuation.

name: max temperature reached
description: Maximum temperature reached by the system, sensor or equipment

name: rotation 1
description: Value of first rotation, as indicated by the first token in ROTATION_SENSE, used in transforming a coordinate system into a new (local) coordinate system.

name: max inclination
description: Maximum inclination of sensor

name: msl source dz
description: Z coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: production history reference time
description: Reference Date and Time for Production History

name: north departure
description: Displacement to the North relative to some coordinate system origin; e.g., the north component of the well departure from the vertical. (Negative value is departure to the South.)

name: low power flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not the tool is operating in low power consumption mode. When the flag is set, the sensor warmup duration is taken into account.

name: fann test temperature
description: The temperature at which the Fann test was performed.

name: chlorine yield
description: Elemental contribution of Chlorine with respect to total.

name: surface temperature
description: Temperature above ground. Temperature of the atmosphere.

name: true common midpoint x coord
description: X-coordinate of Common midpoint (CMP) position

name: y displacement
description: Displacement in the Y Direction relative to some coordinate system; e.g., the Y-Component of the Well departure from the vertical.

name: mass per time per length
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per time per length that acts as a parent for other property instances

name: inclusion proportion
description: Percentage of rocks occupied by inclusions within a given depth interval

name: non darcy skin
description: The skin effect resulting from turbulent flow conditions within the reservoir or the completion. This is the only skin which is flowrate dependent.

name: uranium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of uranium to total dry weight

name: rigid flag
description: Flag indicating that a piece of equipment is rigid.

name: gas gravity
description: The ratio of the molecular weight of the gas to that of air

name: cost per volume
description: Amount of money per unit of volume

name: flushed zone resistivity
description: Resistivity of the formation flushed zone (that portion of the formation in which the movable fluids are considered to have been completely replaced by mud filtrate during drilling).

name: true receiver line position theta
description: Horizontal angle of true position in a receiver line, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: damaged zone permeability
description: Permeability of the near-wellbore Damaged Zone, the sandface layer around the wellbore where permeability and mobility are impaired, generally by a damaging material (e.g. completion or drill mud).

name: interwell storativity thickness
description: Inter-well Storativity-Thickness [phi*Ct*h] for a horizontal interference test.

name: interval density
description: Interval value of the material density (density for a layer).

name: recorder type
description: Recorder type

name: frame number
description: Multi-source/multi-receiver shot record identifier

name: dry gas critical pressure
description: The pressure needed to condense a dry gas at its critical temperature (Dry gas = free gas without condensate)

name: mass rate per geologic time
description: Mass per volume per geologic time. E.g. the generated hydrocarbon mass per volume of rock per geologic time

name: fluid return elevation
description: Elevation of the drill fluid return line measured from the defined elevation reference datum (normally kelly bushing or rig floor). Note that if the elevation is negative, the return line is below the elevation reference datum.

name: wind azimuth
description: Azimuth of the direction from which the wind is blowing.

name: oil flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures
description: Change in oil flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures

name: pressure sensor noise
description: Random changes in pressure sensor response.

name: acoustic slowness
description: The transit time interval per unit length of an acoustic wave; inverse of wave velocity. Applies to all types of Delta-T: Compressional, Shear and Stoneley.

name: initial in situ gas volume
description: Total volume of in situ gas in the reservoir.

name: absolute delta flowrate
description: Absolute value of Delta Flow Rate. Calculated from the flowrate data contained in the Flow History, i.e., Q(associated Flow Period) - Q(previous Flow Period).

name: intrinsic safety certification marking
description: Mark made on an equipment item defining the type of intrinsic certification. Typical marking includes certifying authority symbol, type of protection, protection group for electrical apparatus and temperature class, e.g., "EEx ia I T5": CENELEC Intrinsic Safety-2 faults Methane 100 degree C.

name: neutron quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a neutron survey.

name: great circle azimuth
description: The azimuth of a plane represented by a great circle.

name: reel inlet pressure
description: Pressure at the inlet of a coiled tubing reel.

name: carbon yield
description: Elemental contribution of Carbon with respect to total.

name: heat flow rate
description: Heat flow per unit time

name: property multiplier
description: An arbitrary mutliplier applied to properties in a simulation

name: rig heading
description: Azimuth of the direction to which the rig is facing.

name: angular velocity
description: Rotation rate, usually measured in revolutions per unit time; e.g., spinner speed, motor speed, etc. The term Angular Frequency is also used, but generally refers to data scaled in radians per second.

name: initial final wellbore storage ratio
description: Ratio of early-time (initial) to final wellbore storage factor ("Ca/C")

name: covariance
description: A measure of the common variance between two quantities; a non-normalized crosscorrelation function.

name: top two way time
description: Depth of Top of Interval in Two Way Time

name: multi comp compressional angle
description: The angle between the vector perpendicular to the wave front, and the amplitude vector of the seismic defined by the X,Y and Z components. Seabed compressional velocity used.

name: cement unit output
description: Cementing unit maximum output flowrate

name: occurrence probability
description: The probability that an item (element, mineral, ..) occur within a particular environment under certain conditions.

name: conn 1 box flag
description: Flag indicating if connection is a box (Y) or a pin (N).

name: resistivity index
description: The ratio of the resistivity of a formation to the resistivity it would have if 100% saturated with formation water (Rt/Ro).

name: torque
description: Something that produces rotation or torsion and whose effectiveness is measured by the product of the force and the perpendicular distance from the line of action of the force to the axis of rotation.

name: reference location
description: Location used as a reference for other data.

name: merge strategy
description: Strategy for merging data, such as into a waveform gather.

name: hydrocarbon density
description: Density of hydrocarbons.

name: albite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of albite with respect to the total volume.

name: pressure point setup code
description: Encoding of the pressure point position setup of a Testing Tool by concatenation of the PRESSURE_POINT_SETUP enumeration separated by space, e.g., "Tubing-Above-Valve Annulus Empty"

name: azimuth turn rate
description: The rate of change of the azimuth of the borehole, normally expressed in degrees per unit of course length

name: nom near trace offset
description: Nominal in-line offset between the sources and the first receiver group on each cable (for symmetric configurations)

name: perforation gun position
description: The position of the perforating gun relative to the tubing/casing in the borehole. Options include: Positioned (usu. Through-Tubing guns), Not Positioned (usu. Casing guns), Centralized.

name: bottomhole circulating pressure
description: The pressure at the bottom of a borehole during circulation of any fluid.

name: kb source dx
description: X coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: blade width
description: Width of the blade at gauge, as used for drill stabilizer blades.

name: wellhead liquid flowrate
description: Liquid flowrate at the Wellhead

name: wellhead flowing temperature
description: Temperature at the Wellhead with well flowing

name: molar heat capacity
description: Heat capacity per amount of substance

name: pore pressure gradient
description: The change in pore pressure per unit length.

name: confidence factor
description: The probability that a given event will occur or that a given data set will contain a specified element.

name: proppant density
description: The density of the proppant material

name: grid convergence angle
description: Angle to be used in converting azimuths between true north and grid north or the Y axis of the cartographic projection. [Geoshare convention: True Azimuth = Grid Azimuth + Grid_Convergence_Angle]

name: geocentric ry
description: Rotation of the geocentric Cartesian coordinate system about its Y axis. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: tbg grade bearing
description: TBG Drill Bit Grade based on bearing condition.

name: oil gas ratio
description: Ratio of the volume of oil (including condensate) to that of gas.

name: vertical depth offset
description: Offset in true vertical depth versus some true vertical depth reference.

name: slackoff reel back tension
description: Amount of tension kept on the coiled tubing between the gooseneck and the reel while going into the hole

name: shear stress
description: Shear force (shear: strain that causes contiguous parts of a body to slide relatively to each other in a direction parallel to their plane of contact) per area unit of surface

name: bubble point temperature
description: The temperature at reservoir conditions at which gas in solution in crude oil comes out of solution as free gas.

name: burst pressure
description: Burst Pressure.

name: agency lease number
description: Unique lease number assigned by leasing agency

name: free gas oil ratio
description: The ratio of the volume of free gas to the volume of oil for a reservoir fluid at standard conditions.

name: weight
description: The force with which a body is attracted toward the center of the earth or any celestial body by gravitation. The product of the mass of the body by the local gravitational acceleration.

name: text location
description: Location of a section of text, such as a contract clause; typical locations are paragraph number or line number on a page.

name: detection gain
description: Coefficient used to adjust signal amplitude for detection of some event, such as the first arrival in a sonic waveform.

name: j function coeff
description: Coefficients used in the J function, a function used to normalize capillary pressure to account for differences in permeability, porosity, and fluid systems.

name: chlorine dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of chlorine to total dry weight

name: funnel viscosity
description: Time needed for a given quantity of fluid (generally a quart of mud) to flow into a specified size funnel (3/16 inch id tube of a 12 inch long funnel). Used for drilling fluids.

name: central wavenumber
description: Central frequency in the depth domain

name: module weight
description: Module Weight

name: acquisition file number
description: Acquisition system file number

name: pseudocritical temperature
description: The highest temperature at which a fluid can exist as a liquid and above which its vapor cannot be liquefied regardless of the amount of pressure. Used for mixtures, analogous to Critical_Temperature for pure components.

name: start age
description: The earliest (numerically largest) geologic or geochronologic age associated with an event or item, such as an earth layer, a fossil or pollen type.

name: riser internal diameter
description: The internal diameter of the marine riser.

name: orifice meter gas temperature
description: Temperature of gas at orifice meter line when a sample is taken

name: event class
description: Event classification by type

name: matrix shear velocity
description: Acoustic velocity of a shear wave in a given material or matrix.

name: event date
description: The date of an event.

name: alphacode
description: Synonym of Code using the alphabet character set.

name: isolated porosity volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of isolated porosity with respect to the total volume.
