name: orthoclase dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of orthoclase to total dry weight

name: square root pressure
description: Square root pressure

name: receiver line rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of position in a receiver line.

name: length per rotation
description: Length per angle of rotation

name: pore volume compressibility
description: The relative change in the pore volume of a rock under conditions of changing confining pressure.

name: thread type
description: Type of thread for casing pipe (such as short, long, buttress, extreme line)

name: cs trans type
description: The type of Transformation used between 2 coordinate systems, e.g. Molodensky, Affine 2D, etc.

name: bit revolution count
description: The number of revolutions of the bit since it started drilling

name: zone stop
description: The stop depth of a zone, usually along the borehole. This may be the deeper or the shallower end of the zone.

name: solution gas liquid ratio
description: The ratio of dissolved gas volume to total liquid (oil + water) volume

name: reflection heterogeneity
description: An indirect measure of how much a reflection signal is changing or of how erratic a trace is. A constant has a Reflection_Heterogeneity of 0. Heterogeneity can be computed from any of several signals, including seismic data, instantaneous phase, instantaneous frequency, apparent polarity and reflection strength.

name: water flowrate per perforation length
description: Change in water flowrate per perforation length

name: failure arc
description: The portion of the borehole circumference that has failed, expressed as the angle subtended by the arc length of the failure.

name: water production volume per lateral length
description: Normalized water cumulative per lateral length

name: well to boundary distance x
description: The distance between the well trajectory and the adjacent reservoir boundary in the X direction.

name: acoustic travel time
description: The elapsed time required for an acoustic wave to travel from one point to another.

name: quartz volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of quartz with respect to the total volume.

name: first derivative
description: First derivative of a scalar function

name: liquid head pressure
description: Pressure, represented as the height of a column of dense fluid that can be supported by the pressure.

name: spring stiffness
description: Coefficient relating spiral spring exerted force and corresponding elongation

name: porosity correction
description: Correction to a Porosity measurement.

name: feedback loop deviation
description: Departure (error) from the exact setting of a feedback loop

name: legal projection
description: Code of legislated map projection method.

name: fracture spacing
description: The distance between adjacent fractures.

name: completion date
description: Date that the activities that created the wellbore were completed and the wellbore was available to produce gas or oil, or for other intended service (e.g. gas storage, geothermal, etc.). Common completion activities include running and cementing the "production string" of casing, perforating the casing and cement sheath, installing the production string (tubing, packers, etc.) and the wellhead, etc.

name: def unit
description: Code of default Unit

name: cement unit discharge pressure
description: Cementing unit maximum discharge pressure

name: max extreme time
description: Maximum time at extreme conditions

name: mud temperature
description: The temperature of a mud or drilling fluid (sample) under certain conditions.

name: velocity to seismic datum
description: Velocity of the medium between the zero-time reference of a particular survey to the Seismic Reference Datum.

name: gas deviation factor
description: Dimensionless quantity expressing how a gas deviates from perfect gas law, commonly expressed by PV=ZnRT. Sometimes named Gas Compressibility Factor, but NOT the same as Gas_Compressibility. Z usually varies from 0.7 to 1.2.

name: oil brine ratio
description: Ratio of oil volume to brine volume for a fluid, such as an oil based mud

name: water saturation min so 3phase
description: The water saturation at minimum oil saturation in a three phase system. (SCAL SWM)

name: rotation
description: The angular displacement of a rotating body or figure.

name: sayers anellipticity
description: Sayers' normalized anellipticity factor, an alternative to eta for describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout compressional velocities.

name: longitudinal relaxation time
description: Longitudinal, or spin-lattice, relaxation time constant for alignment rate of nuclei to static magnetic field; normally abbreviated by symbol T1.

name: motor operating time
description: Operating time of the motor over the reporting period.

name: normalized distance
description: Normalized distance to the center of a point cluster in multi-dimensional attribute-space.

name: sys copy number
description: Number used to identify an instance of a particular type object within a set; used in conjunction with Copy_Number in GeoFrame.

name: horizontal well standoff
description: Distance from Horizontal Well to bottom of the Hydraulic Unit

name: solubility
description: A measure of the amount of one substance (the solute) which will dissolve in a given amount of another (the solvent).

name: expected life
description: Expected operating time of the equipment, generally defined as operating time of the first failure for 95% of the equipment

name: conn 1 approx weight
description: Approximate weight joint/connection 1

name: spontaneous potential drift
description: The drift in the measured Spontaneous Potential per depth.

name: spore color index
description: Relative color of fossil spores as caused by thermal processes. Index is used as an indicator of thermal maturation of organic material.

name: shallow normal resistivity
description: Shallow Resistivity measurement using a "normal" electrode arrangement.

name: treatment flow path
description: Indicates how the fluid is pumped into the well e.g. by the casing, the tubing, the annulus Casing-tubing ...

name: fluorescence
description: Measure of the emission of visible light by a substance that has absorbed light of a differing wavelength.

name: oil connection size
description: Standard oil pipe size connection supplied on the equipment inlet

name: working temperature
description: Temperature at which an equipment item normally operates

name: bladeface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between a (sensor-bearing) stabilizer blade and a fixed reference, measured in a plane normal to the drillstring. In near-vertical applications, North is the fixed reference (Magnetic_Bladeface); for higher deviation applications, Top of Hole is the reference (Gravity_Bladeface).

name: origin y
description: Y component of the location of the origin of a Local Coordinate System, measured with respect to the origin of the "from" coordinate system. Units, if any, are those of the "from" system.

name: liquid flowrate
description: Rate of flow of liquid.

name: medium induction resistivity
description: The resistivity, made by an induction log, which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation.

name: mass concentration
description: Concentration of material in a sample expressed as mass of the material per unit volume of sample.

name: fracture pressure gradient
description: Ratio of the Frac Pressure to the true vertical depth. Typical values for a reservoir range from 0.4-0.6 psi/ft for a depleted reservoir to 0.8-1.0 psi/ft for deep high pressure formation.

name: molar energy
description: Energy per amount of substance

name: initial oil volume
description: Volume of oil accumulated prior to the beginning of the measurement period.

name: publisher name
description: Name of Organization which published of a document.

name: mineral type
description: The type of a mineral.

name: bit rate
description: The number of bits that may be transported, say via telemetry, per unit time.

name: from property code
description: Code of Property of Entity from which the relationship originates.

name: bit drilled depth
description: The distance drilled by the bit

name: bottom value
description: Value at the bottom of an interval.

name: flushed zone gas volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of gas in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: nominal receiver dx
description: X coordinate of nominal correction vector to receiver position.

name: net pay porosity thickness
description: Total net pay porosity-thickness of the zone interval: the product of Net Pay Thickness and Net Pay Average Porosity

name: compartment count
description: Number of independent storage units

name: lease status
description: Status of a lease.

name: heat capacity per temperature cubed
description: The cube of the change in aggregate heat capacity of an object with respect to temperature
quantity: PWLS:specific heat capacity per temperature cubed
parent: specific heat capacity per temperature cubed

name: image clipping region
description: Vector of pixel values indicating which portion of an input image is represented in a clipped output; the structure of the vector is [Offset from Top, Offset from Left, Height, Width].

name: survey top depth
description: Shallowest depth of the survey or suite of surveys.

name: driller total depth
description: The total depth of the well borehole as reported by the drilling contractor.

name: archie porosity constant
description: The constant "a" in the Archie formation resistivity factor - porosity relationship.

name: volume rate per volume
description: The volume per volume in geologic time. E.g. The volume of generated hydrocarbons of a volume of source rock in a geologic timeframe

name: job number
description: Reference number assigned to a job or service

name: effective permeability water
description: The measure of the capacity of water to flow through a rock when the pore spaces of the rock contain other fluids.

name: avg shear compressional velocity ratio
description: Time average of shear-compressional velocity ratio from top to reflector.

name: wellhead producing liquid gas ratio
description: Ratio of volume of liquids to volume of gas produced at the wellhead; used primarily to express the amount of condensate produced in gas wells; typical unit is barrel per million cubic feet (RP66: 1E-6 bbl/ft3)

name: nmr t1t2 map
description: Map of volume fractions for different longitudinal relaxation times (T1) and different transverse relaxation times (T2); normally represented as a 2d map of volume fraction values indexed by T1 components along the y-axis and T2 components along the x-axis.

name: cumulative borehole volume
description: Cumulative volume of the borehole (integrated over length of borehole).

name: residual gas saturation
description: The fraction or percentage of gas remaining following production from the reservoir.

name: operating mode
description: Operating mode of an equipment

name: deep laterolog conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: newtonian viscosity
description: Slope of Shear Stress/Shear Rate curve for the Newtonian rheology model (Shear Stress proportional to Shear Rate)

name: resolution
description: The smallest separation between two objects such that they can still be discerned as separate objects. In sensor technology, the smallest change in input which will produce a detectable change in output. In this context, it is the same as Sensitivity.

name: turbidity
description: Measure of the degree to which light traversing a medium is scattered; for water, the scattering is due to particulate material and/or soluble colored compounds. Turbidity is most commonly measured in Nephelometric Turbidity Units (NTU).

name: dimension count
description: The number of dimensions for an object or a representation of such an object, e.g. dimensions of an array.

name: dip azimuth
description: Azimuth of the direction of maximum dip of a surface; dip may be computed in several ways, including from logs, from well-to-well correlation, from gradients on interpreted time or depth surfaces, etc.

name: api neutron
description: The Neutron calibration measurement determined using the API test pit. This quantity is associated with the natural formation hydrogen concentration.

name: organization name
description: Name of organization

name: downstream coil pressure
description: Coil working pressure downstream of the choke box

name: true receiver position x coord
description: X-coordinate of true receiver position.

name: iron yield
description: Elemental contribution of Iron with respect to total.

name: liquid radius
description: Liquid radius in the Bowl = Bowl Inner Radius - Pond_Depth

name: flowrate
description: A measure of the volume of fluid flowing per unit time.

name: chemical function
description: Primary purpose of a chemical e.g. Corrosion_Inhibitor, Gelling_Agent, Retarder, Emulsifier, ...

name: sedimentation rate
description: The rate at which sedimentation occurs.

name: nom receiver group distance
description: Nominal distance between consecutive receiver groups

name: engine oil pressure
description: Pressure of the lubrication oil

name: gas acoustic velocity
description: Sound velocity of gas at reservoir pressure and temperature. Typical value is 200 m/s.

name: load
description: The load (down or up) exerted on some object; e.g., hook load.

name: reservoir fluid density
description: The density of the reservoir fluid i.e. the mixture oil, gas and water.

name: 10 minute gel test deflection
description: The maximum reading (deflection) taken from a direct-reading viscometer after the fluid has been quiescent for 10 minutes.

name: resistivity data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a resistivity logging measurement.

name: borehole salinity
description: Salinity of the fluid in the borehole.

name: pad pressure
description: The pressure with which the pad of a logging or testing device is applied to the formation or other interface.

name: vertical lift flow regime flag
description: Flag identifying flow regime flag at some depth

name: oil mass flowrate
description: Mass flowrate of oil.

name: rectangle width
description: The width distance between two parallel boundaries in a rectangular reservoir model.

name: temperature measure point
description: The distance from the bottom of the Equipment to the point where the Temperature is measured

name: cutter count
description: Number of cutters, as for drilling hole openers and reamers.

name: dip pattern shape
description: Shape of a dip pattern, e.g. Convex, Concave, etc.

name: nom length
description: Nominal (approximate, for naming purposes only) length of an equipment item.

name: inclination
description: The vertical angle between a line and the horizontal; has historically been used in the drilling industry to mean the angle between the borehole path and vertical (the term Hole_Deviation is preferred for this concept).

name: northing latitude
description: Latitude of Northing reference point.

name: rig heave
description: Amplitude of the vertical motion of the rig

name: material phase
description: The physical state or phase of a material, such as Liquid or Solid.

name: zone set type
description: The type of a set of zone intervals traversing one or more Boreholes and/or one or more Earth subsurface Volumes.

name: conn 2 thread type
description: Complete and non ambiguous identification of the second threaded connection, e.g., "Hydril Joint Type EIU", "Pittsburgh Special ACME-Thread Casing-Internal-upset"

name: screen count
description: Number of Screens

name: damaged zone mobility
description: Mobility of the near-wellbore Damaged Zone, the sandface layer around the wellbore where permeability and mobility are impaired, generally by a damaging material (e.g. completion or drill mud).

name: compressibility
description: The change in specific volume and density under pressure; the reciprocal of Bulk Modulus, 1/k.

name: completion type
description: Type of well completion.

name: burner type
description: Type of burner

name: water fraction
description: Volumetric fraction of water in the total fluid

name: description
description: The description or complete definition of any data item or object

name: chloride concentration
description: Concentration of chloride ions in water based mud or in the water phase of oil based bud

name: spherically focused resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by a spherically focused log, which represents the resistivity approximately one to two feet into the formation.

name: max surge pressure
description: Maximum pressure to which this Equipment can be exposed for a short time without permanent damage; the Equipment will again perform to specifications when the pressure is reduced below the maximum working pressure.

name: frequency factor
description: The Frequency Factor is the pre-exponential factor of the Arrhenius equation describing the frequency of collisions between reactant molecules

name: receiver station time
description: Time of first measurement for each station since the Origin_Time stored in Seis_Survey_Area

name: one way time
description: The time required for an acoustic wave to travel directly from one point to another; used to distinguish from Two_Way_Time.

name: survey north south
description: Indicates whether survey location is North or South of reference line, such as survey baseline.

name: clay resistivity
description: The Resistivity of clay, usually referring to that measured in the Earth formations.

name: end age
description: The latest (numerically smallest) geologic or geochronologic age associated with an event or item, such as an earth layer, a fossil or pollen type.

name: conn 2 outside diameter
description: Outside diameter of tool joint/connection 2

name: proportion
description: The ratio of one part of an amount to the whole, with respect to quantity or magnitude.

name: entity object
description: Name of the implementation object of the entity. A table name in a relational implementation.

name: fault throw
description: Length of the vertical displacement of a Fault.

name: net pay permeability
description: Average permeability in the net pay portion of the zone interval (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: min concentration 4
description: Minimum concentration or proportion of fourth component

name: processing option
description: An indicator of which of two or more options has been selected for data processing.

name: inductance
description: The capability of an electric circuit to induce an electromotive force (emf) within the circuit.

name: pressure density
description: Pressure multiplied by density - typically the product of an elastic modulus and density.

name: time system offset wrt standard time
description: Time zone correction (defined to fractions of an hour) to be added to vehicle system time to correct to standard time. (GMT, UTC,...)

name: stress tensor
description: A second rank tensor whose components are the stresses exerted across surfaces perpendicular to the coordinate directions.

name: logger total depth
description: The total depth of the well borehole as reported by the logging contractor.

name: operating system name
description: Name of computer Operating System, e.g. Unix, VMS, Windows NT.

name: surface reflection coefficient
description: Reflection coefficient for the case when the multiples are reflecting from the free surface

name: injector head weight
description: Weight of the injector head of a coiled tubing unit

name: mud total gas
description: The total hydrocarbon content of the drilling fluid, by volume concentration

name: from datum code
description: Code of the source datum used in a datum-to-datum coordinate system transformation (datum shift).

name: tube material
description: Material composition of the tubular product.

name: processing window length
description: Length of processing window

name: drill jar shock type
description: Generic type such as hydraulic jar, mechanical jar, shock sub

name: coulomb friction coefficient
description: Ratio of contact and friction forces between 2 materials in dry friction conditions i.e. without lubrication (Coulomb law)

name: amplitude kurtosis
description: Kurtosis of seismic amplitude (normalized).

name: reservoir fluid viscosity
description: The viscosity of reservoir fluid at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: put function name
description: Name of function used to write data.

name: snap criteria
description: Set of parameters used by an application for "snapping" interpretation values to their corresponding data samples

name: trajectory
description: A description of the path that some activity or object makes as it traverses a medium.

name: cbl quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a Cement Bond logging survey.

name: negative threshold
description: Negative threshold value.

name: get function name
description: Name of function used to read data.

name: mud chloride concentration
description: Concentration of chlorides in mud.

name: bit operating time
description: Operating time of the bit over the reporting period.

name: effective permeability gas sor
description: Effective permeability to gas at residual oil saturation.

name: use checkshot flag
description: A processing option indicating whether or not Checkshot survey data should be used for depth-time conversion.

name: centralizer test type
description: The type of a Centralizer Test used to test a centralizer, usually during any well operation.

name: background pressure trend
description: Background pressure trend for a horizontal interference test

name: receiver orientation
description: Downhole receiver orientation vector

name: resistance
description: The resistance of a medium to the flow of electric current; the real component of the complex quantity Impedance.

name: water bubble flow velocity
description: Water Bubble Velocity

name: inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of an entity, such as an item of drillstring equipment

name: liquid flowrate per perforation length
description: Change in liquid flowrate per perforation length

name: component 2 name
description: Name of second component in a mixture or composition.

name: interpretation grid count
description: Number of Interpretation grids that exist for the horizon.

name: hydraulic model type
description: Type of Flow Behavior for the Hydraulic Unit, including the Inner Boundary Type + Reservoir Behavior Type + Outer Boundary Type

name: analytic trace
description: Complex seismic trace resulting from combination of input trace and its Hilbert transform. Normally represented as a pair of floating point numbers. [GeoFrame Value type: Complex32_t]

name: stack anisotropic axis 1 crossline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 1 crossline direction for all layers to the current depth.

name: rock subclass
description: Classification of rocks into Carbonate, Evaporite, etc. Commonly called Lithology.

name: profile conductance
description: Measurement related to conductance but not necessarily scaled or calibrated for quantitative use.

name: coefficient
description: A number which serves as a measure of some characteristic of a process, substance or device.

name: major axis
description: Length of the major (long) axis of an ellipse.

name: hydrocarbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of hydrocarbon with respect to the total volume; the product of porosity and hydrocarbon saturation

name: saturation exponent
description: The exponent of the Saturation term in the Archie saturation equation. Abbreviated "n".

name: primary output flag
description: Flag indicating that data constitute a valid primary output (1) or an auxiliary output (0)

name: calcium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Calcium with respect to total.

name: firmware version
description: Version of the firmware.

name: vsplib waveform header
description: The waveform header used in Vertical Seismic Profile. The structure of the data is specific to Schlumberger Borehole Seismic applications.

name: differential radius
description: The difference between the actual radius of an object and its average radius; for boreholes, 1/2 bit size may be used instead of the average radius.

name: nickel dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of nickel to total dry weight

name: bottom dip number
description: Number of Dip (in the Dip Set) at the bottom of the Bed

name: raw relative bearing
description: Raw relative bearing

name: apparent porosity
description: Initial estimate of porosity, normally from logs, not corrected for the (often large) effects of clays, gas, etc. Such estimates should only be used for qualitative interpretation of clean, gas-free intervals.

name: namespace code
description: Code of a Namespace across which object names are unique.

name: permeability thickness ratio
description: Ratio of component permeability-thickness to total system permeability-thickness [kh(i) / kh(total)], usually known as Kappa in reservoir dynamics work.

name: drill bit code
description: Specific drill bit code given by the manufacturer and usually approved by the IADC.

name: epithermal neutron porosity
description: Porosity as measured with an epithermal neutron device.

name: monophasic fluid flag
description: Indicates if the fluid is monophasic

name: receiver line position
description: Position in a receiver line

name: undisturbed zone oil volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of oil in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: service type
description: Type of service

name: blade to conn 2
description: Distance from blade to Connection 2.

name: gas oil ratio
description: A measure of the volume of gas which is produced with a given quantity of oil.

name: award date
description: Date lease awarded

name: makeup torque
description: Torque required to make up a pipe or casing connection

name: dominant frequency
description: Predominant frequency within power spectrum.

name: array induction conductivity
description: Formation conductivity as measured by an induction device capable of taking measurements at various combinations of resolution, depth of investigation, azimuth; such surveys allow detailed investigation of the invasion profile.

name: plug back total depth
description: Measured Depth of the current bottom of the borehole. It is the physical bottom of the borehole which is plugged either by a cement or by a mechanical plug. The P.B.T.D. can changes in time. It is smaller than the total depth drilled.

name: bored flag
description: Flag to indicate that equipment item has been bored.

name: thermal conduction transmissibility
description: Thermal conduction transmissibility is a property measuring the transmissibility of heat between adjacent objects via conduction, as opposed to convection or mass transfer

name: granulometric sequence type
description: This property specifies whether the granules making up a Earth subsurface sequence are coarsening up or fining up.

name: ccp trajectory
description: List linking shots and receivers to Common Conversion Points (CCP) in depth. Defines the trajectory in shot-offset domain to stack along to image a point in depth.

name: thermal resistance
description: Resistance of a material to heat flow

name: mud flow in
description: The mud flow going into the hole

name: min magnitude
description: Minimum magnitude

name: gas pseudo-pressure
description: was pressure squared per force time per area

name: chemistry type
description: Type of chemical system.

name: formation resistivity sw100
description: Resistivity of formation, assuming 100% water-saturated.

name: transit time sensor
description: Transit time taken from tool sensor

name: fracture type
description: Type of formation fracture.

name: sampling duration
description: Duration of data sampling or recording.

name: upper surface relation
description: The type of relationship between a surface and the ones above (e.g. the surfaces below a Horizon are onlapping.)

name: liquid concentration
description: Concentration of liquid

name: lower fluid type
description: The type of fluid found in the layer below a reference surface (e.g. Water in layer below a Fluid Contact in a Reservoir.)

name: simulation layer name
description: Name given to a layer in a reservoir simulation model.

name: mass length
description: An abstract property to serve as a root for real mass length properties

name: american aircraft regulation
description: American Aircraft Transportation Regulation pertaining to a type of material or equipment, e.g., DOT-E-752 Cargo Only

name: j function
description: Name of the J Function, a function used to normalize capillary pressure to account for differences in permeability, porosity, and fluid systems.

name: tool type
description: The type of a Tool usually used in some activity, e.g. CNTA, USIT, AIT, etc.

name: stop time
description: The time a certain activity or sub-activity stopped.

name: min depth
description: Minimum Depth of Activity

name: ratio
description: The value of one item divided by the value of another item.

name: tool status
description: Indicator of some condition in the operation of a tool.

name: concentration 2
description: Concentration or proportion of second component in mixture or other composition.

name: shallow resistivity
description: The resistivity which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: loss on ignition
description: Proportion by weight of a sample which remains after the sample has been heated (e.g. 1000 degC) in an oxygen atmosphere and the volatile oxides evaporated.

name: pickup reel back tension
description: Amount of tension kept on the coiled tubing between the gooseneck and the reel when pulling out of the hole

name: to property code
description: Code of Property of Entity to which the relationship points

name: cutter type
description: Type of cutters, as used in drilling reamers (such as Type T, F, or B)

name: time per volume
description: Amount of time for a given volume

name: stage count
description: Number of stages in an activity.

name: horizon sample count
description: Number of horizon samples to use while smoothing.

name: tube wall thickness
description: Wall thickness of tube or body of equipment item.

name: fracture element width
description: Width of fracture element

name: net reservoir core water saturation point match
description: Average water saturation in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from core data by point-match method.

name: synthetic seismogram
description: An artificial seismic reflection record produced by assuming a particular wavelet and model. Commonly, a one dimensional synthetic seismogram is generated by convolving a typical seismic wavelet with log-derived Reflectivity.

name: standoff porosity
description: Porosity measurement of the "standoff" region, a very shallow porosity determination used to correct formation porosity measurements from nuclear logging tools.

name: max working temperature
description: Recommended maximum temperature at which equipment can be used

name: oil wettability index
description: Relative affinity of a mineral surface for oil. Amott

name: molar volume
description: The volume occupied by per mole of a substance at a given temperature and pressure.

name: max up pull
description: Maximum up pull for an equipment item, such as drilling jars (upper limit of shock/cushion load).

name: surface tension
description: Surface tension

name: preservation method
description: Method by which an item or sample, such as a core sample, has been preserved.

name: transit time qfactor
description: Transit time q-factor

name: electric potential
description: A measure of Voltage

name: extensive heat capacity
description: Heat capacity as extensive property in contrast to Specific_Heat_Capacity

name: downhole mud pressure
description: The pressure inside a downhole MWD/LWD tool

name: msl receiver dy
description: Y coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: compressional impedance
description: Acoustic impedance to compressional waves

name: asap depth parameter
description: Private structure used by the ASAP autotracking application; holds depth variations of time-domain Property ASAP_Parameter.

name: minor axis
description: Length of the minor (short) axis of an ellipse.

name: small rotation per length
description: Angle of rotation per unit of length for small quantities

name: coordinate
description: Any coordinate of a Location.

name: volumetric coefficient of thermal expansion
description: Expansion of the volume of an object with a unit increase in temperature

name: solution gas oil ratio correlation
description: Model used to compute gas solubility in oil

name: ideal receiver position 1 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal receiver position 1.

name: cementitious flag
description: Flag indicating if the chemical is accounted for as a cement when proportioning by weight of blend. Cementitious chemicals are mostly weight extenders like bentonite.

name: barium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of barium to total dry weight

name: elemental yield
description: The fractional contribution of an element to the total; in induced gamma-ray spectroscopy, it is the fraction of the counts in the measured spectrum due to a given element.

name: direction overthrust
description: Azimuth of the direction of overthrust in case of faulting in the Earth subsurface.

name: tape density
description: Tape density, usually expressed in bits per inch.

name: energy length per area
description: A measure of energy length per area

name: core preparation method
description: Method by which a core sample has been prepared for analysis.

name: rectangle length
description: The length distance between two parallel boundaries in a rectangular reservoir model.

name: cement unit power
description: Cementing unit input horse power

name: bound water resistivity
description: Resistivity of water bound to clay in the formations.

name: liquid production volume per length
description: The measure of liquid volume per linear displacement

name: cultural feature type
description: The type of cultural feature that is to be found on a map

name: liquid production volume per number of fractures
description: Normalized liquid cumulative per number of fractures

name: upper fluid type
description: The type of fluid found in the layer above a reference surface (e.g. Water in layer above a Fluid Contact in a Reservoir,)

name: min inside diameter
description: Minimum inside diameter of an equipment item.

name: snap depth window top
description: Distance above the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type when snapping

name: air supply flowrate
description: The flowrate value which the air supply should be able to achieve

name: dry gas critical temperature
description: The highest temperature at which a gas can exist as a liquid and above which its vapor cannot be liquefied regardless of the amount of pressure (Dry gas = free gas without condensate)

name: fracture closure time
description: Time required by a hydraulic fracture to close. Can be derived from a Nolte plot (pressure vs. time). The more fluid that fluid leaks off into the formation, the faster the fracture closes.

name: fracture element distribution type
description: Type of spatial variation (linear or elliptical) of fracture height, width and conductivity

name: micro conductivity
description: A measurement of the conductivity of the formation within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: true source sensor position y coord
description: Y-coordinate of position of sensor placed near source, for detection of shot event.

name: tie point total time correction
description: Total amount of mis-tie correction to apply. Evaluated at line ties.

name: dimensionless rectangle length
description: Rectangle length divided by reference length ("BxD")

name: bend 1 angle
description: Angle of first bend in equipment item.

name: pressure per flowrate squared
description: Pressure per flowrate per flowrate

name: gas pressure axis type
description: One of the pressure transformations used in Gas Well Interpretation

name: spectral fluorescence intensity
description: Intensity of light emitted by a material represented as a function of emitted light wavelength and wavelength of the excitation beam, typically an ultraviolet light source.

name: area per area
description: Area per area

name: load date
description: Date data was loaded

name: sequence trend
description: The type of vertical evolution recognized in a particular sequence e.g. fining up.

name: correction factor
description: Coefficient used to correct data, such as for environmental effects.

name: mf titration volume
description: Amount of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid required in order to turn the color of methyl orange indicator solution from yellow to pink when determining methyl orange alkalinity of the mud filtrate, Mf, API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis.

name: axis azimuth
description: Azimuth of the axis, usually pertaining to a depositional environment such as a tidal-flat.

name: small circle dip
description: The angle of the pole associated with a small circle.

name: matrix electromagnetic propagation time
description: The time it takes for an electromagnetic wave to traverse a fixed distance of a given material or matrix. In this case the material or matrix is a specific, zero porosity rock, e.g. sandstone, limestone or dolomite.

name: co2 foam quality
description: Ratio volume of CO2 over foam volume. Indicator of the quality of a foam generated with CO2 for well treatment. Below 50% the foam is not stable, above 95% the foam changes to a mist. C02 foam are used when low pH is required.

name: non zero sample count
description: Number of samples that do not have a value of zero.

name: true common depthpoint offset
description: Shot position relative to the CDP Line

name: cobalt dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of cobalt to total dry weight

name: sedimentary structure type
description: The type of sedimentary structure associated with an interval.

name: core diameter
description: The Diameter of the recovered core.

name: rectangle height
description: The height distance between two parallel boundaries in a rectangular reservoir model.

name: conn 1 size
description: Size of the top or the first standard tool connection.

name: bearing type
description: Type of bearing, such as sealed or mud lubricated

name: fault control flag
description: Flag marking if a layer is affected by faulting.

name: plunger count
description: Number of plungers e.g. 3 for a triplex pump.

name: angular acceleration
description: The rate of change of angular velocity per unit of time.

name: drainage area shape factor
description: The shape factor for enclosed drainage areas, used to correct pseudosteady-state flow performance behavior of sinks in non-circular drainage regions.

name: valve inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of the valve assembly

name: flushed zone oil volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of oil in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: neighborhood
description: A topological property indicating whether a spatial object lies to the "left" or to the "right" of a neighboring object whose orientation sense has been specified.

name: wellhead producing gas liquid ratio
description: Ratio of volume of gas to volume of liquids produced at the wellhead.

name: to entity code
description: Code of Entity to which the relationship points

name: next receiver group distance
description: For non-equidistant receiver groups, distance to next group

name: session duration
description: Elapsed time from the start to the finish of a recording or processing session.

name: logarithmic power ratio
description: was level of power intensity

name: business region type
description: The type of a Business defined region of the Earth surface, e.g. Field, Lease, Concession, etc.

name: weight per joint
description: Weight of each joint in a string of equipment

name: horizontal mean permeability
description: Geometric mean permeability in the horizontal plane (X-Y) of the reservoir.

name: nozzle count
description: The number of nozzles in an equipment item, such as a drill bit.

name: cement additive type
description: Type of additive(s) used to change the properties of the cement.

name: distance
description: Amount of separation between two points, lines, surfaces, or objects measured along the shortest path joining them.

name: fluid compressional velocity
description: Acoustic velocity of an acoustic (compressional) wave in fluid.

name: axis unit
description: Unit for spacing and start value on axis.

name: perforation diameter
description: The diameter of the perforation entrance hole. Often called Entrance Hole Diameter.

name: test pressure
description: Recommended pressure at which the equipment is tested when inspected or certified

name: chlorite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of chlorite with respect to the total volume.

name: reciprocal area
description: was per area

name: setting tool
description: Generic type of plug or packer setting tool: Drill-Pipe or Wireline

name: air supply pressure
description: Air supply pressure; for a burner, the pressure required to achieve effective atomization

name: wall building coefficient
description: (Fracturing) Measure of the capability of a fluid flowing in front of a porous media to build up a filter cake inhibiting the fluid leakoff through the porous media. Non RPP66 unit :length/(time)**1/2 e.g. ft/min**1/2

name: reactance
description: The opposition to alternating current flow offered by inductance or capacitance; the quadrature component of impedance.

name: well name
description: Name given to a well, quite possibly the legal name. The name may vary as ownership and rights are transferred.

name: trace depth
description: The depth coordinate of a trace

name: invasion radius
description: The radius of the "invaded zone", the region in which drilling mud filtrate has invaded porous and permeable rock around the borehole.

name: api total penetration
description: Total penetration in an API Section I test

name: water viscosity
description: The viscosity of water at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: recovery factor
description: Recovery factor of reservoir fluids expressed as the ratio of standard volumes (stock tank barrels, etc.) recovered to pore volume.

name: cement sheath thickness
description: Thickness of the cement sheath between casing and borehole wall.

name: latitude longitude unit
description: Unit for Latitude and Longitude data.

name: gross rock volume
description: Total rock volume from a top reservoir surface to a contact, usually the oil-water contact

name: initial reservoir pressure depth
description: Depth reference of initial reservoir pressure

name: prescale offset
description: Special Offset value used in certain calibrations It is not part of the Calibration_Coefficient list.

name: gas volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of gas with respect to the total volume; the product of Porosity and Gas_Saturation

name: synthetic seismic section
description: An artificial seismic section produced by collecting artificially-generated traces (such as a Synthetic_Seismogram from log-derived Reflectivity) or by extracting data from an actual seismic section.

name: ph
description: An indicator of the degree of acidity or basicity of an aqueous solution. A value of 7 denotes a neutral fluid, lower values correspond to acidic fluids and higher values to basic fluids.

name: burner pilot pipe size
description: Standard gas pipe size connection supplied on the pilot inlet equipment

name: motor speed
description: The rotational speed of a motor.

name: inclination error
description: Plus or minus inclination error of sensor

name: dimensionless rectangle width
description: Rectangle width divided by reference length ("ByD")

name: right handed
description: Flag indicating that a 3D axis system is right-handed: a 3D coordinate system is Right_Handed if the direction of rotation from the x axis to the y axis is counter-clockwise when viewed from a positive position on the z axis. For example, if x is East and y is North, a Right_Handed system will have the positive z pointing upward (as increasing elevation). Right_Handed is meaningless for 2D systems.

name: rig pitch angle
description: Measure of the fore-aft rotational movement of the rig due the combined effects of wind and waves.

name: oil compressibility correlation
description: Name of the correlation model (often the author name) used to compute oil compressibility (e.g. Calhoun, Vasquez and Beggs)

name: matrix volume
description: The volume of material in a porous system that does not include the volume of the pores.

name: operator name
description: The name of an operator of a well, an equipment, etc.

name: lithologic color
description: The characteristic color of a lithologic sample.

name: washout caliper ext
description: The extension of a borehole diameter beyond which caliper data becomes unreliable due to bad contact with the tool pads.

name: confidentiality level
description: Describes the confidentiality of the information related to the well, e.g., Tight (operator only), Sensitive (some restriction), Public

name: inlet connection size
description: The connection size of the input line to the equipment

name: erosional velocity
description: The velocity of a flow below which erosional damage to devices such as completion equipment is minimized.

name: to datum code
description: Code of the target datum used in a datum-to-datum coordinate system transformation (datum shift).

name: wellhead gas flowrate
description: Gas flowrate at the Wellhead

name: interval mode converted velocity
description: Converted-wave velocity measured over a finite interval, with the interval usually determined by geologic layering. The converted wave velocity is determined from the time taken for the energy to travel in one direction as Compressional wave and in the other as Shear.

name: blade height
description: Height of blade at gauge from the body of the equipment, such as a stabilizer.

name: hydrogen index
description: The ratio of the number of hydrogen atoms per unit volume of a material to that number in pure water at 75 degF. Neutron logging response depends mainly on hydrogen index.

name: none
description: No property code applies; this is a temporary property type used to flag Parameters and Arrays for which we cannot make a meaningful mapping to any Property.

name: naming system
description: Name of the system which controls the valid or legal names of entities. For example, there are numerous system for naming wells: API 12 digit, CPA, Tobin

name: etched half length
description: Half Length of formation etched (dissolved) by reaction with acid (Acid fracturing)

name: fracture pressure
description: Fluid pressure in the wellbore required to undergo hydraulic fracturing.

name: fit equivalent mud weight
description: Equivalent mud weight determined by the formation integrity test (FIT) for a new formation below last casing shoe via increasing the pressure until a pre-determined value.

name: effective permeability
description: The measure of the capacity of a single fluid to flow through a rock when the pore spaces of the rock are not completely filled or saturated with the fluid.

name: ideal sample shift 2
description: Fractional sample shift associated with ideal position 2

name: api country code
description: Code used by the API (American Petroleum Institute) to identify sovereign nations, colonies, overseas territories, etc.

name: acoustic impedance
description: Property which controls the propagation of an ultrasonic wave in a medium. It is the product of the material density and the acoustic wave velocity within the material.

name: downhole axial vibration
description: Along-pipe vibration measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: litho penetration rate
description: The rate at which a drill bit penetrates a particular lithostratigraphic layer; measured in units of time per mass.

name: true source sensor position x coord
description: X-coordinate of position of sensor placed near source, for detection of shot event.

name: ordinal number
description: A number used to indicate the position, rank or order of items in a sequence.

name: gas water contact depth
description: Depth at which the gas water contact has been identified in a Reservoir Unit

name: aluminum dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of aluminum to total dry weight

name: reflection intensity
description: Rate of flow of wave energy through a unit area perpendicular to the direction of wave travel; for a seismic wave, intensity is proportional to the square of the amplitude of displacement or velocity.

name: wellbore shape
description: Type of wellbore trajectory shape; common types are: build and hold, S shaped, vertical, horizontal. In the early stages of well planning, this information, along with some key parameters, are used to generate an approximate well profile - without the requirement for detailed trajectory planning. This information is also of value for wells that have already been drilled because it is difficult to categorize wells by their detailed trajectory.

name: gravity toolface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between Top of Hole and a reference direction on the drill string (e.g. Y-Axis accelerometer); used in hole sections of high deviation. Measurement is from -180 to +180 degrees.

name: electromagnetic caliper
description: Borehole diameter as estimated by an electromagnetic logging device.

name: residual water saturation
description: The fraction or percentage of water remaining at maximum hydrocarbon saturation, as measured in core analysis. It differs from Irreducible_Water_Saturation because of filtrate invasion and gas expansion from the core being brought to the surface.

name: partial completion model
description: Model used to compute the Partial Completion apparent skin effect

name: length per volume
description: Volumetric length

name: bid number
description: Bid number assigned by governing agency

name: model output measurement
description: Output Measurement (Unit Quantity) for a calibration or computation model

name: lease name
description: Name of a lease

name: burner head count
description: Number of heads of the burner (conventionally, 3,4 or 6)

name: cementation factor
description: The exponent of the Porosity term in the Archie formation resistivity factor - porosity relationship. Abbreviated "m".

name: storativity
description: Product of Porosity and Total Compressibility for a reservoir hydraulic unit.

name: surface location
description: The location of a well, region, or facility/measurement point at the surface of the Earth.

name: centralizer count per joint
description: Number of centralizers per joint, e.g. 2 per joint.

name: zone number
description: An ordinal identifier that uniquely characterizes each zone

name: discriminator 1 cutoff
description: Cutoff value for first discriminator

name: area per time
description: Change in area per unit time

name: extrapolated pressure
description: Extrapolated pressure from infinite-acting analysis

name: eff formation stress
description: Effective Stress of completed interval

name: y transverse amplitude
description: Y component of Transverse_Amplitude in multi-component seismic.

name: filtrate viscosity
description: The viscosity of the fluid filtrate i.e the viscosity of the fluid which crossed the filtering media.

name: rights type
description: Type of lease rights

name: tortuosity
description: A characteristic of permeable media that is the squared ratio of the mean flow path length to the medium length.

name: nmr t2 distribution
description: Distribution of volume fractions for different values of transverse relaxation time (T2); normally represented as a waveform of volume fraction values indexed by T2 components.

name: matrix photoelectric factor
description: Photoelectric Factor of the matrix (zero-porosity rock) or pure material; often expressed in an approximation unit barns/electron.

name: gauge pressure
description: Pressure above one atmosphere.

name: sum positive amplitude
description: Sum of amplitudes greater than zero.

name: reel core diameter
description: Drum core diameter, such as for a coiled tubing reel

name: amplitude difference
description: Amplitude difference between two interpretations. Usually, one interpretation is hand-picked and the other one snapped or smoothed (i.e. a slight modification of the first one).

name: attenuation factor
description: Coefficient used to quantify the attenuation of a plane wave: a wave traveling a distance X will be reduced by a factor of e**(-AX), where A is attenuation factor.

name: tetrahedron code
description: Mineral tetrahedron name, e.g. Pettijohn

name: max shale volume fraction
description: Maximum value of Shale/Clay volume fraction

name: elevation reference code
description: Code of the local elevation reference, such as "KB" for "Kelly Bushing".

name: thorium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Thorium with respect to total.

name: elastic impedance reflectivity
description: Reflectivity due to changes in elastic impedance

name: vertical section azimuth
description: Angle between the true north and the vertical section plane.

name: transit time nmo
description: Normal moveout transit time

name: flushed zone water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of water in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: pressure accuracy
description: The maximum difference, over the calibrated range, between pressure applied to the gauge, with a reference standard, and the pressure measured by the gauge.

name: separator pressure
description: Pressure of the separator when a sample is taken

name: calibration coefficient code
description: Calibration coefficient code.

name: trade name
description: An arbitrarily adopted name that is given by a manufacturer or merchant to an article or service to distinguish it as produced or sold by him and that may be used and protected as a trademark.

name: nmr permeability
description: Formation permeability as measured with an nuclear magnetic logging device.

name: max casing inside diameter
description: Maximum inside diameter of casing for which service or equipment is suitable

name: barometric pressure
description: The pressure of the atmosphere (relative to vacuum) as measured by a barometer

name: wavelet type
description: Type of wavelet used to deconvolve seismic data or to convolve with a basic reflection model to produce synthetic seismic data.

name: sampling bottle code
description: Code for sampling bottle

name: biological name
description: A name used for classifying items in a biological taxonomy.

name: wellhead temperature
description: The temperature at the wellhead occurring at the time of the activity being performed on the well.

name: geometry
description: The geometry of an object; e.g. the geometry of an Earth formation, a Fault, a Field, a Basin, a Borehole, etc. Usually represented with a Grid, Mesh, Parametric curves, or other complex representations.

name: min scan time
description: Scan Time corresponding to the fastest scanning rate supported by the Equipment

name: dominant wavenumber
description: Dominant Wavenumber in depth domain. Reciprocal of distance between successive peaks or troughs.

name: api range
description: API range characteristic for length of tubular goods

name: flux leakage
description: The proportion of magnetic flux forced out of the pipe by the distortion of the field caused by the presence of a discontinuity

name: lambda rho
description: Product of Lame constant and density, LR

name: bottomhole circulating temperature
description: The bottom hole temperature reached when circulating. Due to the cooling effect of the drill fluid, BHCT is below the BHST.

name: mud tank volume
description: The volume of a mud tank or pit

name: riser angle
description: Angle of the marine riser with the vertical.

name: zenith angle
description: Angle from an upward-pointing vertical line, measured in a vertical plane. A horizontal line has a zenith angle of 90 degrees

name: temperature data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for an temperature measurement.

name: cost
description: Amount of money spent to obtain goods or services.

name: flow regime
description: The flow condition of a multiphase process stream; e.g. slug, mist, or stratified flow.

name: fracture pressure safety factor
description: Amount by which borehole pressure should remain below fracture pressure, to allow for uncertainty in fracture pressure estimation.

name: heat capacity per temperature
description: Change in aggregate heat capacity of an object with respect to temperature

name: net pay hc porosity thickness
description: Total Net Pay hydrocarbon porosity-thickness for all zones; that portion of Net_Pay_Porosity_Thickness which is hydrocarbon-filled.

name: min concentration 2
description: Minimum concentration or proportion of second component

name: density quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a density logging survey.

name: water flowrate per lateral length
description: Change in water flowrate per lateral length

name: tensile yield
description: Maximum force which can be applied to an object without causing permanent deformation.

name: instantaneous frequency slope
description: Least squares slope (gradient) of instantaneous frequency in an interval.

name: eou cone depth increment
description: Depth increment of the ellipse of uncertainty cone

name: body heat capacity
description: The amount of heat required to raise the temperature of a given body by one degree.

name: principal meridian
description: Principal Meridian of Jeffersonian_Parcel

name: spinner speed
description: Rotational speed of the flowmeter spinner.

name: max down load
description: Maximum down load for an equipment item such as a drilling jar (lower limit of shock/cushion load.)

name: error band
description: Tolerance range within which the measurement should remain; the sum of the positive and negative tolerances. May be scaled in measurement units or expressed as a proportion of the instrument rating.

name: central frequency
description: Central frequency within power spectrum; average of the low and high frequencies of the band.

name: integrated seismic magnitude
description: The integral of the absolute value of the Seismic Amplitude trace over a given interval.

name: energy
description: Capacity for doing work

name: conn 1 nom length
description: Nominal length of joint/connection 1

name: mobility
description: The measure of the ease with which a fluid can be moved in a specific medium (i.e. rock). The ratio of the effective permeability and the viscosity of the fluid.

name: pipe outside diameter
description: Outside diameter of pipe

name: job count
description: Number of jobs performed or included.

name: deep induction conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by an induction log, which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: mass flowrate
description: A measure of flow rate expressed as mass of material per unit time.

name: apparent dip azimuth tool
description: In the plane perpendicular to the borehole, viewed from above the tool, angle measured clockwise from logging tool reference direction to the projection of the true dip azimuth.

name: surface sensor type
description: Type of surface sensor such as depth sensor, hydraulics depth sensor, kelly revolution sensor, etc.

name: flow head code
description: Code for the flow head

name: min outside diameter
description: Minimum outside diameter of an equipment item.

name: apparent velocity
description: In seismics, the phase velocity which a wavefront appears to have along a line of geophones. Otherwise, the inverse of the slope of a refraction time-distance curve.

name: diameter
description: Length from one side of an object to the other measured along a straight line through the center of the object

name: x direction permeability
description: Permeability in X Direction

name: sampling end time
description: End date/time of surface sampling

name: existence kind
description: Classification of the lifecycle state of an entity: actual, planned, predicted, etc.

name: free water level
description: Depth at which the water pressure and oil/gas pressure are equal; the depth at which Pc (capillary pressure) is equal to 0.

name: electromagnetic power
description: The rate at which electromagnetic energy is emitted or transferred.

name: gas compressibility
description: Change in gas volume per unit volume per change in pressure (dV/V.dp) at a given pressure and temperature.

name: shallow conductivity
description: The conductivity which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: positive threshold
description: Positive threshold value.

name: node locked flag
description: A Y/N flag indicating whether a particular Node is locked and cannot be displaced.

name: deviation skin
description: The skin effect caused by the well trajectory not being perpendicular to the bedding plane.

name: conicity
description: The solid angle measuring the degree of resemblance of a solid to a cone especially in shape.

name: bit number
description: An identification number assigned to a drill bit, normally for tracking purposes at the wellsite.

name: medium lateral resistivity
description: Resistivity measurement using a "lateral" electrode arrangement with a "medium" investigation radius (~a foot or two into the formation).

name: expiry date
description: The date at which a contract terminates or is no longer in force. If the expiry date is amended, this is the amended date.

name: shear strain
description: Shear component of the change in dimensions caused by stress, generally expressed as a unitless ratio.

name: compressional shear velocity ratio
description: Ratio of velocity of Compressional wave (Vp) to that of Shear wave (Vs).

name: affine coeff d
description: Coefficient "D" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: flushed zone dissolved salt volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of dissolved salt in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: max bend 2 angle
description: Maximum second bent angle

name: def value string
description: Default value if string

name: interval bale kappa
description: Interval value of Bale's kappa, the mode-converted wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout Converted wave velocities, for each layer.

name: sand concentration
description: Sand content per Mud Volume, API RP13B, Section 5, Sand

name: thorium uranium ratio
description: Ratio of concentration of Thorium to that of Uranium.

name: tubular string connect type
description: The string tubular equipment connection number that is at the top. Allowed values are: UNKNOWN, 1st connection, and 2nd connection.

name: nom station increment
description: Nominal increment in station number for consecutive stations

name: count rate
description: The number of events per unit time; e.g. the output of a scintillation counters.

name: operations per time
description: Num er of operations conducted in a unit time

name: rock eval
description: Ratio of generated rock eval components per rock mass or organic content of a sample used to characterize source rocks

name: net reservoir log grain density point match
description: Average grain density in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from log data by point-match method.

name: inlet flowrate
description: Flow Rate at the inlet of an equipment (e.g. suction side of a pump)

name: length per temperature
description: Reciprocal thermal gradient

name: method type
description: The type of method used in an analysis activity in the lab or other type of activities at the wellsite. For example: chemical treatment methods.

name: probability
description: The likelihood that a given event will occur, expressed as the ratio of the number of occurrences of the specified event to the total number of events.

name: prime meridian name
description: Name of the meridian from which longitudes are referenced. Normally the meridian through Greenwich is defined as the prime meridian.

name: variable deck load
description: Current temporary load on the rig deck

name: gravity bladeface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between Top of Hole and a sensor contained in a stabilizer blade; used in hole sections of high deviation. Measurement is from -180 to +180 degrees.

name: iron dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of iron to total dry weight

name: water acoustic velocity
description: Sound velocity in water. Typical value under reservoir conditions is 1550 m/s.

name: scale z
description: Scale factor in Z dimension

name: apparent thickness
description: Layer thickness measurement along the borehole, neither corrected for borehole deviation nor for layer dips

name: biotite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of biotite with respect to the total volume.

name: min in situ stress
description: Formation minimum principal stress, the smallest of the 3 components of the diagonal stress tensor (fractures will propagate perpendicular to its direction). Can be defaulted to Frac Gradient x TVD. Can be output from DataFRAC treatment.

name: rock solubility in acid
description: Amount of rock, normally expressed as a percentage by weight soluble in a given acid

name: value string
description: Value if of data type String

name: nmr dc distribution
description: Distribution of volume fractions for different values of diffusion coefficients (DC); normally respresented as a waveform of volume fraction values indexed by DC components.

name: latent heat
description: The amount of thermal energy required to convert an unit mass of liquid at its boiling point to completely vapor.

name: data mask
description: Data pattern which allows storage and access of several types of independent data within a simple representation; common masks use individual bits of integer representations, or individual characters of string representations, to carry independent information.

name: propped half length
description: Half Length of the part of an hydraulic fracture which is filled by proppant laden slurry . It is shorter during fracture propagation than the fracture half_length as the propped slurry follows a gel volume w/o proppant , the "clean" fluid

name: amplitude standard deviation
description: Standard deviation of seismic amplitude.

name: northing longitude
description: Longitude of Northing reference point.

name: molar rate
description: The amount of substance per unit of time.

name: electrochemical potential
description: The component of the Spontaneous or Self Potential comprised of the sum of the liquid-junction and the shale-membrane potentials, both of which are related to ratio of the activity of the formation water to that of the mud filtrate.

name: impedance
description: The measure of the ability of an object or medium to resist the flow of electric current. Impedance is a complex quantity composed of a real term (Resistance) and an imaginary term (Reactance).

name: sensitivity to temperature
description: Sensitivity to temperature variation for a sensor

name: genus
description: A category of biological classification ranking between the family and the species. A class, kind, or group marked by one or more common characteristics.

name: true vertical thickness depth
description: The depth of a point relative to a True Vertical Thickness (TVT) Index. Such indices may be local to a particular zone interval, hence their values can only be compared to other values referenced to the same index.

name: x magnetometer
description: Magnetic Field Strength along the X-axis.

name: multi intersection flag
description: Flag to indicate that two geometric objects have more than one intersection; for example a wellbore may intersect a geologic feature more than once, due to the geometry of the wellbore path or that of the geologic feature.

name: net pay water saturation
description: Average water saturation in the net pay portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: wellhead shutin pressure
description: Static wellhead pressure during test

name: nomenclature code
description: Code built by compounding different codes e.g. drill fluid code built on product-packaging type: 103481052 means Barite API(103481) in 50kg sack (052).

name: top discontinuity type
description: Type of Discontinuity forming the top boundary

name: copper dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of copper to total dry weight

name: h2s service type
description: Type of H2S corrosion service capability, e.g., Proof or Resistant

name: initial water volume
description: Volume of water accumulated prior to the beginning of the measurement period.

name: kaolinite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of kaolinite with respect to the total volume.

name: acid concentration
description: Concentration of acid.

name: name
description: The name given to any object or data item, e.g. Name of Well, Name of Field, etc.

name: graphical file
description: Name of file containing related graphical information

name: titanium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of titanium to total dry weight

name: modify date
description: Date of modification of a data item in the database.

name: manganese yield
description: Elemental contribution of Manganese with respect to total.

name: fossil type
description: Type of fossil (animal or plant remnant from past geological ages, preserved in the earth's crust)

name: min permeability
description: Minimum value of Permeability

name: luminous efficacy
description: Luminous efficacy is the efficiency which a light source produces light given a unit input of power or the power produced from light. Typical unit is lumens per watt.

name: critical gas saturation
description: The value of gas saturation at which gas will begin to flow, as gas saturation is increased.

name: formation compressive strength
description: The compressive strength of an earth formation.

name: tie point phase shift
description: Phase difference between traces of seismic lines at a tie point.

name: shape code
description: Catalog-controlled code of an array Shape.

name: nom diameter
description: Nominal (approximate, for naming purposes only) diameter of an object.

name: gas probability
description: The probability that gas is present in the formation.

name: electrokinetic potential
description: A voltage which results from the flow of a fluid containing ions. A component of the Spontaneous or Self Potential.

name: irradiance
description: Radiant flux per unit area

name: relative dip angle
description: Magnitude of formation dip relative to structural dip; computed by subtracting structural dip from true dip (dip removal).

name: safety drill type
description: Type of Quality, Health, Safety, and Environmental safety drill such as Fire Drill, Abandon Ship Drill, Spill Control Drill.

name: snap window bottom
description: Interval below the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type when snapping

name: total depth
description: The total depth, usually of the well borehole.

name: liquid production volume per lateral length
description: Normalized liquid cumulative per lateral length

name: user data ident
description: User-defined mask

name: gas production volume per perforation length
description: Normalized gas cumulative per perforation length

name: true source position y coord
description: Y-coordinate of true source position.

name: boundary type
description: The type of a Boundary in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Facies Boundary, Sequence Boundary, etc.

name: alkalinity
description: Concentration of basic anions in an aqueous solution (e.g. OH-, CO3-- and HC03-)

name: solids concentration
description: Solid Concentration (Cutting, clays, polymer) per fluid Volume

name: max bend 1 angle
description: Maximum first bent angle

name: gas density
description: Density of gas (air, hydrocarbon, etc.) at a particular temperature and/or pressure; e.g., gas density at well bottomhole conditions or at well surface conditions.

name: gas production volume per lateral length per no of fractures
description: Normalized gas cumulative per lateral length per number of fractures

name: source
description: The source of an entity instance, usually a user name or an application (or activity) instance.

name: elastic impedance
description: Property which controls the propagation of a seismic wave at a particular (non-zero) angle of incidence. It is a function of the material density, the compressional wave velocity within the material, the ratio between the shear and the compressional wave velocities, and the angle of incidence. This property, analogous to Acoustic_Impedance but for non-zero incidence angles, is described in 1998 SEG Paper "Calibration and Inversion of Non-Zero Offset Seismic Data", by Patrick Connolly (BP).

name: event time 3
description: Event Time 3

name: eff reservoir radius
description: The characteristic radius of a reservoir used to quantify the behavior of a reservoir. This is the radius that a reservoir would have if circular in shape.

name: major component
description: The major component of a composition (e.g. the major component of a chemical product)

name: liquid to gas ratio rate
description: Liquid to gas ratio rate

name: effective permeability oil swi
description: Effective permeability to oil at initial water saturation.

name: scal flood direction
description: Direction of fluid flow through the sample in the laboratory (e.g. Horizontal, Downwards, Upwards). Water-oil experiments are almost always horizontal, gas-liquid experiments may be horizontal or vertical. If they are vertical they are done in the gravity stable direction. For example gas flooding an oil filled plug would be downwards, water flooding a gas filled plug would be upwards.

name: matrix density
description: Synonym of Grain_Density. The density of the material in a porous system that is not within the pores.

name: rat hole diameter
description: Diameter of the section of the borehole running from the tester valve to the effective bottom of the well

name: fracture orientation
description: The orientation of a fracture relative to north.

name: direction downthrown block
description: Azimuth of the direction to the downthrown block in case of faulting in the Earth subsurface.

name: gravel packed perforation length
description: Length of the portion of the perforation which is filled with Gravel Pack material.

name: critical water saturation
description: The highest water saturation a hydrocarbon-producing rock can maintain before water will begin to flow.

name: net reservoir cutoff absent fraction
description: Fraction of the summation interval for which data to apply "Net_Reservoir" cutoff criteria are unavailable (including the fraction for which "Net" criteria are unavailable); used as a coarse indicator of the reliability of the summation results.

name: propped top depth
description: Top Depth of proppant laden slurry during the propagation of an hydraulic fracture considered along the well bore. Often named Slurry height. At fracture closure, Propped_Top_Depth = Fracture_Height.

name: equilibration ratio
description: The equilibrium vaporization ratio, or ratio of the mole fraction of a fluid system component in the vapor phase divided by the mole fraction of the same component in the liquid phase.

name: right hidden width
description: For core images, the width of the core which is hidden on the right side of the image (by core box, for example).

name: nominal source dx
description: X coordinate of nominal correction vector to source position.

name: gas water solubility
description: Measure of the degree to which a gas is soluble in water, often designated Rs Water

name: tracking depth operator length
description: Length of the cross correlation window to use while tracking

name: micro laterolog resistivity
description: A measurement of the resistivity of the formation, by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: hole translation friction coefficient
description: Vertical component of the Friction coefficient between open hole and drill string during an helical movement, e.g., reaming mode

name: matrix volumetric photoelectric factor
description: Matrix identification indicator computed from bulk density and Photoelectric Factor; often expressed in an approximation unit barns/cc.

name: critical distance
description: In seismic work, the offset at which the reflection time equals the refraction time.

name: ellipsoid invflat
description: Ratio derived from semi-major and semi-minor axes to define degree to which ellipsoid shape departs from the spherical. [a/(a-b)]

name: event location
description: Describes where the event took place, e.g., Well Head, Separator

name: reflection coefficient threshold
description: Minimum reflection coefficient when processing the multiple reflections

name: faulting time wrt tilt
description: Time of faulting with respect to tectonic events which tilted the bed, e.g. Anterior, Posterior

name: kill line pressure
description: Pressure observed at kill line/BOP.

name: positive slope
description: Positive slope value.

name: anisotropic axis 1 inline direction
description: Angle of first (or only) anisotropic symmetry axis, relative to vertical, measured in the in-line direction. Axis 1 on its own defines the rotational symmetry axis for transverse isotropy. If accompanied by Axis 2, they together define the symmetry planes for orthorhombic anisotropy.

name: property
description: Any SDM Property defined in this catalogue

name: api grade
description: Grade used by the API (American Petroleum Institute) to qualify material and/or equipment used in the industry, e.g., Tubulars.

name: density porosity sandstone
