description: Porosity derived from a formation density measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is quartz.

name: trough trough delta depth
description: Depth difference between successive troughs

name: electromagnetic phase shift
description: Difference in phase of two electromagnetic waves.

name: casing collar locator
description: Signal from a device which indicates the presence of a casing or tubing collar, used for depth control in logging operations.

name: corrected depth
description: Depth which can be offset and scaled from the raw depth acquired from a sensor to take into account the position or deformation of the sensor thus the name of corrected.

name: slope
description: The slope of a function: the tangent of the angle between the x-axis and the tangent to the curve defined by the function.

name: modified by
description: Name of person who modified data

name: temperature rate
description: A measure of the rate at which temperature varies per time

name: absolute time
description: A time value which is intended to fix an event in time, such as a geological time, a date, or the start time of a process.

name: model output unit
description: Output unit for a calibration or computation model

name: refractive index
description: The ratio of the velocity of light in a vacuum to that in the medium in question.

name: fold cdp
description: Number of traces stacked at a CDP.

name: apparent viscosity
description: Ratio Shear Stress/Shear Rate. Equal to Newtonian Viscosity for Newtonian fluid.

name: stacked time interpretation
description: Seismic traveltime interpretation based on stacked seismic sections

name: shotsequence number
description: Nominal ordering matching raw receiver sort

name: direction to source
description: The direction from which sediments are brought

name: filter cake density
description: Density of the filter cake (mudcake).

name: corrosion indicator
description: Any of several measurements which show that material has been damaged by corrosion.

name: separator code
description: Code for the separator

name: bottom discontinuity type
description: Type of Discontinuity forming the bottom boundary.

name: gas sampling point
description: The location where gas samples are taken on the separator

name: gross area
description: Gross area of a region such as that of a lease parcel or covered by a lease agreement.

name: hgs removal efficiency
description: Ratio of mass rate of HGS (high Gravity Solid) discarded through the underflow of a piece of SCE (Solids Control Equipment) to the mass rate of HGS fed into it

name: reduced traveltime
description: Difference between observed refraction traveltime and the traveltime which would have been observed if only one head-wave velocity had been involved.

name: population
description: A count of the number of persons or objects.

name: sonic data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a sonic logging measurement.

name: max concentration 3
description: Maximum concentration or proportion of third component

name: sparse 2d data
description: A data set of sparse location data in 2-space, where none or up to n Properties may be represented at each location. Example: X_Coordinate,Y_Coordinate,Porosity,Density.

name: fluid resistivity
description: Resistivity of a fluid.

name: collapse pressure
description: Collapse Pressure.

name: end element
description: The number of the last element, usually in an array or along an axis.

name: total flow area
description: Total cross-sectional area through which fluid can flow.

name: tbg grade tooth grade
description: TBG Drill Bit Grade based on teeth condition.

name: permeance
description: Prepensity of a material to conduct magnetic flux; inverse of reluctance. Units of inductance but not the same property

name: tbg grade gauge oh
description: TBG Drill Bit Grade based on gauge out of hole.

name: particle displacement
description: The distance a particle is moved from its equilibrium position, as in ground motion associated with a seismic wave.

name: stack alkhalifah eta
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Alkhalifah's eta anisotropy parameter.

name: from mounting location
description: Location of the from Equipment in a From-To connection : Inside, Outside, Top, Bottom. If A is mounted on top of B in the borehole and if From_Id=A, To_Id=B, then From_Mouting_Location=Top. If Packer P is set inside casing C, with From_Id=P, To_Id=C then From_Mouting_Location=Inside

name: trough trough delta time
description: Time difference between two troughs

name: thickness loss
description: Loss of thickness due to any action such as corrosion or erosion

name: oil formation volume factor
description: For a sample of oil and its residual solution gas at surface, the ratio of the volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions to the volume at surface (stock tank) conditions. Normally abbreviated Bo; typical range 1.1 - 2.

name: solids control cone count
description: Number of cones of a solid Control Equipment

name: gel temperature
description: Temperature of gelled fluid (fracturing gel, gelled acid ...)

name: projection distance unit
description: Unit of distance in projection system, typically m or ft

name: capillary number
description: The ratio of capillary to viscous forces on fluids in a porous media.

name: simulation time
description: Simulation time

name: state code
description: Catalog-controlled code of a State

name: electric charge
description: A definite quantity of electricity.

name: mis tie phase time equivalent
description: Equivalent time correction corresponding to the phase corrections. Assumes a specified dominant frequency.

name: pressure measure point
description: The distance from the bottom of the Equipment to the point where the pressure is measured.

name: geodetic datum point latitude
description: Latitude of Origin of Geodetic Datum

name: flow capacity
description: The characteristic of a layer in a permeable system that describes the fraction of greater permeability-thicknesses for a layer with respect to the system permeability-thickness.

name: sale date
description: Date of lease purchase

name: running direction
description: Running direction of an equipment: Pulling Out Of Hole-POOH (Up=-1) or Running In Hole-RIH (Down=1)

name: level count
description: Number of levels in a sequence or portion of a sequence, such as in a hierarchy.

name: sensitivity
description: The ratio of sensor or instrument output to input.

name: sensor type
description: Type of sensor used to acquire data

name: journal file
description: File that maintains process history, i.e., the chain of actions performed on the object.

name: time interval
description: A time value which is intended to indicate the duration of a process or event.

name: lambda rho reflectivity
description: Reflectivity computer from lanbda rho

name: top true vertical depth
description: True Vertical Depth of Top of Interval

name: density out
description: Density of the output fluid, such as the drilling fluid returning from the well annulus.

name: perforation status
description: Not perforated, perforated, plugged or squeezed

name: prime meridian greenwich offset
description: Longitude of the prime meridian referenced from the meridian through Greenwich. Positive denotes east of Greenwich. Example: PARIS PANTHEON meridian in France is at longitude 2.337229 degrees.

name: ideal receiver position 2 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal receiver position 2.

name: oil water contact depth
description: The depth at which oil water contact has been recognized in a Reservoir Unit.

name: material code
description: Catalog code of material.

name: density porosity limestone
description: Porosity derived from a formation density measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is calcite.

name: plane type
description: The type of a plane in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Bed Plane, Fault Plane, Fracture Plane, etc.

name: gas metering line size
description: Line size of gas meter inlet and outlet pipe

name: luminance
description: Luminance is the amount of light (luminous intensity) which falls on a specific projected area.

name: fill height
description: Height of unwanted material (formation sand, proppant, gravel pack failure, workover debris ...) filling up the wellbore

name: avg acoustic velocity
description: Average velocity of an acoustic wave: the distance between two points divided by the travel time of the compressional wave between those points.

name: storativity thickness ratio
description: Ratio of component storativity-thickness to total system storativity-thickness [phi*Ct*h(i) / phi*Ct*h(total)].

name: normalized quantity
description: Normalized property derived by a statistical algorithm normalizing between 0. and 1. the original values of some numerical data; the original data Property code and normalization range may be documented in Remarks.

name: definition
description: A full textual description of the meaning of a term.

name: ultrasonic caliper
description: Borehole diameter as measured by an ultrasonic logging device.

name: fishneck diameter
description: Diameter of the fishing neck of an equipment item.

name: transit time initial
description: Initial transit time

name: water neutron capture cross section
description: The macroscopic capture cross section, i.e. the effective cross sectional area per unit volume, of water for the capture of neutrons.

name: bandwidth
description: Effective frequency range, typically between the half-power points (the frequencies at which the power drops to half of the peak power). Bandwidth is occasionally represented by the central frequency of the band or as the difference between the lower and upper limits of the frequency band, but generally the absolute frequencies should be specified, such as by using Band_Low/High_Frequency properties or by using a complex value type with the Bandwidth property.

name: force area
description: A measure of force area

name: bottomhole static temperature
description: The bottom hole equilibrium temperature (when circulation is stopped)

name: force length per length
description: A measure of force length per length

name: downhole bending moment
description: The bending force measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: shear compressional slowness ratio
description: Ratio of shear slowness (Shear_Slowness) to compressional slowness (Compressional_Slowness).

name: total organic carbon
description: Volume concentration of organic carbon relative to the total volume.

name: screen angle
description: Angle of the screen, with respect to horizontal

name: acoustic amplitude
description: A measure of the maximum departure of an acoustic wave from the average value

name: net reservoir thickness
description: Total thickness of the portion of the zone which has porosity suitable to be a potential reservoir; i.e. the footage which satisfies the Net Thickness conditions and where the porosity cutoff and any discriminator cutoffs specified as "Net Reservoir" are satisfied.

name: abandon time
description: The time that a reservoir was or is anticipated to be abandoned.

name: derived minor axis
description: Flag indicating that the semi-minor axis value of an ellipsoid has been derived from the semi-major axis length and a flattening value.

name: gas liquid ratio
description: Volume ratio of gas to liquid (oil + water) in a volume of fluid.

name: casing grade
description: Casing pipe grades given to material properties that fall within the tolerances set by API specifications; e.g., J55, K55, H40, etc.

name: slot width
description: Width of a slot, such as in a slotted liner.

name: coordinate system code
description: Catalog Code of a coordinate system.

name: drill jar shock code
description: Specific code of the drill jar or shock sub.

name: rayleigh slowness
description: The acoustic slowness of a Rayleigh wave (type of seismic wave propagated along the free surface of a semi-infinite medium).

name: proppant areal distribution
description: Mass of proppant per fracture area (hydraulic fracturing)

name: fissure storativity ratio
description: Ratio of fissure storativity to total system storativity. Usually known as Omega in reservoir dynamics.

name: producing water cut
description: Producing Water Cut from the Hydraulic Unit

name: interval crossline dip
description: Estimation of the crossline dip for a layer.

name: mis tie variable time correction
description: Time correction applicable to each trace on a seismic line.

name: seismic vertical depth
description: Vertical Depth from Seismic Reference Datum

name: acoustic energy
description: Energy of an acoustic wave, calculated as the sum of the squares of the amplitudes of the elements in a wavelet, sometimes multiplied by a proportionality constant.

name: matrix compressional velocity
description: Acoustic velocity of a compressional wave in a given material or matrix.

name: flowrate gradient
description: A measure of the change in the flowrate of a fluid per unit length.

name: alternate phone number
description: Alternate phone number, including country code.

name: borehole volume
description: The volume of the borehole.

name: source orientation rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of downhole source.

name: nmr fitting error
description: Error in NMR window sum or raw echo fitting.

name: avg mode converted velocity
description: Average converted-wave velocity from the surface to the reflector. The converted wave velocity is determined from the time taken for the energy to travel in one direction as compressional wave and in the other as shear.

name: water holdup
description: Volume fraction of water in the upward-moving stream of a producing well.

name: restoring force
description: The force required to restore initial conditions. For example, at the end of a test.

name: dimensionless changing storage pressure
description: Dimensionless changing wellbore storage pressure ("CphiD")

name: blade gauge length
description: Length of the in-gauge portion of the blade.

name: cumulative cement volume
description: Cumulative volume of cement (may be integrated over length of borehole or over time of cementing operation).

name: component 4 name
description: Name of fourth component in a mixture or composition.

name: longitudinal dispersivity coefficient
description: A coefficient used as a multiplier of interstitial velocity to estimate dispersion in the direction of movement for a displacement front in permeable media.

name: heterogeneity instantaneous phase
description: Measure of heterogeneity computed from the Instantaneous Phase trace over a given interval.

name: energy per area
description: The amount of energy per unit area

name: inner pipe outside diameter
description: Outer diameter of the inner pipe

name: resistivity time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a resistivity sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: dogleg severity
description: The change in wellbore orientation per distance

name: baud rate
description: The net speed at which data are transmitted.

name: receiver offset
description: The distance to a seismic receiver from some other object, such as a wellbore in VSP work.

name: electromagnetic propagation resistivity
description: Formation resistivity as measured by the attenuation or phase shift of a high frequency electromagnetic wave; the frequency range for these measurements is higher than that of induction measurements, typically hundreds of KHz to several MHz, and over 1 GHz in the case of the Schlumberger EPT tool.

name: drill survey tool code
description: Specific code of survey tool.

name: perforation distance
description: Distance from the top of the hydraulic unit to the top of the perforations. For use in the partial penetration model.

name: water resistivity
description: Resistivity of connate (formation) water

name: value number
description: Value if of data type Number

name: inverse gas formation volume factor
description: Ratio of gas volume at surface (stock tank) conditions to the gas volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions.

name: cosine of phase
description: Cosine of Instantaneous Phase, also known as normalized seismic amplitude

name: mud type
description: Type of mud used

name: bottom depth
description: The deepest depth of a borehole interval, a formation, or any depth indexed representation of a data item.

name: specific heat capacity
description: Heat capacity per unit of mass

name: min compress outside diameter
description: Minimum compressed outside diameter, such as for a centralizer.

name: cumulative water influx
description: The cumulative volume of water that encroaches into a reservoir.

name: min x
description: Minimum X Coordinate for region

name: well status
description: A property indicating the operational condition of a well: proposed, active, abandoned, etc.

name: up stroke
description: Up stroke distance, as used for drilling jars. Maximum stroke travel in shock/cushion sub

name: transient end time
description: End time (tend) of the Transient

name: choke size
description: Internal diameter of the flow choke(s)

name: conn 2 nom length
description: Nominal length of joint/connection 2

name: fluid loss
description: The volume of drilling fluid filtrate which is obtained in a filtration test under specific test conditions; used as an indication of the expected rate of filtrate invasion into the formation during drilling.

name: array laterolog resistivity
description: Array Resistivity measurement using laterolog (or guard log) resistivity logging principles.

name: geophone type
description: Type of geophone, used to detect particle motion associated with the passage of a seismic wave.

name: formation stiffness factor
description: Dimensionless estimate of the formation stiffness, i.e., ratio between the applied pressure and the displacement of the formation.

name: county code
description: Catalog-controlled code of a County or Parish.

name: eastern meridian
description: The meridian on a graticule that is the eastern extreme on a map projection.

name: well treatment type
description: Matrix acidizing, Cementing, Acid fracturing, Hydraulic fracturing, Gravel Packing ...

name: trace count source
description: The maximum number of traces assigned to the source

name: conn 2 approx weight
description: Approximate weight joint/connection 2

name: msl source correction
description: Correction vector to source position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: recorder scanning rate
description: Scanning rate at which gauge records data

name: coherence
description: A measure of the similarity between two or more functions; used with seismic waveforms to distinguish seismic events and to implement automatic picking schemes.

name: n c6h14 concentration
description: Concentration of Normal Hexane (n-C6H14).

name: width
description: The measurement taken at right angles to the length.

name: max weight on bit
description: Maximum weight on bit

name: net reservoir water saturation
description: Average water saturation in the net reservoir portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: oil metering line size
description: Diameter of the oil metering line

name: frequency
description: The repetition rate of a periodic waveform. The inverse of period.

name: level number
description: Identifier of a particular level in a sequence; used by GeoFrame as an auxiliary depth identifier.

name: parent code
description: Code of the supertype or parent of this object type.

name: lgs concentration
description: Low gravity solid Concentration

name: vitrinite reflectance
description: The optical reflectivity of solid organic constituents of rock, known as vitrinite, which provides an indication of thermal maturity.

name: estimated borehole volume
description: The estimated volume of the Open Hole used in fluid volume/placement computations

name: water flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures
description: Change in water flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures

name: true vertical thickness
description: Isochores obtained by correcting for structural dip in order to account for the lateral offset of the intersections of the well bore with the top and bottom of a layer.

name: response phase
description: Instantaneous phase at local maximum of reflection intensity

name: flushed zone free water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of free water in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: integrated reflection strength
description: The integral of the Reflection Strength trace over a given interval

name: model input measurement
description: Input measurement (Unit Quantity) for a calibration or computation model

name: stress
description: Force acting per unit area in a material resisting the stretching, compression or shear induced by external forces; fully characterized by a Stress_Tensor.

name: nitrogen flowrate
description: Nitrogen flowrate

name: depth increment
description: Length of interval which is used as a regular increment to depth-based processing.

name: yield stress
description: Resistance to initial flow; the stress required to start fluid movement. Specifically, shear stress at 0 shear rate for Bingham Plastic (BP) rheological model, otherwise named Bingham yield value or yield point. BP fluid remains static until applied forces build up to the point where it starts to move. See Plastic_Viscosity.

name: net thickness
description: Total thickness of the non-shales in the interval; i.e. total footage where the clay volume cutoff and any discriminator cutoffs specified as Net are satisfied.

name: integrated cosine of phase
description: The integral of the Cosine Of Phase trace over a given interval

name: uranium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Uranium with respect to total.

name: anelasticity factor
description: Factor used to compute loss of wave energy due to anelasticity (deviation from a linear proportionality between stress and strain). Loss is computed as exp(-pi * f * Anelasticity_Factor).

name: muscovite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of muscovite with respect to the total volume.

name: mwd tool type
description: The type of a tool used for Measurement While Drilling.

name: scale factor longitude
description: Longitude at which scale factor is exact.

name: cement density
description: The density or weight per unit volume of cement (or cement slurry).

name: molar concentration
description: The ratio of the number of moles of a material in a sample to the volume of the sample.

name: feldspar volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of feldspar with respect to the total volume.

name: iadc grade bearing seals
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on condition of bearing seals

name: tubular string location type
description: The location of the super tubular equipment where the sub tubular equipment is attached. Allowed values are: UNKNOWN, attached outside of super string equipment, and attached inside of super string equipment

name: unit cost
description: Cost per unit amount

name: transit time slope
description: Transit time slope

name: integrated instantaneous frequency
description: The integral of the Instantaneous Frequency trace over a given interval

name: partial completion skin
description: The skin effect caused by flow convergence due to not completing the entire flowing thickness. Does not include the skin due to the completion itself.

name: attribute name
description: Name of an Attribute of an Object

name: wetting type
description: Classification of the wetting characteristic of the rock, such as Oil Wet or Water Wet.

name: map migrated depth
description: Depth obtained through map migration of time surface data

name: flattening
description: For an ellipse, the difference between the lengths of the major and minor axes divided by length of the major axis, often expressed as its inverse (Inverse_Flattening).

name: max manifold choke size
description: Maximum inner diameter of the choke orifice

name: top value
description: Value at the top of an interval.

name: gap length
description: The length of gap usually detected in some pattern or geological feature. The length is usually an interval length like depth.

name: base latitude
description: Latitude value used as the basis or starting point, such as in a multiple regression computation.

name: capacitance
description: The ratio of the charge on a capacitor to the electric potential across it.

name: classification scope
description: Per Method expects a maximum of one parameter instance per classification activity. Per Class expects a maximum of as many parameter instances as classes were involved in the classification activity.

name: length uncertainty
description: Uncertainty of a Length measurement.

name: etched width
description: Width of formation etched (dissolved) by reaction with acid on the fracture face (Acid fracturing)

name: klinkenberg permeability
description: Empirical permeability measure derived by extrapolating the trend of gas permeability versus inverse pressure to infinite pressure (zero inverse pressure). The result is equivalent to the permeability which would be measured if the sample were 100% saturated with a non-reactive liquid and is sometimes called "liquid permeability" and abbreviated KL (where L is a subscript).

name: buildup pressure
description: Pressure recorded in the borehole at downhole conditions during a pressure buildup test.

name: nmr quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a nuclear magnetic resonance logging device.

name: illuminance
description: The intensity of light striking a surface.

name: cable speed
description: Cable speed, generally measured at the surface as an approximation of tool speed.

name: flushed zone fluid volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of fluid in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: oil viscosity correlation
description: Model used to compute oil viscosity

name: primary porosity
description: The porosity remaining after sediments have been deposited but without considering changes because of subsequent chemical action or water flow.

name: test number
description: The number (or rank) associated with a particular test activity.

name: stack thomsen gamma
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Thomsen's gamma anisotropy parameter.

name: pressure per flowrate
description: Pressure Per Flowrate

name: estimation flag
description: Indicates whether the data are an estimation (Y) or not (N)

name: polarity reversal flag
description: When set, apply reverse polarity.

name: irreducible water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of water which remains after flushing with hydrocarbon, with respect to the total volume.

name: projection class
description: Base projection type (e.g. TM for UTM_1)

name: cobalt concentration
description: Concentration of Cobalt.

name: weight safety factor
description: Weight in excess of what has been calculated for the job. Used to account for loss or safety margin

name: auto exit
description: Flag indicates module is to be automatically stopped when run in chain

name: thermal resistivity
description: A property of a material indicating its resistance to thermal conduction; an indication of a material's insulative quality. The reciprocal of Thermal_Conductivity.

name: oil flowrate
description: Rate of flow of oil

name: transient final pressure
description: Pressure at Transient End Time (pend)

name: projection zone code
description: UTM Zone of projection.

name: transmissibility
description: Transmissibility

name: standoff ratio
description: A measure of standoff of tubular equipment from the borehole wall, computed as the ratio of Standoff to the difference between hole radius and tubular radius; Standoff Ratio is 0 if the tubular is in contact with the hole wall, 1 if the tubular is centered in the hole.

name: horizon tracking event
description: Type of waveform event identified by the Horizon (crossing +/-, crossing -/+, peak, trough)

name: manufacturer
description: The unique code of the manufacturer, usually a company or organization code.

name: min gas flowrate
description: Minimum gas flowrate

name: digital file format
description: The type of file structure in which the depiction rendering is encoded; e.g. PostScript, ANSI text, GIFF, JPG, Maker Interchange Format (MIF), SGML, HTML.

name: uncertainty
description: Precision with which a measurement is known; often implies a 50-50 chance that any one of a series of measurements will fall within a given range; the unit quantity is determined by that of data value. Uncertainty is not necessarily related to Accuracy.

name: dimensionless rectangle height
description: Rectangle height divided by reference length ("ByD")

name: resolution description
description: Textual description of the qualified resolution, e.g., 0.005 psi at greater than 4 s sampling rate, 0.01 psi at 1 s sampling rate.

name: thermal conductivity
description: Heat flux or thermal energy per unit length and temperature. The capacity of a body to conduct or pass thermal energy. The capacity of a material to conduct or pass thermal energy.

name: format
description: General plan of organization or arrangement, such as for a computer data file or for the presentation of data.

name: pressure drop correlation
description: Pressure drop correlation (e.g., Dun-Ros, Cullender, )

name: moment of inertia
description: The torque needed for a desired angular acceleration about a rotational axis,

name: top true stratigraphic thickness depth
description: True Stratigraphic Thickness Depth of Top of Interval

name: map scale factor
description: The ratio of the scale along the meridian or along the parallel at a given point to the scale at some map point or along some line; each point on the map has a distinct value.

name: volume per mass
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity VolumePerMass, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: integrated mobility
description: The product of thickness and mobility of a permeable medium.

name: interfacial tension
description: The tension between two interfaces; e.g., light and heavy fluid phases, gas-liquid, gas-oil, gas-water. Also called surface tension or surface tensity

name: nominal source dz
description: Z coordinate of nominal correction vector to source position.

name: service code
description: MIS Code of the service and unique identifier.

name: origin longitude
description: The longitude of the point of origin of an orthogonal grid constructed on a map projection. Frequently this is the central meridian, but can be any defined longitude

name: surface torque current
description: A measure of the electric current driving the rotary table or top drive

name: borehole diameter
description: The inside diameter of a borehole.

name: wireline tool type
description: The type of a Tool usually used in some wireline activity, e.g. CNTA, USIT, AIT, etc.

name: grading date
description: Date on which the grading of equipment condition or state took place.

name: gas line pressure gauge type
description: Gauge used to measure gas meter pressure

name: value type table
description: Name of database table where value type may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: medium laterolog conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation.

name: origin z
description: Z component of the location of the origin of a Local Coordinate System, measured with respect to the origin of the "from" coordinate system. Units, if any, are those of the "from" system.

name: inclination build rate
description: The rate of change in inclination expressed in degrees per unit of course length.

name: min net thickness
description: It is common in an interbedded reservoir for sands thinner than a certain cutoff thickness (Min_Net_Thickness) to be discarded as non net or non pay in a ResSum type analysis. However, a thick sand may have two closely spaced shale stringers, such that they create the effect of a thin sand separated from thick sands above and below by thin shale beds. In this case, if the shale beds are thinner than a second thickness threshold (Min_Non_Net_Thickness), the thin sand would be counted as net or pay.

name: velocity uncertainty
description: Uncertainty of a velocity measurement.

name: molar enthalpy
description: Enthalpy per amount of substance

name: surface torque
description: Rotary torque as measured at the surface

name: electrical property
description: Coarse classification of the electrical nature of a material; e.g. Conductive, Resistive

name: n2 foam quality
description: Ratio volume of N2 over foam volume . Indicator of the quality of a foam generated with N2 for well treatment. Below 50% the foam is not stable, above 95% the foam changes to a mist.

name: perforation charge type
description: Type of explosive charge used in a perforating gun.

name: medium induction conductivity
description: The conductivity, made by an induction log, which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation.

name: module state
description: Indicates the execution status of a module, such as Running, Aborted, etc.

name: dosing mode
description: The way an additive is measured e.g. By Weight Of Cement, BOW, gl/sk ....

name: klinkenberg factor
description: Empirical conversion factor used to estimate Klinkenberg permeability from measured gas permeability.

name: bore count
description: Number of bores, as in a production packer.

name: morpho type
description: The classification of rocks from their internal morphology i.e., lamination thickness, inclusion size, etc.

name: volume per mass per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity volume per mass per time, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: non magnetic flag
description: A flag indicating whether the equipment is made with non magnetic material.

name: rotation 2
description: Value of second rotation, as indicated by the second token in ROTATION_SENSE, used in transforming a coordinate system into a new (local) coordinate system.

name: oil water ratio
description: Ratio of oil volume to water volume for a fluid, such as an oil based mud

name: memory guard flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not a memory guard (memory saving mechanism which decreases the acquisition rate above 80% memory usage) option was selected.

name: concentration
description: The relative content of a component; e.g., the concentration of salts in brackish water, the concentration of electric charges in a circuit, etc.

name: shape
description: A visible makeup characteristic of a particular item or kind of item. Also the spatial form of an item, or a standard or universally recognized spatial form.

name: coefficient of linear thermal expansion
description: Expansion of the length of an object with a unit increase in temperature

name: company lease number
description: Unique lease number assigned by owning company

name: neutron porosity sandstone
description: Porosity derived from a neutron logging measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is quartz.

name: interval thomsen epsilon
description: Interval value of Thomsen's epsilon anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between vertical and horizontal Compressional velocities, for each layer.

name: net reservoir permeability
description: Average permeability in the net reservoir portion of the zone interval (thickness weighted arithmetic/geometric/harmonic average).

name: array induction quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from an array induction survey.

name: display name format
description: Specification of how the name of a data item will be displayed to the user.

name: min oil flowrate
description: Minimum oil flowrate

name: n c5h12 concentration
description: Concentration of Normal Pentane (n-C5H12); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.25%.

name: sequence surface type
description: The type of surface bounding a particular sequence.

name: velocity gamma factor
description: Gradient factor g for Faust Nth root velocity function v(z) = g * z**(1/n)

name: relative permeability water
description: Ratio of effective water permeability to absolute permeability. Usually abbreviated as Krw.

name: response strength
description: Reflection strength at local maximum of reflection intensity

name: line thickness
description: Line drawing width or thickness

name: snap depth window bottom
description: Distance below the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type when snapping

name: crushed zone thickness
description: Thickness of the Crushed Zone around perforation

name: region of interest
description: Geopolitical area of interest

name: filter cake resistivity
description: Resistivity of Mud Filter Cake

name: nitrogen yield
description: Elemental contribution of Nitrogen with respect to total.

name: downhole torque
description: Downhole torque, as applied to the drill string

name: hydraulic diffusivity
description: The characteristic of a rock-fluid system that describes the relationship of pressure change in time to pressure gradient. It is defined as permeability divided by the product of porosity, fluid viscosity and fluid compressibility.

name: weathering velocity
description: Average acoustic velocity of the weathered layer, the near-surface low velocity layer consisting of unconsolidated material and rock in which air rather than water fills the pore space.

name: geodetic datum name
description: Name of the reference system that describes the position, orientation and scale relationship of the ellipsoid and the earth, such that referenced coordinates are unique.

name: sediment and water
description: Measure of impurities which are contained in oil produced from a well, as described in ASTM Standard Test D96-82. Traditionally called Basic Sediment and Water.

name: api gravity
description: A measure of hydrocarbon density equal to 141.5/(specific gravity @ 60 degF) - 131.5; usually reported with a temperature.

name: oil fraction
description: Volumetric fraction of oil in the total fluid

name: attenuation rate
description: A measure of the rate of attenuation of a wave per unit length.

name: show quality
description: A qualitative indicator of the intensity of the fluid show.

name: thermal insulance
description: Resistance of a material to heat flow over a unit area

name: energy half depth
description: Depth, within a specified interval, at which half the energy of the interval occurs

name: external boundary pressure
description: The pressure existing at the external boundary of the drainage area of the well.

name: throughput
description: A measure of the mass produced, say from some facility, per unit time.

name: money
description: Amount of money; should be associated with a unit of currency.

name: undisturbed zone free water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of free water in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: equivalent circulating density
description: Drilling fluid density that would be required to produce the same effective borehole pressure as the combination of fluid density, circulating pressure and cuttings loading of the drilling fluid in the wellbore.

name: stop date
description: The date a particular activity stopped.

name: cumulative gas volume
description: Cumulative gas production at standard conditions. At constant BHP or WHP, cumulative volume is not the straightforward sum of volume by RHU but determined by Inverse Laplace transformation.

name: bottom subsea vertical depth
description: Subsea Vertical Depth of Bottom of Interval

name: velocity k factor
description: Velocity depth gradient, dv/dz used in some velocity functions like linear velocity : v(z) = v_0 + k*z depth of burial : v(z,z_1) = v_0 + k_1*z_1 + k_2*(z-z_1)

name: min concentration 1
description: Minimum concentration or proportion of first component

name: avg trough amplitude
description: Average of the amplitudes of waveform troughs.

name: signal type
description: Type of data signal.

name: reference time
description: Reference Date and Time For Elapsed Time

name: x transverse amplitude
description: X component of Transverse_Amplitude in multi-component seismic.

name: bottom true vertical thickness depth
description: True Vertical Thickness Depth of Bottom of Interval

name: fax number
description: Telephone number used for FAX (facsimile) transmission and/or reception.

name: total hardness
description: Sum of Ca and Mg concentration in water, API RP13B, Section 8, Water Based Mud, expressed as being entirely composed of calcium

name: nominal receiver dz
description: Z coordinate of nominal correction vector to receiver position.

name: overburden pressure
description: The pressure exerted on the matrix of a porous media by the weight of overlying strata.

name: fan shape
description: Shape of a Fan type depositional environment, i.e. Elongated or Crescent.

name: source offset
description: The distance to the seismic source from some other object, such as a wellbore in VSP work.

name: slant rig flag
description: A flag indicating if the rig is slanted.

name: gas mass flowrate
description: Mass flowrate of gas.

name: wetting contact angle
description: Angle between a fluid droplet and a solid surface at the point of contact; the lower the angle (measured inside the droplet), the greater the adhesion and thus the greater the wettability of the solid to that fluid.

name: axis spacing
description: Spacing or displacement along axis

name: vibration frequency
description: Frequency of vibrations

name: tracking depth window top
description: Distance above the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type while tracking

name: frequency interval
description: An octave is a doubling of a frquency.

name: packer inside diameter
description: Packer internal diameter (Casing_Tubing Packer)

name: host identifier
description: Identification of a host computer system where, for example, an application is to run.

name: hole azimuth
description: The angle between a vertical plane tangent to the borehole and north.

name: sonde error
description: An unwanted portion of the total conductivity measurement of an induction logging instrument, generated by imperfections in the coils in the sonde. It is measured during surface calibration and then cancelled during the survey operation.

name: tensile strength
description: The maximum tensile stress a material can tolerate without splitting

name: geodetic datum code
description: Code of the reference system that describes the position, orientation and scale relationship of the ellipsoid and the earth, such that referenced coordinates are unique.

name: displacement
description: The linear distance which a point or object is displaced with respect to another, usually as the result of some activity or process.

name: anchor tension
description: Tension of the anchor chains or cables of a marine vessel; may be implemented as a vector.

name: min density
description: Minimum density

name: top subsea vertical depth
description: Subsea Vertical Depth of Top of Interval

name: packaging unit
description: Code of a packaging unit

name: mass per area per geologic time
description: The mass per area versus geologic time. E.g. generated mass of hydrocarbons per area of a source rock per million years

name: tolerance
description: Allowable uncertainty or deviation from a standard; the unit quantity is determined by that of the data value.

name: drill pipe type
description: Generic drill pipe type such as Normal Grade, Heavy Weight, Hevi-Wate, or Thick Wall

name: stack shear velocity
description: Stacking shear wave velocity computed from an RMS average of the Shear interval velocities. In practice it is often determined from velocity analysis on Shear wave data, or indirectly from the stacking velocities for Compressional and Converted wave data.

name: neutron diffusion length
description: Average straight-line distance a neutron travels at thermal energy levels before being absorbed by a formation nucleus.

name: interval q ratio
description: Interval value of the compressional wave quality factor.

name: max operating temperature
description: Maximum operating temperature for an equipment item.

name: memory usage
description: Ratio of memory used to total memory.

name: transverse relaxation time
description: Transverse, or spin-spin, relaxation time constant for transverse magnetization decay rate of nuclei; normally abbreviated by symbol T2.

name: inner outer storativity ratio
description: Radially composite system storativity ratio [inner/outer bank]

name: drift gradient
description: The change in the borehole drift per length, usually referring to the borehole measured depth.

name: strength
description: A measure of the ability of a body to resist applied force.

name: rp66 array code
description: Code or Identifier of this type of RP66 Channel object.

name: reservoir energy density
description: Reservoir energy density

name: unit quantity column
description: Name of column in database table where Unit may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: interruption type
description: The type of interruption in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Missing Section, Repeat Section, etc.

name: mole fraction
description: The ratio of the number of moles of a component to the total number of moles present.

name: optical power
description: The rate at which optical enery is emitted or transferred.

name: stack sayers anellipticity
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Sayers' normalized anellipticity factor.

name: coordinate system name
description: Name of a coordinate system.

name: conductive inclusion size
description: Average area of conductive inclusions as seen at the borehole wall

name: unit object
description: Name of Object where Unit may be found if not specified

name: shear failure mode
description: Mode, or geometry, of shear failure in a wellbore; depends on the magnitude and direction of the two orthogonal principal wellbore stresses that cause the shear failure.

name: calibration ratio
description: Ratio of measurement during logging to measurement at calibration

name: lgs removal efficiency
description: Ratio of the mass rate of LGS (low gravity solid) in the underflow of a piece of SCE (Solids Control Equipment) to the mass rate of LGS fed into it

name: mixture type
description: Qualifier to determine if a component is a pure chemical or a mixture of other chemicals.

name: organization code
description: Catalog-controlled code of Organization.

name: from conn number
description: Indicates which end (1 or 2 for tubulars, 3 for a hydraulic tee,...) of the "From" equipment is connected to the "To" equipment

name: nominal number
description: An integer number used to identify an object or an element of an array.

name: reservoir production volume
description: Volume of fluids produced from a reservoir

name: casing type
description: Type of casing or tubing used, such as riser, conductor, intermediate, liner, surface, tubing, production, etc.

name: moved hydrocarbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of moved hydrocarbons with respect to the total volume; moved hydrocarbons are those which have been displaced from the flushed zone by the invasion process.

name: object name
description: Name of an Object

name: test code
description: Catalog-controlled code of test type or analysis method.

name: conn 1 thread type
description: Complete and non ambiguous identification of the first threaded connection, e.g., "Hydril Joint Type EIU", "Pittsburgh Special ACME-Thread Casing-Internal-upset"

name: critical temperature
description: The highest temperature at which a fluid can exist as a liquid and above which its vapor cannot be liquefied regardless of the amount of pressure. Applies to pure components; for mixtures use Pseudocritical_Temperature.

name: azimuth unit
description: Unit for Azimuth data

name: time stamp
description: A time value which is associated with some event to fix its occurrence in time; often expressed as an elapsed time from recent reference time.

name: direction channel to flow
description: Azimuth of the direction to flow, usually pertaining to a sedimentary channel.

name: max surge temperature
description: Maximum Temperature to which this Equipment can be exposed for a short time without permanent damage; the Equipment will again perform to specifications when the Temperature is reduced below the maximum working temperature.

name: geologic age code
description: Reference code of a geologic age; e.g., Paleozoic, Permian, etc. classified according to the type of geologic age unit (Era, Epoch, etc.).

name: non darcy flow coefficient
description: Non-Darcy (turbulence) flow coefficient ("D")

name: derivative type
description: Type of derivative used in evaluating this transient.

name: instantaneous phase
description: Phase component of an analytical seismic trace when decomposed into amplitude and phase components (Hilbert transform technique)

name: acquisition transit time
description: Acquisition system transit time

name: bottomhole flowing pressure
description: Flowing pressure inside the wellbore at midpoint of the completed interval. Res. Eng. Pwf

name: neutron porosity dolomite
description: Porosity derived from a neutron logging measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is dolomite.

name: entity code
description: Code of SDM Entity

name: measured depth
description: Depth measured along the borehole path from the working datum.

name: wire diameter
description: Diameter of wire, such as that used in a mesh or a slotted liner

name: y acceleration
description: Acceleration along the Y-axis.

name: pi code series
description: Petroleum Information Alpha-Numeric code series. Example 110 for Producing Wells, 400 for Gas Injection Wells.

name: gross porosity
description: The average porosity in a gross thickness interval or a group of intervals.

name: micro resistivity
description: A measurement of the resistivity of the formation within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: port count
description: Number of ports, such as in a Coiled Tubing BHA

name: pumping schedule type
description: Type of pumping schedule i.e. as measured, design, alternate...

name: period
description: The time T for one cycle of a periodic function. The time for a wave crest to traverse a distance equal to one wavelength. The reciprocal of Frequency.

name: instantaneous frequency
description: Time derivative of Instantaneous_Amplitude.

name: purchase number
description: Purchase Order Number

name: avg q ratio
description: Average (harmonic mean) value of the compressional wave quality factor.

name: outside diameter
description: Outside diameter of an entity, such as an item of drillstring equipment

name: tank type
description: Tank type

name: downhole cable tension
description: Tension of the logging cable as measured at the top of the logging tool

name: pressure time per volume
description: Pressure time per volume

name: thermal neutron near far ratio
description: Ratio of the count rate of the near detector to that of the far detector in a thermal neutron logging device

name: deep laterolog resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: shank diameter
description: Outer diameter of the equipment shank; for a drill bit, the shank is the portion of the bit body between the threaded connection and the base of the bit leg (for roller cone bits) or bit crown (for fixed cutter bits).

name: drill fluid volume
description: Volume of drilling fluid

name: avg weight on bit
description: Average "Weight On Bit" (WOB)

name: cement volume
description: Volume of cement.

name: eccentricity squared
description: The square of the ratio of the focus-to-center distance to the length of the semi-major axis of an ellipse.

name: undisturbed zone bound water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of bound water in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: compressional impedance reflectivity
description: Reflectivity due to changes in compressional impedance

name: display index type
description: Type of index used for display; e.g. MD, DSRD, TVD etc.

name: stroke count
description: Cumulative number of strokes over a time interval

name: max tool speed
description: Maximum service speed allowed for, or attained by, a logging tool.

name: circulation loss depth
description: Depth at which circulation is being lost to the formation.

name: tectonic cycle type
description: The type of tectonic cycle, i.e. distensive or compressive.

name: fundamental strength
description: The stress a material is able to withstand under a given set of conditions (temperature, pressure, solution, etc.) without deforming continuously.

name: permeability length
description: A permeability length used in rel per calculations

name: nmr 3d map
description: Map of volume fractions for different transverse relaxation times (T2), different diffusion coefficients (DC), and different relaxation time ratios (T1/T2); normally represented as a series of 2D maps of volume fraction values indexed by T2 and DC components, with each 2D map representing one T1/T2 ratio.

name: sonic porosity limestone
description: Porosity calculated using the compressional wave travel time measurement from an acoustic log with a limestone matrix travel time.

name: time constant
description: Exponential decay time constant, also known as mean lifetime, tau and inverse of decay constant (lambda)

name: static pressure
description: Static (non-flowing) Pressure

name: ideal source position 1
description: Idealized source position 1

name: proppant permeability factor
description: Fraction of proppant permeability retained in the in-situ fracture condition, and due to mechanical damage excluding any damage due to fluid residue. Has the same effect than Fluid_Permeability_Factor.

name: oil flowrate per number of fractures
description: Normalized oil flowrate per number of fractures

name: interval anisotropic axis 2 crossline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 2 crossline direction for a layer.

name: start time
description: The time a certain activity or sub-activity started. Use Start_Age for geochronological time.

name: author name
description: Author of document

name: sliding window duration
description: Duration (length) in time of the sliding window used for processing.

name: borehole radius
description: Radius of the open borehole. Normally taken as the radius of the drillbit.

name: magnetic declination date
description: Effective date and time at which the magnetic declination value has become valid.

name: drill structure code
description: Code which uniquely identifies a particular drill structure

name: affine coeff f
description: Coefficient "F" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: reciprocal length
description: was per length

name: net reservoir core permeability point match
description: Average permeability in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from core data by point-match method.

name: receiver line theta
description: Horizontal angle of position in a receiver line, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: packaging code
description: Identifier of the packaging e.g. 303: 50 gal Drum

name: conductive bed proportion
description: Percentage of rock occupied by conductive beds within a given depth interval

name: fossil genus
description: Name for genus of fossil within some group.

name: volume per time per area
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity volume per time per area, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: kb receiver correction
description: Correction vector to receiver position relative to Kelly Bushing

name: carbon dioxide flowrate
description: Carbon dioxide flowrate

name: productivity index
description: Ratio of flow rate to pressure drop. For oil wells, PI is normally expressed in barrels per day per psi decline in bottomhole flowing pressure.

name: mechanical skin
description: Sum of Completion_Skin, Formation_Damage_Skin including anything limiting the flow across the completed interval. Does not include Partial_Completion_Skin.

name: dip angle
description: The maximum vertical angle that a surface; e.g. a bedding or fault surface, makes with the horizontal, measured perpendicular to the strike direction of the structure. Dip may be computed in several ways, including from logs, from well-to-well correlation, from gradients on interpreted time or depth surfaces (See Time_Dip and Depth_Dip), etc.

name: true stratigraphic thickness depth
description: The depth of a point relative to a True Stratigraphic Thickness (TST) Index. Such indices may be local to a particular zone interval, hence their values can only be compared to other values referenced to the same index.

name: fracture width
description: Width of a fracture.

name: api code
description: Code used by the API (American Petroleum Institute) to identify an industry related entity, e.g., Service Company, Country, another Standard organization, etc.

name: terminal mode flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not the setup was filled in terminal mode (e.g. via an HP hand calculator). This affects the interpretation of the Job_Duration parameter.

name: max differential pressure
description: Maximum Differential Pressure

name: ideal source position 2
description: Idealized source position 2

name: end time
description: Time at which a process ended

name: summed traces number
description: Number of traces in stack

name: window end time
description: End time of the processing window.

name: phase shift
description: The difference in phase between two phase measurements; the result of adding or subtracting from a phase measurement.

name: package size
description: Quantity of material contained in each package. Unit depends upon the type of material and packaging.

name: geologic age type
description: Type of geologic age unit; e.g., Era, Period, Epoch, Age.

name: amount of substance per time per area
description: was mole per time per area
quantity: amount of substance per time per area

name: heat capacity per temperature squared
description: The square of the change in aggregate heat capacity of an object with respect to temperature
quantity: PWLS:specific heat capacity per temperature squared
parent: specific heat capacity per temperature squared

name: read only flag
description: Flag indicating that a record is available for read access only (cannot be updated or deleted).

name: ideal receiver position 0 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal receiver position 0.

name: max index
description: Generalized maximum value of index, typically distance or time.

name: representation attribute
description: Object Attribute name where Representation may be found if not specified.

name: central line pt2 latitude
description: Latitude of second point on central line of projection.

name: interval porosity
description: Interval value of the material Porosity (Porosity for a layer).

name: operator
description: The code of an operator, usually that of a Service, Contractor, Vendor or E and P company

name: core date
description: Date on which the core was recovered.

name: erosion rate
description: The rate at which erosion occurs.

name: gas meter type
description: Type of meter used to measure gas flowrate

name: heat flux
description: The quantity of thermal energy which passes through a cross-sectional area per unit time.

name: volume rate per mass
description: The volume per mass in geologic time. E.g. The volume of hydrocarbons generated by a mass of source rock in a geologic timeframe

name: true source line position theta
description: Horizontal angle of true position in a source line, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: priority
description: Superiority in rank, position, or privilege

name: reservoir flowrate
description: Reservoir flowrate

name: investigation radius
description: The radius of a circle (or cylinder) which has the primary influence on a measurement; material or objects outside the Investigation_Radius have little or no effect on the measurement.

name: transit time ampmod
description: Transit time estimated from processing

name: perforation gun phase
description: Phasing of the perforating gun for the given perforated interval. Standard phasings include Inline (0 deg), Spiral (45, 60, 90, 120, 180 deg), Tangential(90-270 deg).

name: thermal expansion
description: The change in size of a material due to a change in temperature at a constant pressure.

name: hthp filtrate volume
description: Volume of filtrate produced under high temperature, high pressure (HTHP) conditions.

name: total permeability thickness
description: Total permeability-thickness [= kh(1) + kh(2)] for a vertical interference test

name: rotating weight
description: Surface weight of the drillstring while drilling

name: capillary transition zone height
description: The vertical interval height that describes the transition between two different fluid phases in a porous media. This transition is caused by changes in saturation dependent capillary forces in equilibrium with gravitational forces.

name: deep lateral resistivity
description: Resistivity measurement using a "lateral" electrode arrangement with a "deep" investigation radius (several feet into the formation).

name: conn 2 size
description: Size of the bottom or second standard tool connection.

name: sodium chloride yield
description: Elemental contribution of Sodium Chloride with respect to total.

name: personnel role
description: Role of the personnel counted in Personnel_Count; these may be implemented as lists.

name: work
description: Work is the energy transferred by a system to its surroundings

name: water mass flowrate
description: Mass flowrate of water.

name: report flag
description: Flag indicating the presence of a report, or that an item or event is to be included in a report.

name: gadolinium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Gadolinium with respect to total.

name: fault character
description: The characterization of a Fault in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Sealing, Non Sealing, Constant Pressure, etc.

name: inter bed contrast
description: Conductivity ratio between adjacent beds

name: total compressibility
description: Compressibility of the rock matrix combined with fluid compressibilities within the matrix.

name: net reservoir porosity thickness
description: Total pore thickness of the zone; i.e. the product of Porosity and Net_Reservoir_Thickness.

name: welded section flag
description: Y/N : does the section has a weld or not : used as a weak point flag in coiled tubing.

name: model input unit
description: Input unit for a calibration or computation model

name: peak peak amplitude ratio
description: Ratio of amplitudes of two peaks.

name: wellbore purpose
description: A property indicating the purpose of a wellbore (borehole).

name: pressure per liquid flowrate
description: Pressure per flowrate for liquids

name: system identifier
description: Identifier of a computer system.

name: hydraulic unit top to perforation top
description: Distance from Top of Hydraulic Unit to Top of Perforation

name: copy number
description: Number used to identify an instance of a particular type object within a set.

name: resistive inclusion size
description: Average area of resistive inclusions as seen at the borehole wall

name: open fraction
description: Fraction to which the equipment is open, e.g., 50% open

name: specific heat capacity per temperature cubed
description: The cube of the change in specific heat capacity with temperature
quantity: PWLS:specific heat capacity per temperature cubed

name: mercury saturation
description: The fraction of the total pore volume in a rock sample occupied by mercury (special core analysis)

name: downhole torsional vibration
description: Torsional pipe vibration measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: reduced temperature
description: The temperature of a fluid divided by the critical temperature of the fluid.

name: profile conductivity
description: Conductivity profile measurement, used primarily for pattern recognition; may or may not be calibrated.

name: condensate flowrate
description: Rate of flow of condensate

name: azimuth error
description: Plus or minus azimuth error of sensor

name: surface lines volume
description: Total volume of the surface lines equipment

name: battery weight
description: Battery Weight

name: drill collar type
description: Generic type of drill collar, such as spiral, normal, slip and elevator

name: tube nom length
description: Nominal length of tube of body of equipment item.

name: min amplitude
description: Trace min amplitude

name: circulating line pressure
description: Pressure observed at circulating line/BOP

name: event time 1
description: Event Time 1

name: fraction above depth point
description: Unitless fraction of an image that is displayed above the depth associated with the image.

name: relative permeability basis
description: Absolute or effective permeability basis for the relative permeability.

name: point type
description: The type of an Earth zero-dimensional object such as a marker.

name: horizontal well flowing length
description: Total Horizontal Well Flowing Length

name: classification
description: Systematic arrangement in groups or categories according to established criteria.

name: sensor end time
description: End time (tend) as observed by downhole or surface sensors, measured as elapsed time since the Time Reference.

name: gas mass concentration
description: Concentration of material in a sample expressed as mass of the material per unit volume of gas sample.

name: issue number
description: Issue (e.g. Volume,number) of a periodical publication

name: initial gas volume
description: Volume of gas accumulated prior to the beginning of the measurement period.

name: wellbore tortuosity wave length
description: The wave length of the sinusoidal function fitting the deviation survey station points and simulating a real well path

name: logging unit
description: Serial number of the logging unit.

name: permeability
description: A property of rock (formation) denoting its ability to pass fluids through its interconnected pores.

name: friction angle
description: Angle relating the increase in shear strength with compressive strength.

name: stack bale xi
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Bale's xi, the shear wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout shear wave velocities.

name: abandon pressure
description: The pressure at which a reservoir was or is expected to be abandoned.

name: electrical penetration
description: The apparent borehole diameter as viewed by electrical measurements

name: stroke length
description: Length of stroke (maximum travel), such as for a pump piston or for hydraulic jars).

name: facies boundary type
description: The type of a Facies Boundary in the Earth subsurface

name: rat hole volume
description: Available volume of fluids below testing valve. The rat hole is the section of the borehole running from the tester valve to the effective bottom of the well. The calculation of this volume is not straight-forward as the rat hole is not generally empty.

name: affine coeff c
description: Coefficient "C" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: min calibrated value
description: Minimum value of the range for which the equipment is calibrated.

name: calcite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of calcite to total dry weight

name: formation resistivity factor
description: Ratio of the resistivity of water-saturated rock to that of the water solution contained in the rock. Also called Formation Resistivity Factor and abbreviated "F".

name: inverse formation volume factor
description: The ratio of the volume occupied by a fluid at standard conditions to the volume which would be occupied at specified conditions, such as reservoir conditions.

name: fault hade
description: The angle that a fault plane makes with the vertical.

name: unit system code
description: Code of a Unit System in the SDM/OSDD Units model.

name: water saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a formation contains water.

name: well to fault distance
description: The distance between the sealing fault and the well trajectory.

name: pumping time
description: Elapsed time during which pumping has taken place.

name: max hydraulic power
description: Maximum hydraulic power (Flowrate x pressure) of a fluid. Often referred to Hydraulic horse power

name: energy per length
description: A measure of energy per length

name: max oil flowrate
description: Maximum oil flowrate

name: low acoustic slowness
description: Acoustic slowness for small quantities

name: sequence order
description: The order of a sequence in the depositional process.

name: porosity length ratio
description: The ratio of the sum of layer porosity thicknesses to total system porosity thicknesses for a layered porous media.

name: chromium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Chromium with respect to total.

name: square root energy per volume
description: The Hildebrand solubility parameter is the square root of the cohesive energy density and used in petroleum systems to describe the solubility of hydrocarbon components in water

name: back pressure drop
description: Constant pressure drop on a flowline used mainly to approximate any kind of restriction, choke, nozzle ...

name: safety factor
description: Amount by which some operating condition could be exceeded before reaching the theoretical operational limit, to allow for uncertainty in the actual upper limit. For upper limits, Operating Condition X (1 + Safety Factor) = Upper Limit.

name: bend 1 to bottom conn
description: Length from the first bend to the bottom connection of the tool

name: weathering velocity cdp
description: Weathering velocity at a CDP.

name: cumulative production volume
description: Volume of fluids produced by a zone or interval since the beginning of the production

name: net pay porosity
description: Average Porosity of the levels which satisfy "pay zone" criteria; such criteria typically include cutoffs for clay content, porosity, water saturation and permeability.

name: effective length thickness ratio
description: A measure of the tendency of a permeable stratum to exhibit vertical equilibrium of flowing fluids, defined as: (length / height) * SQRT(kv/kh), where length is the characteristic length of the flow path and height is the gross or net height.

name: kurtosis
description: A measure of the sharpness of a population distribution. If X10, X25, X75 and X90 are the values for which 10, 25, 75, and 90 percent of the population is smaller, respectively, then kurtosis = (X75 - X25) / 2(X90 - X10).

name: drill bit grade iadc
description: The IADC, the International Association of Drilling Contractors, grading of a drill bit based on certain criteria; e.g., Bearing Seals, Dull Characteristic, Gauge, etc. grading.

name: ideal source position 0
description: Idealized source position 0

name: casing shoe depth
description: Casing shoe depth

name: begin time
description: Time at which a process began

name: execution date
description: The date that a contract is executed, usually the date of signing of the last signatory

name: max lift load
description: Maximum lift load

name: declination
description: The angle between the celestial equator and a celestial body, measured along a great circle passing through the celestial poles.

name: toolface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between a reference direction on the drill string and a fixed reference, measured in a plane normal to the drillstring. In near-vertical applications, North is the fixed reference (Magnetic_Toolface); for higher deviation applications, Top of Hole is the reference (Gravity_Toolface).

name: lot equivalent mud weight
description: Equivalent mud weight determined by the leak off test (LOT) for a new formation below last casing shoe via increasing the pressure until the formation starts taking fluid.

name: visible width
description: For core images, the width of the core which is visible in the image.

name: antenna quality factor
description: Antenna Quality Factor (Sensitivity of Tuned Antenna)

name: acoustic contrast
description: Interface property which is the difference between the Acoustic Impedance values of two adjacent beds.

name: bid amount
description: Amount of lease bid

name: mwd dpoint
description: Integer representation of MWD/LWD data as transmitted from the downhole tool.

name: velocity ellipticity flattening
description: Degree of velocity elliptical anisotropy, in the range 0 (isotropic) to 1, defined as the ratio of the difference between the major and minor axes to the major axis of the velocity ellipse.

name: net cutoff absent fraction
description: Fraction of the summation interval for which data to apply "Net" cutoff criteria are unavailable; used as a coarse indicator of the reliability of the summation results.

name: rotor lobe count
description: Number of rotor lobes in a drill motor configuration (PDM only). Note: Stator is equal to rotor plus one.

name: cushion type
description: Type of fluid in the test string prior to initial open of the well.

name: elevation reference name
description: Name of the local elevation reference, such as "Kelly Bushing".

name: pass through diameter
description: Equipment (e.g. drillbit) attribute which specifies the minimum inside diameter of casing through which the equipment will pass.

name: tube tensile yield
description: Maximum Force which can be applied to a tube or body without causing permanent deformation.

name: peak peak delta time
description: Time difference between two peaks.

name: gas flowrate per perforation length
description: Change in gas flowrate per perforation length

name: hydraulic unit top to flowing top
description: Distance from Top of Hydraulic Unit to Top of Flowing Interval

name: flow behavior index
description: The n parameter in the Power-Law and Herschel-Bulkley rheological models. The Power_Law model is "Shear_Stress=k times (Shear_Rate at the power of n)". n is dimensionless.

name: max flowrate
description: Maximum flowrate

name: max gamma ray
description: Maximum value of Gamma Ray

name: true receiver line position z
description: Z-coordinate of true position in a receiver line.

name: color map
description: Name of entity which maps from Implementation index values to color; GPD_COLOR_MAP arrays are commonly used.

name: drag
description: In drilling, the extra force needed to move the drillstem resulting from the drillstem being in contact with the borehole wall.

name: base for spacing
description: A flag that determines which reference along a Borehole will be used to space Boreholes on a Cross Section.

name: oil production volume per perflength per no of fractures
description: Normalized oil cumulative per perforation length per number of fractures

name: api yield stress
description: Resistance to initial flow; the stress required to start fluid movement. When using the direct-indicating viscometer, it is found by subtracting plastic viscosity (API_Plastic_Viscosity) from the 300-rpm reading of a Fann35 rheometer.

name: max hole deviation
description: Maximum deviation value of the wellbore from the vertical

name: ideal source position 1 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal source position 1.

name: wave height
description: Average trough-to-peak height of the waves.

name: owner name
description: The name of the owner of an item like a piece of equipment.

name: computation type
description: Computation method used in the generation of data.

name: fill bottom depth
description: Measured depth of the bottom of the fill. (Fill : unwanted material, formation sand, proppant, gravel pack failure, workover debris ... filling up the wellbore)

name: viscosity
description: The property of a substance offering internal resistance to flow; a measure of the degree of fluidity.

name: bha number
description: An identification number assigned to a bottomhole assembly, normally for tracking purposes at the wellsite.

name: begin element
description: The number of the first element, usually in an array or along an axis.

name: loss on ignition h2o plus
description: Volatile Hydrogen component of Loss On Ignition, sometimes abbreviated H2O+.

name: min y
description: Minimum Y Coordinate for region

name: stack velocity ellipticity flattening
description: Estimation of the velocity ellipticity flattening for all layers to the current depth.

name: trace aperture
description: The size of the aperture of the trace on the borehole surface

name: great circle dip
description: The dip of the plane represented by a great circle.

name: bottomhole mud resistivity
description: Resistivity of the mud at Bottomhole Conditions

name: geologic flag
description: Flag indicating that the object or data pertains to geology or was derived from geologic data.

name: dimensionless well y position
description: Well position expressed as fraction of rectangle width ("yby")

name: bend 2 to bottom conn
description: Length from the second bend to the bottom connection of the tool

name: centralizer type
description: The type of a Centralizer used to center a casing, a tubular, or a logging tool in the center or near the center of the borehole, aligned with the borehole axis.

name: ideal source position 2 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal source position 2.

name: matrix block skin
description: Matrix to natural fracture skin factor in a naturally fractured system.

name: current density
description: Electric current per unit cross-sectional area.

name: effective permeability gas swr
description: Effective permeability to gas at residual water saturation.

name: filter cake thickness
description: Filter cake thickness in API test

name: company type
description: The type of a Company, e.g. E and P, Service, Contractor, Vendor, etc.

name: lame lambda
description: Lame constant, Lambda

name: initial reservoir pressure
description: Initial reservoir pressure, before any production or injection occurs, normally abbreviated Pi; sometimes taken as the pressure at the external boundary of the drainage area.

name: cylindrical position
description: Set of coordinates specifying the position of a point in a cylindrical coordinate system

name: relationship constraint type
description: Type of constraint for a relationship, such as Restrict, Cascade, or Nullify.

name: saturation
