description: The fraction or percentage of the pore volume occupied by a specific fluid; e.g., oil, gas, water.

name: photoelectric factor quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a photoelectric factor survey.

name: station inflection
description: Logical flag for each seismic station indicating whether or not it is an inflection point

name: siderite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of siderite to total dry weight

name: length per length
description: Ratio of two lengths

name: hydrocarbon saturation
description: The fraction of pore volume filled with hydrocarbons.

name: eccentering
description: A measure of the amount by which an object is off-center with respect to another; e.g. the displacement between the axis of a logging tool and the borehole axis.

name: carbonate volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of carbonate rock with respect to the total volume.

name: true stratigraphic thickness
description: Cumulative thickness of an earth layer, measured perpendicular to the bedding plane, thus eliminating any offset effect due to borehole deviation or structural dip. Also called True Bed Thickness.

name: smectite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of smectite with respect to the total volume.

name: graphic symbol name
description: Name assigned to a graphic symbol.

name: liquid flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures
description: Change in liquid flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures

name: wettability index
description: Relative affinity of a mineral surface for hydrophilic (water wet) or hydrophobic fluids.

name: normal moveout
description: The additional time required for energy to travel from a source to a flat reflecting bed and back to a geophone at some distance from the source point compared to the time to return to a geophone at the source point.

name: lead yield
description: Elemental contribution of Lead with respect to total.

name: trimmed length
description: Length of material which has been cut away either to prevent fatigue rupture on a cable or a coiled tubing or to connect an equipment

name: housing number
description: Identifying number often etched onto the housing.

name: differential temperature
description: The difference in temperature between two objects or materials.

name: sedimentary unit type
description: The type of sedimentary unit e.g. channel, bar, etc.

name: unit namespace code
description: Code of the Namespace for a Unit Symbol

name: value type column
description: Name of column in database table where value type may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: running length
description: Sum of all the displacements in one direction (generally downhole) made by a downhole equipment. Used as fatigue indicator or charged item in coil tubing operations.

name: boat type
description: Supply boat, tanker, dynamic positioning vehicle etc.

name: mud connection gas factor
description: Drill fluid gas content spike as output by the chromatograph after stopping circulation in order to make or break connections.

name: joint count
description: The number of joints of tubular goods.

name: minor dimension
description: Minor (normally shorter) dimension of an object; the actual type of measurement depends upon the shape of the object. [Used for Drilling Targets, whose shapes could be Elliptical, Circular, Rectangular...]

name: acoustic dispersion
description: Variation of acoustic velocity with frequency. Dispersion may be normal (velocity decreases with frequency) or inverse (velocity increases with frequency).

name: inclusion type
description: The type of inclusions in a rock e.g. pebble, nodules, etc.

name: x acceleration
description: Acceleration along the X-axis.

name: von mises stress
description: Normalized sum of the square of the differences of principal stresses applied to a material, e.g. for coiled tubing hoop, bending and radial. See Von_Mises_To_Yield_Ratio.

name: code
description: The code, mnemonic, or identifier used to enumerate types, occurrences, or instances of some property or entity.

name: detector background yield
description: Elemental contribution of Detector Background with respect to total.

name: reflection strength
description: Amplitude of analytical seismic trace (Hilbert transform technique). Synonym of Instantaneous_Amplitude.

name: avg seismic energy
description: Energy of seismic trace within window, computed by summing the squares of the amplitude values and dividing by the number of samples summed.

name: boundary file
description: Name of file containing boundaries

name: rotation 3
description: Value of third rotation, as indicated by the third token in ROTATION_SENSE, used in transforming a coordinate system into a new (local) coordinate system.

name: mud density in
description: The density of mud going into the hole, usually measured in the active circulating pit

name: true receiver position
description: True receiver position

name: differential pressure
description: The difference between the pressures of two systems, or between the pressures measured at different points in a system.

name: time of first data
description: Listening time until first detection

name: flex joint angle
description: Angle between riser and blowout preventer at the flex joint.

name: wave differential energy
description: The change in attenuation of an acoustic wave (compressional, shear or Stoneley) per unit length.

name: peak trough amplitude ratio
description: Ratio of amplitudes of peak and trough.

name: power supply start time
description: Actual date and time at which the recorder was powered on.

name: mode converted velocity
description: Converted-wave velocity corresponding to a Compressional wave traveling in one direction and a Shear wave traveling the opposite direction, with conversion at the reflector.

name: electrochemical equivalent
description: The mass in grams of a substance produced or consumed by electrolysis (with 100% current efficiency) during the flow of a quantity of electricity equal to 1 Faraday (96,487 Coulombs); conventional unit is the "equivalent" (eq).

name: remaining volume
description: Volume of material which remains (e.g. remaining volume to be pumped)

name: bottom true vertical depth
description: True Vertical Depth of Bottom of Interval

name: chlorite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of chlorite to total dry weight

name: compass bearing
description: The azimuth of an object with respect to magnetic north.

name: reflection strength slope
description: Least squares slope (gradient) of reflection strength in an interval.

name: statistical property
description: A property of statistical nature, e.g. Standard Deviation, Average or Mean, Median, etc.

name: reference depth
description: Depth value used as a reference for other data

name: drill pipe grade
description: Drill pipe grade

name: completed thickness
description: Thickness of hydraulic unit actually contributing to the production.

name: input data name
description: Name of the data used as input.

name: unknown
description: Unknown property type; used to assert that a specific Property Code cannot be determined from the information provided.

name: sequence upper limit type
description: The type of limit bounding the top of a sequence.

name: regularization factor
description: Factor used in T2 inversion (nuclear magnetic resonance logging) to ensure the continuity of the T2 distribution as a function of the signal to noise ratio.

name: hierarchical flag
description: Flag indicating that the entities participate in a hierarchy.

name: facies type
description: The type of a Facies in the Earth subsurface

name: file name
description: The name of a computer data file.

name: phase at envelope maximum
description: Instantaneous phase at maximum of reflection strength. Similar to Response_Phase, but with maximum within a user-defined interval.

name: filtrate volume
description: Volume of filtrate, such as recovered from an API Fluid Loss test. API RP13 Section 3

name: transient initial pressure
description: Pressure at start of Transient

name: water formation volume factor
description: Ratio of water volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions to the water volume at surface (stock tank) conditions. Normally abbreviated Bw; typical range .99 - 1.07.

name: viscosibility
description: Normalized derivative of viscosity: -(dv/dp)/v where v=viscosity and p=pressure.

name: well thermal gradient
description: The rate of change of temperature with measured depth in a well; equivalent to Geothermal_Gradient for a vertical well whose temperature has stabilized.

name: blade spiral
description: Degree of spiral blade coverage 0, 270, 450, -270. (0-straight blade; Negative-left spiral; Positive-right spiral)

name: mud background gas factor
description: Drill fluid background gas content as output by the chromatograph in circulating conditions.

name: luminous energy
description: Cumulative quantity of light

name: tar volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of tar with respect to the total volume.

name: breakdown pressure
description: The pressure required to create a hydraulic fracture in an unfractured formation; it is greater than fracture closure pressure except in rare cases, such as very low fracture toughness and very large horizontal stress anisotropy.

name: item code
description: Code reference to an item.

name: structural dip type
description: This property specifies whether the structural dip is constant, variable or contemporaneous.

name: water production volume per perflength per no of fractures
description: Normalized water cumulative per perforation length per number of fractures

name: ideal receiver position 0 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal receiver position 0.

name: azimuth reference type
description: Type of geographical object used as reference for azimuth measurements: by default, azimuths are referred to True North.

name: interval bale xi
description: Interval value of Bale's xi, the shear wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout shear wave velocities, for each layer.

name: co2 mole fraction
description: Mole fraction of Carbon Dioxide to total gas composition

name: vertical mean permeability
description: Geometric mean permeability in the vertical plane (Y-Z) of the reservoir

name: oil holdup
description: Volume fraction of oil in the upward-moving stream of a producing well.

name: separator oil flowrate
description: Oil flowrate at separator conditions when a sample is taken

name: semblance
description: A measure of waveform coherence with respect to slowness and time, computed as a function of coherent energy to total energy; also called "Slowness_Time_Coherence"

name: elastic modulus
description: The stress-strain properties of isotropic materials which obeys Hooke's law, for small formations, are specified by elastic moduli.

name: element count
description: The number of elements, usually in an array or along an axis.

name: hook load
description: The downward force exerted on the hook of the traveling block by the suspended equipment (drillstring, casing, etc.)

name: bore inside diameter
description: The inside diameter of the equipment bore.

name: gadolinium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of gadolinium to total dry weight

name: migration length
description: Length applied in seismic migration

name: unit dimension code
description: Code of a Unit Dimension in the SDM/OSDD Units model

name: chromium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of chromium to total dry weight

name: absolute abundance
description: Quantity of members in a group, as expressed as a count and count units, such as 5 sacks, 3 boxes, or 4 items.

name: induced gamma ray
description: Intensity of gamma-ray radiation which has been induced, either chemically or by nuclear activation.

name: inverse flattening
description: Inverse of the flattening of an ellipse.

name: temperature
description: The degree of hotness or coldness measured on a definite scale

name: water metering line size
description: Diameter of the water metering line

name: column name
description: Name of a Column in a database Table.

name: ramping duration
description: Time duration of the ramp tapering the time window

name: litho gross thickness ratio
description: Ratio of Litho_Thickness to Gross_Thickness of a reservoir summation interval.

name: battery code
description: Code for the recorder battery

name: lease suffix
description: Suffix associated with lease (e.g., OCS-G)

name: drainage area
description: The drainage area of a reservoir.

name: variance
description: A measure of the width of the probability distribution for a single random variable; the square of standard deviation.

name: interval schoenberg ellipticity
description: Interval value of Schoenberg's ellipticity factor, for each layer.

name: mud density
description: The density of mud, or drilling fluid, used during drilling operations.

name: choke manifold type
description: Type of choke manifold

name: water flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures
description: Change in water flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures

name: event time 0
description: Event Time 0

name: interval velocity ellipticity azimuth
description: Estimation of the velocity ellipticity azimuth angle for a layer

name: stretch coefficient
description: The amount of stretch per unit force applied.

name: drilling time
description: Elapsed time during which drilling has taken place.

name: net reservoir log permeability point match
description: Average permeability in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from log data by point-match method.

name: event time
description: Time of an event, such as a pick time from a waveform, expressed as the elapsed time from a chosen "zero" time.

name: coal gas concentration
description: Coal gas concentration as a volume ratio

name: temperature accuracy
description: The maximum difference, over the calibrated range, between temperature applied to the gauge, with a reference standard, and the temperature measured by the gauge.

name: flattening depth
description: Depth at which flattening should be calculated based on the flattening feature.

name: formation damage skin
description: The skin effect caused by mechanical or chemical formation damage such as invasion of drilling fluids, migration of fine material, wettability change, scale deposit or bacteria. The annular volume damaged is called the Damaged Zone.

name: rms amplitude
description: Root Mean Square of amplitudes.

name: rotary speed
description: Rotational speed of the Rotary Table.

name: volume per geologic time
description: Volume per geologic time. E.g. which volume of hydrocarbons were generated in a particular time frame

name: gpd lithology pattern
description: Name of the GPD pattern used to draw the lithology.

name: matrix thermal neutron porosity
description: Matrix response of a thermal neutron porosity logging device.

name: max density
description: Maximum density

name: statistical skewness
description: A statistical measure of asymmetry in a distribution.

name: correlation depth dip
description: Dip of seismic data, similar to Depth_Dip but gradient derived from the seismic data (in depth)

name: integrated apparent seismic polarity
description: The integral of the Apparent Polarity trace over a given interval

name: zinc yield
description: Elemental contribution of Zinc with respect to total.

name: transverse isotropy coefficient
description: The degree of transverse isotropy in a medium; that is, having the different property values when measured within or normal to a plane. Usually represented by the 5 coefficients of the Stiffness matrix: C11, C13, C33, C44, C66.

name: productive flag
description: Indicates whether object or activity is productive. An activity is considered productive if it brings the operation closer to achieving the objective.

name: kick pressure
description: Pressure measurement used for kick detection.

name: remarks
description: Any type of remarks added to an entity instance.

name: litho pressure
description: The pressure produced by the weight of overlying rock. Also called Abnormal pressure.

name: major axis azimuth
description: Major axis Azimuth of the ellipse of uncertainty (related parameter: EOU_MAJOR_AXIS_AZIM)

name: msl receiver dx
description: X coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: conductive inclusion proportion
description: Percentage of rock occupied by conductive inclusions within a given depth interval

name: flushed zone bound water saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a flushed zone around the borehole contains bound water.

name: compliance
description: The relationship of strain to stress, a tensor quantity expressible as the inverse of the stiffness matrix.

name: decimation factor
description: Number indicating the degree of data reduction from decimation (resampling at lower sampling frequency); e.g. a Decimation_Factor of 5 indicates that only every 5th input sample is retained as output.

name: gamma ray
description: The intensity of natural gamma-ray radiation emitted from formations containing radioactive elements, such as Potassium, Thorium, and Uranium. Measured according to API specifications.

name: vertical lift depth
description: Tubing depth in vertical lift fluid flow computation

name: completion count
description: The count of the number of completions.

name: geodetic datum point longitude
description: Longitude of Origin of Geodetic Datum

name: scale y
description: Scale factor in Y dimension

name: mud filtrate methyl orange alkalinity mf
description: The volume ratio of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid (Mf_Titration_Volume) including that amount required for the Pf endpoint (Pf_Titration_Volume) to mud filtrate, API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis.

name: bending moment per length
description: For a rotating body, the product of force and length of angular displacement normalized for the radius of rotation.

name: property code
description: Catalog code of SDM Property

name: lead dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of lead to total dry weight

name: hydrogen yield
description: Elemental contribution of Hydrogen with respect to total.

name: cesium concentration
description: Concentration of Cesium.

name: zone name
description: Zone Name

name: cross section area
description: The cross-sectional area of an object; e.g., area of perforation in a cased borehole.

name: rotor number
description: Number of the rotor. (For a cylindrical rheometer, each number corresponds to a different size. Standard Rotor is #1)

name: ankerite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of ankerite to total dry weight

name: test date
description: The date at which a particular test activity was conducted.

name: exposure class
description: Classification of the installation location and resulting environmental risk, i.e., liquid, dust, shock,...

name: conductive inclusion contrast
description: Conductivity contrast between conductive inclusions and the surrounding rock

name: memory type
description: Memory Type, e.g., EEPROM, RAM ...

name: graphic symbol file name
description: Graphic symbol file specification. [In GeoFrame, this is typically a GPD file, e.g., gpd_lib/stop_symbol.gpd]

name: gas production volume per number of fractures
description: Normalized gas cumulative per number of fractures

name: show distribution
description: A textual description of the distribution of hydrocarbon indicators on a rock surface; e.g. solid, spotty, streaky.

name: one hour pressure
description: Pressure measured 1 hour after start of test.

name: kb receiver dx
description: X coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: drill motor type
description: Generic type of the Motor or Turbine used during a drilling activity.

name: interval velocity ellipticity flattening
description: Estimation of the velocity ellipticity flattening for a layer.

name: snap type
description: When snapping to the Seismic Event Type the application should snap to the Largest or Closest (Valid only for peak or trough)

name: reciprocal mass
description: was per mass

name: mobility ratio
description: Ratio of the mobility of one system or layer (permeability divided by viscosity) to that of another system or layer.

name: faulting time wrt sedimentation
description: Time of faulting with respect to the sedimentation process, e.g. Post Deposition, Post Compaction, etc.

name: resistive inclusion proportion
description: Percentage of rock occupied by resistive inclusions within a given depth interval

name: two way time
description: The time required for an acoustic wave to travel from its source to a reflector and return to a receiver.

name: true source sensor position z coord
description: Z-coordinate of position of sensor placed near source, for detection of shot event.

name: geodetic coord sys name
description: Name of a geodetic coordinate system.

name: relative dip azimuth
description: Azimuth of formation dip relative to structural dip; computed by subtracting structural dip from true dip (dip removal).

name: fracture conductivity
description: Fracture permeability - width product of a finite conductivity vertical or horizontal fracture.

name: fault type
description: The type of a Fault in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Normal, Hinge, Reverse, Dextral, etc.

name: gas fraction
description: Volumetric fraction of gas in the total fluid

name: magnetic flux density gradient
description: A measure of the change in magnetic flux density per unit length.

name: structural dip removal flag
description: This property specifies whether the effect of structural dipping on a particular geological zone has been removed.

name: mass fraction per geologic time
description: The mass per mass versus geologic time. E.g. the generated mass of hydrocarbons per rock mass per million years

name: electric potential gradient
description: Electric potential difference per unit of length.

name: dip number
description: An ordinal identifier that characterizes uniquely each dip

name: liquid saturation
description: The fraction of the total pore volume in a formation or rock sample occupied by liquid.

name: section type
description: Jeffersonian Section Type such as a Lot

name: std parallel 1
description: First line of latitude along which scale is true, for map projections using two standard parallels; this parallel is NEAREST to the EQUATOR.

name: heater type
description: Heater type

name: business line code
description: MIS Code of the business line

name: flushed zone obmf volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of oil-based mud filtrate in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: flow type
description: The type of flow of a fluid, e.g. Laminar, Pivot, etc.

name: vertical rotation
description: Vertical inclination of the ellipses of uncertainties relative to the wellbore at the associated survey point.

name: file type
description: Generic property for computer file types.

name: sedimentary channel type
description: The type of the sedimentary environment that created the channel, e.g. Submarine, Stream, Tidal, etc.

name: max horizontal to min horizontal geostress ratio
description: Ratio of maximum horizontal to minimum horizontal stress. (Normally abbreviated SH/Sh)

name: averaging interval
description: Length of interval over which data are averaged.

name: water depth
description: Water depth

name: x coordinate
description: X-coordinate of Location

name: shank length
description: Length of the equipment shank; for a drill bit, it is the distance from the face of the bit connection to the base of the bit leg (for roller cone bits) or bit crown (for fixed cutter bits).

name: ideal receiver position 2 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal receiver position 2.

name: allowed position
description: Allowed position of an equipment item with respect to the assembly in which it operates.

name: dielectric constant
description: The ratio of the Permittivity of a material to that of free space.

name: nominal weight
description: The weight of a tubular such as casing or drillpipe that has been calculated based on a formula involving diameter and wall thickness of the tubular.

name: diffusivity
description: A measure of the tendency for diffusion to occur. See Hydraulic_Diffusivity.

name: spurt
description: (Fracturing) Volume of fluid flowing through a given area of porous media which leaks off during the formation of the filter cake. Spurt loss reduces the fluid volume available for fracture extension. Typical Unit: gal/100ft2.

name: copper yield
description: Elemental contribution of Copper with respect to total.

name: magnetic flux
description: The flux through a surface is the integral over the surface of the normal component of the magnetic induction.

name: rms velocity
description: Transit-time weighted root mean square of the interval velocities over a series if intervals.

name: absolute permeability gas
description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with gas.

name: apparent seismic polarity
description: Sign of trace sample scaled with Reflection_Strength; used for seismic displays.

name: volume length per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity volume length per time, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: magnetic susceptibility
description: A measure of the degree to which a substance may be magnetized; the ratio of the magnetization to the magnetic field strength.

name: charge density
description: The density of electric charge per unit volume

name: dead weight
description: Weight of material unavailable for use remaining in a container

name: co concentration
description: Concentration of Carbon Monoxide (CO)

name: electromagnetic propagation time
description: Time per unit length required for an electromagnetic wave to propagate over some interval in some medium like air, water, drilling fluid, etc..

name: value long
description: Value if of data type Long

name: 10 second gel strength
description: Shear Stress required to break a gel fluid previously allowed to remain at rest for 10 seconds.

name: rhodochrosite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of rhodochrosite to total dry weight

name: gas production volume per lateral length
description: Normalized gas cumulative per lateral length

name: iadc grade dull
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on dullness characteristics

name: attenuation gain
description: Change in electric potential per unit of attenuation, where attenuation is generally expressed in dB.
quantity: PWLS:electric potential difference per logarithmic power ratio

name: fluid marker type
description: The type of a fluid marker depending on the fluid type occupying either side of the surface intersecting the borehole (e.g. Gas above Oil, Oil above Water, etc.)

name: grain size
description: Average diameter of a mineral grain or set of grains.

name: surface tension alternate
description: Surface tension

name: shear modulus
description: The stress-strain ratio for simple shear. Also called rigidity modulus or Lame's constant.

name: rugosity
description: A measure of surface irregularity, such as of the borehole wall.

name: frequency filter length
description: Length of frequency filter

name: stab to bottom conn 1
description: Length from the mid-point of the first stabilizer to the bottom connection of the tool

name: drill downhole tool code
description: Specific code of the downhole drilling tool.

name: structural model type
description: Structural hypothesis chosen to derive the cross section

name: tracking operator length
description: Length (time or depth interval) of the crosscorrelation window to use while tracking

name: byte count
description: Total number of bytes used or required by a collection of data.

name: stack velocity
description: The velocity determined from velocity analysis based upon normal-moveout measurements.

name: dimensionless well x position
description: Well position expressed as fraction of rectangle length ("xbx")

name: biot coefficient
description: The proportion of fluid pressure in a material which acts to counterbalance overburden pressure. Used in the calculation of net overburden: P_eff = P_overburden - (Biot_Coefficient * P_fluid).

name: def value number
description: Default value if number

name: inertial flow correlation coef
description: Cooke's inertial fracture flow correlation coefficient (b). Empirical coefficient relating Fracture inertial flow coefficient Beta to Fracture permeability. Non RP66 Unit

name: payout period
description: The time in which all costs of leasing, exploring, drilling and operating have been recovered from production of a well or wells as defined by contractual agreement

name: receiver orientation theta
description: Horizontal angle of downhole receiver, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: box number
description: Number of box in which an item or sample is stored.

name: sequence boundary type
description: The type of a Sequence Boundary in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Toplap, Concordance, Baselap, etc.

name: true common midpoint y coord
description: Y-coordinate of Common midpoint (CMP) position

name: precision
description: The repeatability of an instrument measured by the mean deviation of a set of measurements from the average value; the unit quantity is determined by that of the data.

name: bottom vertical section
description: Bottom "depth" of an interval along a Vertical Section (VSCT) index.

name: drill downhole tool type
description: Generic type of downhole drilling tool.

name: max outer vessel pressure
description: Maximum working pressure of the outer equipment

name: sum negative amplitude
description: Sum of amplitudes less than zero.

name: volume per time per length
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity volume per time per length, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: country name
description: Name of a Country

name: east departure
description: Displacement to the East relative to some coordinate system origin; e.g., the east component of the well departure from the vertical. (Negative value is departure to the West.)

name: classification method type
description: The type of method used for classification: e.g. Statistical, Artificial Neural Net, or Clustering.

name: mass per volume
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per time per length that acts as a parent for other property instances

name: liquid production volume per perforation length
description: Normalized liquid cumulative per perforation length

name: spherical mobility
description: A measure of the ease with which a fluid can be moved in a specific medium (i.e. rock); computed as the cube root of (Vertical_Mobility X Horizontal_Mobility**2)

name: oil rate meter type
description: Type of liquid meter used to measure oil rate

name: 30 minute gel strength
description: Shear Stress required to break a gel fluid previously allowed to remain at rest for 30 minutes.

name: linear mass
description: was mass per length

name: anisotropic axis 1 crossline direction
description: Angle of first (or only) anisotropic symmetry axis, relative to vertical, measured in the cross-line direction. Axis 1 on its own defines the rotational symmetry axis for transverse isotropy. If accompanied by Axis 2, they together define the symmetry planes for orthorhombic anisotropy.

name: radiance
description: Radiance is the amount of electomagnetc radiation (radiant intensity) which falls on a specific projected area.

name: max amplitude
description: Maximum value of amplitude

name: thomsen sigma
description: Thomsen's sigma anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between Vertically polarized Shear (SV) velocities in the vertical direction and moveout SV velocity.

name: stable elapsed time
description: Time elapsed since production conditions were stable

name: storativity ratio
description: Ratio of component storativity to total system storativity. Usually known as Omega in reservoir dynamics.

name: avg bed thickness
description: Average thickness of a geologic bed.

name: liquid production volume
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity LiquidProductionVolume, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: corridor stack
description: A summation of the traces in an upgoing Vertical Seismic Profile that have been processed to retain only primary reflection events and that have been time-shifted to their two-way arrival times at the surface. Summation is over a data window (corridor) beginning at the first break time and usually ending 200-300 ms later.

name: quality factor
description: Factor which quantitatively characterizes the acoustic attenuation of a medium.

name: warmup duration
description: Duration between power-on time and acquisition start time.

name: tool deviation x
description: X-axis component of the angle between the tool axis and the vertical.

name: optimum flag
description: Indicates whether the activity, process or solution is optimum.

name: current equivalent time
description: Computed equivalent operating time based on the time spent at a given temperature and the maximum working temperature. If all the time is spent at maximum working temperature, then the equivalent time is equal to the operating time.

name: trace length
description: Length of a trace or mark which is visible on some surface, such as that of a road on a map, or of a fracture on a borehole wall.

name: north south line
description: Indicates whether the North or South boundary line of the survey area has been used as a reference for North_South_Distance values.

name: pressure gradient
description: The change in pressure per unit length.

name: map scale
description: The ratio of a distance measured on a map to the actual distance. It is normally expressed as a unitless ratio (e.g. 1:1000), or as the product of a unitless ratio and the ratio of two units (e.g. 1 in = 5 mile, or .2 in/mi).

name: velocity ellipticity azimuth
description: Fastest direction of elliptic anisotropic velocity (i.e. ellipse major axis) measured clockwise from grid north in degrees.

name: effective date
description: The date on which a contract becomes effective or put in force.

name: compressional velocity
description: Velocity of a compressional acoustic wave (Vp).

name: liquid production volume per perflength per no of fractures
description: Normalized liquid cumulative per perforation length per number of fractures

name: degradation factor
description: Indication of the extent to which the quality of an object or of data has been degraded.

name: oil gravity
description: The ratio of the density of the produced or reservoir oil to that of pure water at atmospheric conditions. See also API_Gravity

name: flushed zone fluid saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a flushed zone around the borehole contains fluid.

name: last calibration date
description: Date when a sensor was last calibrated

name: max sequence count
description: Maximum Sequence Count

name: ideal receiver position 1 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal receiver position 1.

name: sensor number
description: Sensor number

name: mre longitude coefficient
description: Coefficient for a longitude term in a multiple regression equation for computing geodetic datum shifts.

name: scale deposit per length
description: Scale deposit per length

name: reservoir gas oil ratio
description: The ratio of gas to oil of the reservoir fluid at reservoir condition

name: area
description: The two-dimensional extent of some region of interest.

name: iadc grade location
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade - Location

name: young modulus
description: The stress-strain ratio when a body is pulled or compressed.

name: sdm domain name
description: Name of the data domain, as described in the Schlumberger Data Model.

name: fracture origin
description: Characterizes the origin of a fracture i.e. natural (inherent) or induced.

name: oil gravimeter type
description: Type of instrument used to measure oil specific gravity

name: starting force
description: The force applied at the start of a process. For example, at the beginning of a test.

name: ltlp filtrate volume
description: Volume of filtrate produced under low temperature, low pressure (LTLP) conditions.

name: scale factor
description: Coefficient used to convert or correct data, as to some standard.

name: bit drilled time
description: The accumulated on-bottom, drilling time since the bit started drilling

name: validation flag
description: Flag indicating that validation will be or has been performed on the data.

name: max temperature
description: Maximum temperature

name: shear impedance
description: Acoustic impedance to shear waves

name: max water pressure
description: Maximum water pressure

name: pressure sensor code
description: Pressure sensor code

name: rock compressibility
description: Compressibility of the rock matrix.

name: polarity ratio
description: Ratio of number of positive samples to total number of samples. Equivalent to Threshold_Ratio where threshold is zero.

name: index type
description: Type of index for indexed data, such as Measured Depth (MD), True Vertical Depth (TVD), etc.

name: momentum
description: The product of the mass and velocity of an object

name: version
description: Software version number

name: single shot flag
description: If flag is set, it means that the equipment or item can only be used once before rework or replacement.

name: max rig heave
description: Maximum amplitude of the vertical motion of the rig

name: section suffix
description: A subsection single letter suffix designation a part of a Section, as used in California, USA

name: net reservoir flushed zone water saturation
description: Average flushed zone water saturation in the net reservoir portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: rock solubility in rma
description: Amount of rock, normally expressed as a percentage by weight soluble in Mud Acid (standard mixture of 12 % HCl and 3% HF)

name: optical power margin
description: The difference between the optical power that is launched by a given transmitter into the fiber and the minimum optical power that is required by the receiver for a specified level of performance.

name: contractor representative
description: Name of the representative of the Contractor Company

name: conn material
description: Connection material such as steel, aluminum, plastic

name: wavenumber
description: Spatial frequency, reciprocal of wavelength

name: net pay permeability thickness
description: Thickness of the permeable net pay portion of the zone i.e., the product of the Net Pay Thickness and Net Pay Average Permeability

name: conn tensile yield
description: Maximum force which can be applied to a joint/connection/thread without causing permanent deformation.

name: geocentric rz
description: Rotation of the geocentric Cartesian coordinate system about its Z axis. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: borehole temperature
description: Temperature of the material in the borehole.

name: volumetric coefficient
description: Multiplicative factor (Volume per pulse), sometimes called K Factor.

name: survey type
description: Type of survey, such as one performed on a Well, e.g., Check Shot or Deviation Survey, or on a Region, Land or Marine, , e.g., Seismic survey.

name: unit table
description: Name of database table where Unit may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: pipe cross sectional area
description: Cross sectional area of a pipe

name: crossline dip
description: Angle that a surface, e.g. a bedding or fault surface, makes with the horizontal, measured in the cross-line direction.

name: margin
description: The allowable error rate, deviation from normal, or degradation of the performance of, a system or device.

name: net fracturing pressure
description: Hydraulic pressure exerted on a formation during a fracturing job (fracture pressure) minus Closure Pressure.

name: event time 2
description: Event Time 2

name: end date
description: The date/time of the end of an activity.

name: amount of substance per area
description: was mole per area

name: 10 second gel test deflection
description: The maximum reading (deflection) taken from a direct-reading viscometer after the fluid has been quiescent for 10 seconds.

name: trace count receiver
description: The maximum number of traces which were recorded at any individual receiver for all source events

name: dilation angle
description: Angle relating the increase in volumetric strain with stress.

name: shock level
description: Qualitative indicator of Shock_Rate; used as a real-time indicator of vibration severity for MWD/LWD tools. Also referred to as Shock Risk

name: api plastic viscosity
description: Measure of the internal resistance to fluid flow attributable to the amount, type, and size of solids present in a given fluid. When using the direct-indicating viscometer, it is found by subtracting the 300-rpm reading from the 600-rpm reading of a Fann35 rheometer.

name: thickness
description: The smallest of three dimensions {length, width, and thickness}

name: min voltage
description: Minimum Voltage

name: slippage velocity
description: In two-phase flow, the difference between the velocities of the two phases.

name: longitude reference 2
description: Latitude of second reference point in projection definition.

name: unit quantity table
description: Name of database table where Unit may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: filtrate cacl2 concentration
description: Filtrate CaCl2 concentration in the water phase of Oil Based Mud

name: trough peak amplitude ratio
description: Ratio of amplitudes of peak and trough.

name: nmr t1 distribution
description: Distribution of volume fractions for different values of longitudinal relaxation times (T1); normally respresented as a waveform of volume fraction values indexed by T1 components.

name: bound water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of bound Water with respect to the total volume.

name: min amount
description: Minimum quantity, number of items.

name: processing window length time
description: Length of window in time domain

name: code in catalog
description: Flag to indicate that the Code is available in a Catalog.

name: original expiry date
description: The original date that the contract was to terminate. If the contract is extended, this date does not change.

name: fraction
description: Fraction

name: fault transmissibility
description: Ratio of fault transmissibility to formation transmissibility.

name: line type
description: The type of an Earth curvilinear object, e.g. the line along the intersection of 2 subsurface horizons.

name: method
description: Name of method used, such as in acquiring or processing data.

name: heat source
description: Describes the heat generation related to radiogenic decay in a rock

name: pressure sensor resolution
description: The minimum significant pressure change that can be detected above the noise. This is measured as the standard deviation of the differences between two successive measurements.

name: rp66 index code
description: Code or Identifier of an RP66 axis index measured or computed by some activity, e.g. MD, TVD, etc.

name: oil volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of oil with respect to the total volume; the product of Porosity and Oil_Saturation

name: tko model order
description: Number of arrivals assumed per frequency in Pronys dispersion analysis (TKO)

name: nmr relaxation time ratio distribution
description: Distribution of volume fractions for different values of relaxation time ratios (T1/T2); normally represented as a waveform of volume fraction values indexed by T1/T2 components.

name: projection name
description: Name of the projection coordinate system.

name: amount
description: Quantity, total number

name: subgenus
description: A category in biological taxonomy below a genus and above a species.

name: offset
description: Difference from a reference value, generally zero.

name: projection azimuth
description: Azimuth of positive y-axis of projection.

name: net pay moved hc porosity thickness
description: The net pay moved hydrocarbon volume multiplied by the net pay thickness; the portion of Net Pay Porosity Thickness filled with moved hydrocarbons.

name: data reduction type
description: Method used for data reduction, e.g. Linear decimation, Logarithmic, etc.

name: connectedness coefficient
description: A coefficient describing the connectedness of items, such as the connectedness between inclusions (e.g. lenses) in the Earth subsurface formations.

name: zero crossing count
description: Count of zero crossings of waveform(s).

name: dst gauge type
description: Type of DST Gauge Adapter

name: tracking quality
description: The acceptable value of the crosscorrelation for continued tracking (0.0 - 1.0).

name: mass per volume per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity mass per volume per time that acts as a parent for other property instances

name: generation rate per geologic time
description: Describes the generation of hydrocarbons from kerogen in dependency to geologic time

name: display name
description: A name which is used for display purposes, as opposed to the formal controlled name (Code) which is used for interoperability.

name: model year
description: The year or full date of a model usually of an equipment item.

name: centrifuge speed
description: The bowl speed of a centrifuge.

name: spatial gamma radiation intensity
description: Intensity of gamma radiation represented as a function of a spatial path.

name: second derivative
description: Gradient of gradient of a scalar function

name: casing translation friction coefficient
description: Linear component of the friction coefficient between casing and drill string during an helical movement, e.g., reaming mode

name: scheduled start time
description: Scheduled start time for an activity

name: relative permeability function
description: Name of the function used to represent relative permeability.

name: adsorption volume per mass
description: Adsorbed volume of hydrocarbon components per rock mass

name: litho thickness
description: Total thickness for given lithology in a reservoir summation interval.

name: bottomhole flowing temperature
description: Temperature at the bottom of the well while flowing.

name: axis index code
description: Code of axis of n-dimensional data array.

name: concentration 4
description: Concentration or proportion of fourth component in mixture or other composition.

name: atomic number
description: An experimentally determined number characteristic of a chemical element that represents the number of protons in the nucleus which in a neutral atom equals the number of electrons outside of the nucleus and that determines the place of the element in the periodic table.

name: residual hydrocarbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of residual hydrocarbons with respect to the total volume; residual hydrocarbons are those still in place in the flushed zone after the invasion process.

name: porosity
description: Pore volume per unit gross volume. Porosity is determined from measurements on cores or interpreted from logs.

name: oil temperature
description: The temperature of oil under certain conditions.

name: reciprocal velocity
description: The reciprocal of velocity

name: water viscosity correlation
description: Model used to compute water viscosity

name: event subclass
description: Event classification by Subclass

name: integrated seismic amplitude
description: The integral of the Seismic Amplitude trace over a given interval.

name: relative bearing
description: Angle measured clockwise from top of hole to tool angular reference point in the plane perpendicular to the tool axis, viewed from above the tool.

name: parameter label
description: String carrying the short explanation of a parameter, for use in user interface

name: fluid phase
description: The phase of a fluid (gas or liquid)

name: drawdown pressure
description: The difference in shut in and flowing bottomhole pressures, at a constant rate of fluid production.

name: initial water saturation
description: Water Saturation at the beginning of the test, experiment or production.

name: rock thermal conductivity
description: Thermal conductivity of rock

name: investigation radius increase
description: Increase of candidate borehole investigation radius

name: avg shear velocity
description: Average shear wave velocity, from the surface to the reflector. The shear wave velocity is determined from the two-way vertical time taken for the energy to travel to the reflector and back as a Shear wave.

name: iadc code
description: International Association of Drilling Contractor Code, used for drill bits.

name: max element count
description: Maximum number of elements in a group or collection.

name: mineral density
description: The density of a mineral.

name: oil concentration
description: Oil Concentration per fluid Volume

name: azimuth
description: Horizontal angle measured clockwise from true North. (Also referred to as True Bearing.) Occasionally azimuth will be specified relative to some other reference.

name: bulk density correction
description: Correction to the Bulk Density log, as measured with a Gamma-gamma type logging device; used as an indication of hole condition to validate the Bulk_Density measurement; conventionally abbreviated DRHO.

name: fossil species
description: Name for species of fossil within some genus.

name: outer continental shelf name
description: Name of the submerged land area called the Outer Continental Shelf

name: bit run number
description: Sequence number of the bit run.

name: anisotropic axis 2 inline direction
description: Angle of second anisotropic symmetry axis, relative to vertical, measured in the in-line direction. Taken together with Axis 1, Axis 2 is used to define the symmetry planes for orthorhombic anisotropy.

name: mud phenolphthalein alkalinity pm
description: The volume ratio of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid (Pm_Titration_Volume) to mud volume in API Mud Phenolphthalein Alkalinity test (API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis).

name: nom source depth
description: Planned depth for the source

name: international aircraft regulation
description: International Aircraft Transportation Regulation pertaining to this type of Battery, e.g., IATA 3090 Cargo Only

name: hydrocarbon flowrate
description: Rate of flow of hydrocarbons (oil, gas and condensate)

name: iadc grade inner rows
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on condition of inner rows

name: peak peak delta amplitude
description: Amplitude difference between two peaks.

name: force per force
description: Ratio of two forces

name: data compression rate
description: The rate at which data is compressed

name: dry weight fraction
description: The ratio of the dry weight of a component of a system to the total dry weight of the system.

name: pyrite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of pyrite to total dry weight

name: multi comp magnitude
description: Magnitude of multi component seismic

name: central line pt1 longitude
description: Longitude of first point on central line of projection.

name: dowell chemical code
description: Reference to the Dowell chemical product catalog

name: geocentric dy
description: Y component of the translation of the center of a geodetic datum. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: mud resistivity out
description: The electrical resistivity of mud coming out of the hole, usually measured in the ditch before the shale shakers

name: setting mode
description: Mode for setting a plug or packer: by compression or inflation

name: top charge offset
description: Distance from the bottom (make-up plane) of the gun or the assembly of guns to the upper perforating charge

name: sampling start time
description: Starting date/time of surface sampling

name: theta angle
description: The horizontal angle measured counterclockwise from the x-axis.

name: choke manifold code
description: Code for the choke manifold

name: true receiver position y coord
description: Y-coordinate of true receiver position.

name: max allowable flowrate
description: Maximum allowable flowrate for the equipment

name: caliper
description: Borehole diameter as measured by a logging device: a record of the borehole or the internal diameter of tubular goods.

name: time increment
description: Time increment between samples indexed by time.

name: value domain code
description: Code of an SDM Value Domain

name: tool deviation y
description: Y-axis component of the angle between the tool axis and the vertical.

name: min porosity
description: Minimum value for Porosity

name: micro normal resistivity
description: Micro Resistivity measurement using a "normal" electrode arrangement; traditionally combined with Micro Inverse Resistivity in a Microlog survey for identifying permeable beds.

name: electric current
description: Flow of electric charge within an electromagnetic field, per unit time.

name: station residual static
description: Residual static information (time) for each station

name: downhole weight on bit
description: The weight on bit measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: min threshold
description: Minimum threshold value.

name: water production volume per number of fractures
description: Normalized water cumulative per number of fractures

name: location
description: The location of any Earth, Region, Equipment, or other entities relative to a coordinate system.

name: source file
description: File containing the original description of the object, e.g., TIF file for an image.

name: map file
description: Name of file containing standard map.

name: flushed zone hydrocarbon saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a flushed zone around the borehole contains hydrocarbons.

name: elastic limit
description: The greatest stress that can be applied to a body without causing permanent deformation.

name: medium conductivity
description: The conductivity which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contain fluids which are a mixture of mud filtrate, connate water and possibly hydrocarbons.

name: upset diameter
description: Upset diameter (such as replaceable sleeve stabilizer)

name: ray velocity
description: The velocity in the direction of energy transport; in anisotropic media it is different from the direction in which the phase velocity is measured. Also called group velocity.

name: geopolitical region code
description: The code/name given to a geopolitical region, e.g. Nation, State, County, Province, Community, etc.

name: max bend angle
description: Maximum bend angle range available, as in a bent sub.

name: water production volume per perforation length
description: Normalized water cumulative per perforation length

name: burner code
description: Code for burner equipment

name: gain
description: An increase in amplitude or power from one point in a system to another, such as between input and output.

name: effective permeability oil
description: The measure of the capacity of oil to flow through a rock when the pore spaces of the rock contain other fluids.

name: amplitude
description: The extent or range of a property; especially, the maximum departure of a wave from its average value.

name: specific productivity index
description: Rate of fluid produced per unit change in limiting pressure per unit of reservoir thickness. For oil wells, PIs is normally expressed in barrels per day per psi per foot of net reservoir thickness.

name: table name
description: Name of a database Table.

name: hydraulic fracture stage
description: Whether the fracture is considered after closure or at the end of job.

name: show description
description: A textual description of the hydrocarbon shows in a rock sample.

name: crossflow flag
description: Indicates presence of crossflow

name: thomsen epsilon
description: Thomsen's epsilon anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between vertical and horizontal Compressional velocities.

name: hydrophone type
description: Type of geophone, used to detect pressure changes associated with the passage of a seismic wave.

name: archie porosity exponent
description: The exponent of the Porosity term in the Archie formation resistivity factor - porosity relationship. Abbreviated "m".

name: gradient
description: The change in the value of a quantity per unit distance in a specified direction.

name: feature intersection type
description: Defines how a Wellbore intersects with a Geologic Feature

name: altitude
description: Height above a reference level, such as mean sea level.

name: permeability transverse path
description: Permeability measured in the plane transverse to the length of the core cylinder. This may be represented as a single measurement in the flow plane or as a two component permeability represented as a measurement along an arbitrary diameter and another along an orthogonal path in the same plane.

name: formation volume factor
description: The ratio of the volume occupied by a fluid at specified conditions, such as reservoir conditions, to the volume which would be occupied at standard conditions.

name: engine total time
description: Time spent by an engine in operating condition since the last overhaul.

name: displacement velocity
description: The velocity of the shock or displacement front.

name: preferred flag
description: An indicator which shows that a particular item is preferred over another, normally as a result of some interpretation or validation process.

name: casson yield stress
description: Resistance to initial flow; the stress required to start fluid movement. The Casson model equation is: SQRT(Shear_Stress) = SQRT(Yield_Stress) + SQRT(Plastic_Viscosity X Shear_Rate)

name: conductivity
description: A measure of the quantity of electricity transferred across unit area per unit potential gradient per unit time. In isotropic material, it is the reciprocal of Resistivity. Sometimes called Specific Conductance.

name: amplitude correction
description: Amplitude correction applied to one side of an intersection

name: tensile failure mode
description: Mode, or geometry, of tensile failure in a wellbore; depends on the direction of the principal wellbore stress that causes the tensile failure.

name: relationship type
description: Type of relationship between two objects: Containment, Reference, Supertype, Catalog,etc.

name: inner boundary condition type
description: Description of the inner boundary condition for a well test model.

name: critical pressure
description: The pressure needed to condense a vapor at its critical temperature. Applies to pure components; for mixtures use Pseudocritical_Pressure.

name: bulk modulus
description: The stress-strain ratio under simple hydrostatic pressure. k = Delta-P / (Delta V / V), where Delta-P, -V denote the change in Pressure and Volume.

name: heterogeneity reflection strength
description: Measure of heterogeneity computed from the Reflection Strength trace over a given interval.

name: angular dispersion
description: Variation of acoustic velocity with direction, distorting the shape of a wavetrain.

name: packer depth
description: Depth at which the packer is set.

name: from entity code
description: Code of Entity from which the relationship originates.

name: force per length
description: Force per unit length

name: potassium ion concentration
description: Potassium K+ cation concentration

name: direction current
description: The azimuth of the flow direction that insured transportation an deposition of the sediments.

name: max voltage
description: Maximum Voltage

name: energy per mass
description: Energy per mass, also called specific energy

name: counterion conductivity
description: The equivalent conductivity of the counterions (cations) in the diffuse layer around clay particles; ratio of conductivity to cation concentration. Refer to Waxman-Smits, Dual-Water models.

name: rectangular position
description: Set of coordinates specifying the position of a point in a rectangular coordinate system

name: avg peak amplitude
description: Average of the amplitudes of waveform peaks.

name: top location
description: The location of the top of any Entity with a geometric extent (e.g., Zone Interval, Borehole, Borehole Segment, Rig, Arc, Edge, etc.). It is represented by some position relative to a coordinate system.

name: equivalent dose rate
description: The amount of radioactivity in a substance of interest over time

name: stack anisotropic axis 1 inline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 1 inline direction for all layers to the current depth.

name: fracture condition
description: Characterizes the condition of the fracture with respect to its void space; e.g. Open, Closed, Vuggy, etc.

name: reciprocal electric potential difference
description: was per electric potential

name: heterogeneity instantaneous frequency
description: Measure of heterogeneity computed from the Instantaneous Frequency trace over a given interval.

name: show type
description: The type of hydrocarbon show from a Well or from a Sample (Core, Cuttings, etc.): e.g. Gas, Oil, etc.

name: range number
description: Jeffersonian Range Number

name: rock class
description: Classification of rocks into Chemical, Volcaniclastic, etc.

name: mandatory
description: Flag indicating if a relationship is mandatory or optional for the referencing object.

name: capillary pressure function
description: Name of the function used to represent capillary pressure.

name: duration
description: Elapsed time from the start to the finish of a process or activity.

name: fracture density
description: Density of fracture occurrence, often measured as a function of linear trace length of fractures observed in a given surface area.

name: treatment number
description: Internal Dowell treatment number

name: initial gas oil ratio
description: Gas-Oil Ratio at the beginning of the production.

name: bottomhole temperature
description: The temperature at the bottom of a borehole occurring at the time of the activity being performed on the well.

name: volume
description: A measure of the space occupied by a body in cubic units; e.g., cm3, in3, quarts, liters, etc.

name: source orientation
description: Downhole source orientation vector.

name: nmr surface relaxivity
description: NMR surface relaxivity

name: deep conductivity
description: The conductivity which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: circulating pressure
description: Fluid pressure under circulating conditions.

name: foreign system
description: Type of seismic system: Charisma, IESX

name: conn 1 type
description: Type of the top or the first standard tool connection.

name: storativity thickness
description: The product of the Storativity of a layer and its thickness [phi*Ct*h].

name: tracking depth window bottom
description: Distance below the picked Z to search for the Event_Type and Snap_Type while tracking

name: fracture azimuth
description: The azimuth of a fracture usually in an interval of the borehole.

name: heavy phase flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of heavy phase component of fluid.

name: specific heat
description: The amount of heat in calories required to raise the temperature of 1 gram of substance by 1 degree Celsius.

name: max pressure
description: Maximum pressure

name: drill operation mask
description: Mask for the drilling operating mode, such as 0001 - Rotating, 0010 - Sliding, 0100 - Reaming, 1000 - Trip in, 10000 - Trip out

name: fracture closure pressure
description: Magnitude of the stress required to open a preexisting fracture. Assumed to be equal to the least principal stress which acts perpendicular to the face of the fracture, trying to keep it closed. Above it, the fracture is open, closed below.

name: acoustic attenuation
description: The amount of reduction in the amplitude of an acoustic wave.

name: diameter unit
description: Unit for diameter data.

name: montmorillonite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of illite with respect to the total volume.

name: relative permeability gas
description: Ratio of effective gas permeability to absolute permeability. Usually abbreviated as Krg

name: z factor
description: The factor which corrects for the deviation of a gas from the ideal gas law when calculating PVT relationships.

name: fluid compressional slowness
description: Acoustic slowness of a fluid; the slowness of the compressional wave.

name: conn 2 inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of tool joint/connection 2

name: velocity gradient in time
description: First derivative of velocity versus time.

name: solid angle
description: A measure of the field of view from some specific vantage point occupied by an object.

name: representation type
description: The type of computer representation used to manipulate a property value, e.g. Grid, Array, Primitive, etc.

name: eff inside diameter
description: Effective inside diameter for stiffness, as used for drilling tools.

name: left hidden width
description: For core images, the width of the core which is hidden on the left side of the image (by core box, for example).

name: hydrocarbon pore volume
description: The pore volume of a reservoir occupied by hydrocarbons in either the vapor or liquid phase.

name: area per mass
description: An amount of surface corresponding to a unit mass.

name: well to fault angle
description: The angle between the well and either sealing fault in a wedge well test model.

name: count
description: A number indicating the number of occurrences of something.

name: array resistivity
description: Formation resistivity as measured by a device capable of taking measurements of at various combinations of resolution, depth of investigation and/or in different azimuthal directions.

name: sonic porosity sandstone
description: Porosity calculated using the compressional wave travel time measurement from an acoustic log with a sandstone matrix travel time.

name: gas productivity index
description: Ratio of gas flow rate to pressure drop.

name: well count
description: The count of the numbers of wells.

name: anisotropic axis 2 crossline direction
description: Angle of second anisotropic symmetry axis, relative to vertical, measured in the cross-line direction. Taken together with Axis 1, Axis 2 is used to define the symmetry planes for orthorhombic anisotropy.

name: length compressed
description: Length of an equipment item such as a mechanical jar in compressed position

name: residual hydrocarbon saturation
description: The fraction or percentage of hydrocarbons remaining following the production of hydrocarbons from the reservoir.

name: auto start
description: Flag indicates module is to be automatically started when run in chain

name: formation system type
description: Formation system assigned by the client

name: offshore block number
description: Identification of the Offshore block where the well is located

name: direction channel to axis
description: Azimuth of the direction to an axis, usually pertaining to a sedimentary channel.

name: c7plus specific gravity
description: Specific Gravity versus air at standard conditions of the Heptane (C7H14) and heavier component found in crude oil

name: centralizer outside diameter
description: Centralizer outside diameter

name: nmr amplitude distribution
description: Distribution of nuclear magnetic resonance amplitudes for different values of transverse relaxation time (T2); normally represented as a waveform of amplitude values indexed by T2 components.

name: skin factor
description: The term that accounts for additional pressure drops in the immediate vicinity of a well in well performance calculations. A positive skin indicates damaged conditions, negative indicates stimulated conditions.

name: sensor standoff
description: The distance from a sensor to the medium being investigated, such as from a logging sonde to the wall of the borehole.

name: external drainage radius
description: The characteristic radius to the outer drainage boundary of a field or a reservoir

name: volume per time per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity volume per time per time, which acts as the parent for other Property instances

name: pickup hook load
description: Driller estimate of the average pickup hook load (pickup weight) over the reporting period.

name: region initialization
description: Index to indicate that a region is initialized

name: density porosity dolomite
description: Porosity derived from a formation density measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is dolomite.

name: alkhalifah eta
description: Alkhalifah's eta anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout Compressional velocities.

name: temperature unit
description: Unit for temperature data

name: apparent dip azimuth north
description: In the plane perpendicular to the borehole, viewed from above the tool, angle measured clockwise from the projection of the north direction to the projection of the true dip azimuth.

name: api pin conn type
description: API pin connection type

name: well job count
description: Total Number of jobs

name: tectonic feature type
description: The type of tectonic environment associated with an Earth subsurface, e.g. Fault, Fold, etc.

name: gross thickness
description: Total thickness of a zone or a collection of zones, including portions which may not be of interest; may still be subject to discriminator cutoffs specified as "Initial".

name: schoenberg ellipticity
description: Schoenberg's ellipticity factor, the ratio of horizontal to vertical velocity

name: cutter set weight
description: Approximate weight of the set of cutters

name: hthp filter cake thickness
description: Thickness of filter cake produced under high temperature, high pressure (HTHP) conditions.

name: permeability thickness
description: The product of permeability and thickness of the body acting as a conduit.

name: flushed zone water saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a flushed zone around the borehole contains water.

name: included
description: A flag indicating whether an object is included or excluded from the spatial extent of a containing object.

name: unit code
description: Code of a Unit Symbol in the SDM/OSDD Units model or of an RP66 Unit expression.

name: iadc grade reason pulled
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on reason for pulling bit.

name: clay dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of clay to total dry weight

name: eccentricity
description: The ratio of the focus-to-center distance to the length of the semi-major axis of an ellipse.

name: displaced fluid type
description: Type of fluid displaced by the injection of another fluid.

name: litho description
description: Textual description of the lithology.

name: y coordinate
description: Y-coordinate of Location

name: fracture normal weakness
description: The ratio of normal compliance of the fracture to the total normal compliance of the fractured rock. It indicates how much of the total compliance of the fractured rock is due to the fractures. See Compliance.

name: permittivity anisotropy
description: Change in permittivity based upon the direction in which it is measured.

name: gooseneck radius
description: Radius of the gooseneck in a Coil Tubing Unit, along which the tubing is bent; used in the fatigue model

name: casing inside diameter
description: Casing inner diameter

name: propped width
description: Width of the proppant laden volume within an hydraulic fracture (hydraulic fracturing). Smaller during fracture propagation than the fracture width.

name: logging cable flag
description: Y/N: tells if there is a wireline cable inside the tubing allowing logging

name: standing water flag
description: Indicates if there is standing, motionless water

name: aluminum concentration
description: Concentration of Aluminum by weight.

name: oil flowrate per perforation length
description: Change in oil flowrate per perforation length

name: fracture length
description: The length of one wing of a fracture.

name: magnetic dipole moment
description: A measure of the overall polarity of a system, indicated by the separation of all magnetic diploes present.

name: gas holdup
description: Volume fraction of gas in the upward-moving stream of a producing well.

name: total formation volume factor
description: Ratio of fluid volume (liquid + total solution gas) at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions to the volume of liquid and residual solution gas at surface (stock tank) conditions. Used for two-phase systems; abbreviated Bt; typical range 1.1 - 200.

name: echo amplitude
description: The amplitude of an echo signal.

name: max gas flowrate
description: Maximum gas flowrate

name: density porosity
description: Porosity derived from a formation density measurement.

name: inline dip
description: Angle that a surface, e.g. a bedding or fault surface, makes with the horizontal, measured in the in-line direction.

name: coal gas volume per mass
description: Volume of gas production per mass in coal, for example the Langmuir volume constant.

name: core box count
description: The number of core boxes containing samples from a cored borehole interval in a particular well.

name: critical saturation
description: The value of saturation of a specific fluid phase at which the fluid will first begin to flow as saturation is increased.

name: time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: stacking method type
description: Stacking method (e.g. median, average, auto, manual)

name: parallel porosity volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of parallel porosity with respect to the total volume.

name: producing gas liquid ratio
description: The ratio of produced gas to produced liquid (oil + water) at the wellhead

name: impedance factor
description: Impedance Factor

name: start date
description: The date/time a particular activity started.

name: perforation shot density
description: The perforation density; i.e., the number of shots per unit length.

name: transverse amplitude
description: Amplitude of transverse component in multi-component seismic.

name: nitrogen mole fraction
description: Mole fraction of Nitrogen to total gas composition

name: amplitude skewness
description: Skewness of seismic amplitude (normalized).

name: initial in situ oil volume
description: Total volume of in situ oil in the reservoir.

name: water saturation at breakthrough
description: Water saturation at the breakthough point. In Special Core Analysis, breakthough is the appearance of the injected fluid at the outlet face of the rock sample.

name: formula
description: Symbolic expression of a rule or principle.

name: water conductivity
description: Conductivity of Connate Water (in formation)

name: from offset
description: The distance from the mid-point of the "From" equipment to the bottom of the "To" equipment in a From_To connection.

name: strontium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Strontium with respect to total.

name: dew point pressure
description: The pressure at which a liquid phase condenses from a vaporous fluid in equilibrium at a given temperature.

name: contact type
description: The type of contact or interface between Earth subsurface regions

name: ipr fluid flow model type
description: Type of Inflow Performance Behavior for the Hydraulic Unit (Darcy, Forcheimer, Vogel, Cheng)

name: min concentration 3
description: Minimum concentration or proportion of third component

name: length extended
description: Length of an equipment item such as a mechanical jar in extended position

name: extrapolated pressure sph
description: Extrapolated pressure from spherical flow analysis

name: temperature sensor type
description: Type of temperature sensor

name: currency code
description: Money currency (US$, French franc..)

name: sequence increment
description: The non-zero, positive integer indicating the difference between index values of a sequence, most commonly "1".

name: flowing pressure
description: The pressure of the flowing well measured at the intake point in the borehole.

name: short name
description: Informal, usually shortened name given to an object or data item; a nickname.

name: oil saturation
description: The extent to which the pore space in a formation contains oil.

name: def language
description: Default Language used

name: integrated trace
description: The integral of an instantaneous attribute over a given interval.

name: conductivity contrast
description: Conductivity ratio between geological objects

name: axis first value
description: First value along axis

name: dose equivalent
description: A measure of the biological damage to living tissue as a result of radiation exposure.

name: remaining life
description: Remaining relative life predicted by the CoilLIFE model expressed as a percentage

name: geologic k
description: Index of a geologic depth array

name: potash volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of potash with respect to the total volume.

name: wellhead pressure
description: The producing or shutin pressure at the top of the well before any surface pressure drops.

name: wellhead producing water cut
description: Water Cut at the Wellhead while well is producing

name: nuclear magnetic data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a nuclear magnetism measurement.

name: optical wave length
description: Length of Optical Wave

name: potassium chloride yield
description: Elemental contribution of Potassium Chloride with respect to total.

name: reduced pressure
description: The pressure of a fluid divided by the critical pressure of the fluid.

name: hydrocarbon rock mass fraction
description: Describes the mass of hydrocarbons per rock mass

name: origin latitude
description: The latitude of the point of origin of an orthogonal grid constructed on a map projection. Frequently this is a projection standard parallel, but can be any defined latitude.

name: tubing shoe depth
description: Tubing shoe depth

name: heterogeneity seismic amplitude
description: Measure of heterogeneity computed from the Seismic Amplitude trace over a given interval.

name: acoustic caliper
description: Borehole diameter as estimated by an acoustic logging device.

name: digital storage
description: Total number of bytes being stored

name: multi comp shear angle
description: The angle between the vector perpendicular to the wave front and the amplitude vector of the seismic defined by the X,Y and Z components. Seabed shear velocity used.

name: planned depth
