description: The planned measured depth at the end of the reporting period, as described on the driller depth log of the planned borehole

name: lwd operating time
description: Operating time of the logging-while-drilling (LWD) equipment over the reporting period.

name: resistance gradient
description: A measure of the change in electric resistance per unit length.

name: corrosive fluid flag
description: Is the fluid corrosive? (Y/N) Used to apply a wall erosion model to measure the pipe wall thickness.

name: stack crossline dip
description: Estimation of the crossline dip for all layers to the current depth.

name: operating time
description: Period of time which is spent operating, either for a single operation or for a series of operations. Complement of Idle_Time.

name: wet gas gravity
description: The ratio of the molecular weight of the wet gas to that of air (Wet gas - mixture of free gas plus condensate)

name: api nom weight
description: API nominal weight of tube with joint for drill pipe and casing pipe

name: ideal source position 0 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal source position 0.

name: net shale thickness
description: Difference between Gross_Thickness and Net_Thickness; i.e. the thickness of the formations excluded from "Net" due to cutoff for maximum clay content.

name: permittivity
description: The property of a material that enables it to store electrical charge, typically measured in farad/m. Free space has a Permittivity of 8.854E-12 farad/m.

name: storage location
description: The name of the location where an item is physically stored.

name: anorthite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of anorthite to total dry weight

name: net pay flushed zone water saturation
description: Average flushed zone water saturation in the net pay portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: water saturation at breakthrough ff
description: Water saturation at the breakthough point, calculated from fractional flow curve (SCAL SwBkFF). In Special Core Analysis, breakthough is the appearance of the injected fluid at the outlet face of the rock sample.

name: api entrance hole diameter
description: Entrance hole diameter in an API Section I test

name: bale kappa
description: Bale's kappa, the mode-converted wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout mode-converted wave velocities.

name: magnitude
description: Absolute value of Amplitude.

name: pressure sensor type
description: Pressure sensor type

name: steel grade
description: Grade used to qualify the characteristics of the steel. For tubulars, grade determines the minimum yield strength and thus the burst and collapse pressures and is of importance for the proper choice of slips. The grade can be either custom, i.e. defined by the supplier, e.g. US Steel FS80, Vallourec 110 VS 22, or defined by the API, e.g. C75, J55, N80, E. Number in the API grade means the minimum yield strength in kpsi (N80: 80,000 psi). API grades for Tubing, Casing and Drill pipes can be found in the API specifications 5xx.

name: product code
description: The code of a chemical product sometimes named alphacode e.g. D013

name: illite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of illite to total dry weight

name: lime concentration
description: Lime content in water based mud as determined per API RP13P Section 8

name: perforation gun type
description: The type of perforating gun used to shoot the given interval of the tubing (or casing) in the borehole. Examples are: 3-3/8" 6 SPF, 3-3/8" HJ HI-TEMP, 4" HJ II, etc.

name: interval polarization azimuth
description: Estimation of the polarization azimuth angle for a layer.

name: response equation
description: Sensor response equation

name: inertial flow coefficient correlation type
description: Inertial Flow Coefficient Correlation (e.g. Saucier, Firoozabadi, etc. )

name: spud date
description: The date a spud attempt was performed on a well

name: torsional yield
description: Maximum torque which can be applied to an object without causing permanent deformation.

name: mute taper length
description: Number of samples muted in the traces

name: tool background yield
description: Elemental contribution of Tool Background with respect to total.

name: down stroke
description: Down stroke distance, as used for drilling jars.

name: agreement status
description: Status of a lease agreement.

name: status
description: An indicator of the state of an entity or process at some moment in time. Also the position or rank in relation to others.

name: tool rotation speed
description: Rotational speed of the logging tool

name: water connection size
description: Standard water pipe size connection supplied on the equipment inlet

name: business line
description: Group of activities or services gathered by some commonalities

name: transverse dispersivity coefficient
description: The coefficient used as a multiplier of interstitial velocity to estimate dispersion normal to the direction of movement for a displacement front.

name: cement unit type
description: Cementing unit type

name: displacing fluid volume
description: Volume of fluid used to displace another fluid. In special core analysis, may be expressed as unitless multiple of pore volume.

name: thermal alteration index
description: An indicator of the thermal maturity of organic matter, based on a relationship between color of organic particles and the length and intensity of heat exposure.

name: min flowrate
description: Minimum flowrate

name: cacl2 concentration
description: CaCl2 concentration.

name: measure reference plane offset
description: Distance from the Measure Reference Plane to the bottom of the Equipment (which is for a tool practically the make-up line of the bottom connection). The Measure Reference Plane allows recording of the location of the sensor measure point in an equipment composition. The measure point is positioned by a length called Measure_Point_Offset, a property of the composition to which the sensor belongs. The Measure_Point_Offset is the distance from the measure reference plane of the part, i.e., sensor or tool, to the measure reference plane of the whole, i.e., tool or tool string.

name: holdup index
description: Unitless quantity proportional to holdup within a given borehole environment. Holdup indices are comparable only when the borehole and casing sizes are the same.

name: spherical permeability
description: An effective permeability used to combine directional permeabilities, Kx and Ky. Usually abbreviated as Ksph.

name: max concentration 1
description: Maximum concentration or proportion of first component

name: authorization for expenditure
description: Identifier of granted or candidate request for authorization to spend money, usually for a specified purpose and amount. Abbreviated AFE

name: transit time
description: Time required for a wave to travel from one point to another.

name: surface oil flowrate
description: Oil flowrate (surface conditions)

name: vertical geometric skin
description: In a horizontal well, skin effect due to the limited entry in the vertical direction.

name: oil formation volume factor correlation
description: Name of the correlation model (often the author name) used to compute oil formation volume factor (Vasquez_Beggs, Glaso, Standing)

name: pressure sensor drift
description: Pressure difference over time in the gauge output with constant input conditions

name: company
description: The code of a Company, usually that of a Service, Contractor, Vendor or E and P company

name: horizon type
description: The type of a Horizon in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Seismic or Geological

name: concentration 3
description: Concentration or proportion of third component in mixture or other composition.

name: min casing inside diameter
description: Minimum inside diameter of casing for which service or equipment is suitable

name: projection code
description: Catalog code of a Projection coordinate system.

name: time interpretation
description: Generic interpretation on seismic traveltime sections

name: screen arrangement
description: Position of the screens, such as in a shale shaker.

name: vert hor permeability ratio
description: The ratio of vertical to horizontal permeability in a permeable medium.

name: signal to noise ratio
description: The ratio of signal amplitude to noise amplitude, usually expressed in dB.

name: roundness
description: A measure of the degree of how round an object is, such as a contour on a Surface.

name: pressure unit
description: Unit for Pressure data

name: sum amplitude
description: Sum of the amplitudes

name: pf titration volume
description: Amount of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid required in order to turn the color of phenolphthalein indicator solution from pink to colorless when determining phenolphthalein alkalinity of the mud filtrate, Pf, API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis.

name: fluid viscosity
description: The viscosity of a fluid (sample) at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: tool number
description: Acquisition system tool number

name: reference sack mass
description: Sack "weight" (mass) to which unit by sack refers e.g. lbs/sack

name: drill stabilizer type
description: Generic stabilizer type such as Welded Blade, Integral Blade, Replaceable Sleeve, Clamp-on, Rubber Sleeve, Rockback, RWP (replaceable wear pad)

name: absolute permeability oil
description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with oil.

name: nmr dct1 map
description: Map of volume fractions for different diffusion coefficients (DC) and different longitudinal relaxation times (T1); normally represented as a 2d map of volume fraction values indexed by DC components along the y-axis and T1 components along the x-axis.

name: ch4 concentration
description: Concentration of Methane (CH4); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 85%.

name: survey bottom depth
description: Deepest depth to which the borehole was surveyed

name: reciprocal force
description: was per force

name: acquisition type
description: Type or mode of data acquisition

name: effective permeability water sor
description: Effective permeability to water at residual oil saturation.

name: relative time
description: Ratio of two times

name: slackoff hook load
description: Average slackoff hook load (slackoff weight) over the reporting period.

name: output pressure
description: Pressure at the output of an equipment item.

name: projection point mode
description: Flag determining number of points used in defining certain projections, 0,1,2

name: light phase flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of light phase component of fluid.

name: cardinality
description: Number of instances of an Entity type which may be referred to by another Entity in a particular relationship; may be ONE or MANY.

name: wellbore status
description: A property indicating the operational condition of a wellbore: proposed, active, abandoned, etc.

name: mud pump power
description: Mud pump input horse power.

name: article title
description: Title of article or memo

name: cable length
description: Cable length; measured from a fixed reference point and used as Measured Depth in Wireline operations

name: interpolation method
description: Interpolation method used in the generation of data.

name: outer pipe inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of a pipe in external position within an annulus

name: unconformity type
description: The type of an unconformity in the Earth subsurface, e.g. Joint, Disconformity, Diastem, etc.

name: drilling exponent
description: An exponent that normalizes the drill rate for variations in drilling conditions such as WOB, RPM and mud density

name: friction coefficient
description: Ratio of the frictional (tangential) force to the contact (normal) force between two objects or materials in contact.

name: compressive strength
description: The degree of resistance of a material to force acting along one of the axes in a manner tending to crush it.

name: slowness time coherence
description: A measure of waveform coherence with respect to slowness and time, computed as a function of coherent energy to total energy; also called "Semblance"

name: gas flag
description: Flag indicating presence of gas

name: bit inclination
description: Inclination of the drillstring as measured as the bit

name: x displacement
description: Displacement in the X Direction relative to some coordinate system; e.g., the X-Component of the Well departure from the vertical.

name: trough trough amplitude ratio
description: Ratio of amplitudes of two troughs.

name: 10 minute gel strength
description: Shear Stress required to break a gel fluid previously allowed to remain at rest for 10 minutes.

name: mixing order
description: Order in which the materials are added together. This order matters e.g. the acid is poured into the water and not the contrary, the water to the flour ...

name: dip pattern type
description: The type of pattern created by the earth dipping planes, e.g. Green, Red, Blue, etc.

name: samarium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Samarium with respect to total.

name: liquid flowrate per number of fractures
description: Normalized liquid flowrate per number of fractures

name: true vertical depth
description: The true vertical depth from the surface of the Earth to a particular subsurface point.

name: core preservation method
description: Method by which a core sample has been preserved.

name: township number
description: Jeffersonian Township Number

name: critical drawdown pressure
description: The upper limit of drawdown pressure that can be applied to a completion system without causing damage to the system (such as erosion to a gravel pack completion system).

name: max working pressure
description: Recommended maximum pressure at which equipment can be used

name: spot description
description: The fractional part of interest within the section

name: gas flowrate per lateral length
description: Change in gas flowrate per lateral length

name: api well number
description: A unique well identification number as defined in the API (American Petroleum Institute) Bulletin D12A.

name: sample type
description: Nature of the sample e.g. oil or gas

name: molar density
description: Number of moles of a material per unit volume.

name: eou cone growth ratio
description: Ratio of the ellipse of uncertainty cone radius increase per depth increment

name: mud pump output
description: Mud pump maximum output, measured in terms of the rate of amount or mud output.

name: oil line temperature gauge type
description: Type of gauge used to measure oil line temperature of separator

name: shear velocity
description: The velocity of a shear wave (Vs); a shear wave is a type of seismic wave in which the particle motion is perpendicular to the direction of propagation; also called S-wave or secondary wave.

name: specific energy
description: Energy per unit mass, an intensive property in contrast to Energy as the extensive property

name: critical angle
description: Angle of incidence for which a refracted ray follows the surface of contact between two media of different velocities.

name: crossplot porosity
description: Estimate of porosity determined by plotting one type of data against another.

name: nitrogen dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of nitrogen to total dry weight

name: yield strength
description: Unit stress which will produce a small amount of deformation generally equal to a strain of 0.2%. This value is a little greater than the Elastic limit. It is often supplied by the manufacturer of the material.

name: electromagnetic moment
description: A measure of the strength of an electromagnetic field measured as the torque experienced when the field is exposed to an ortogonal magnetic field.

name: perforation count
description: Total number of perforations over the perforated interval

name: projection relative bearing
description: Projection relative bearing

name: lwd tool type
description: The type of a tool used for Logging While Drilling.

name: recorder code
description: Code for the recorder

name: force per volume
description: A measure of force per volume

name: bha run number
description: Sequence number of the bottomhole assembly (BHA) run.

name: drift time
description: The difference between actual acoustic travel time to a subsurface point (as measured in a check shot survey) and the integrated acoustic slowness from sonic logging data.

name: gas description type
description: Type of data describing the gas: complete hydrocarbon composition, impurities (H2S, CO2,N2) or gas gravity.

name: spacing z
description: Spacing in Z dimension; may be expressed as an absolute spacing with units or as a proportion of some reference X Spacing.

name: litho density
description: Formation density as measured with a Litho-Density or Gamma-Gamma type logging tool; conventionally abbreviated RHOB.

name: base longitude
description: Longitude value used as the basis or starting point, such as in a multiple regression computation.

name: mean particle diameter
description: Average diameter of the particle (e.g. for Gravel pack sand 20/40 mean diameter=0 .025 inc/0.635 mm, 40/60 mean diameter=0.014 inch/0.355mm).

name: shallow induction resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by an induction log, which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: h2s mole fraction
description: Mole fraction of Hydrogen Sulfide to total gas composition

name: equipment type
description: The type or class of an equipment used for some activity, e.g. Sensor, Drill Bit, Turbine, etc.

name: sample interval
description: Index interval between sequential data samples; see also Depth_Increment and Time_Increment (Sampling_Period)

name: body material
description: Material used in the body such as steel, aluminum, monel

name: iadc grade other
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on other characteristics

name: sample gas oil ratio
description: Ratio of gas flowrate to oil flowrate when a sample is taken

name: time pick
description: Acoustic transit time (normally a two-way time) from seismic reference datum to the well marker, as picked from a seismic section.

name: ellipsoid flat
description: Ratio derived from semi-major and semi-minor axes to define degree to which ellipsoid shape departs from the spherical. [(a-b)/a]

name: density data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a bulk density logging measurement.

name: net reservoir core grain density point match
description: Average grain density in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from core data by point-match method.

name: min horizontal stress azimuth
description: The minimum horizontal stress azimuth with respect to true north.

name: standoff
description: The amount of physical separation between two objects, usually maintained in order to control their interaction.

name: channel width
description: The perpendicular distance between two parallel boundaries.

name: geological influence type
description: The type of geological influence that dominates some feature such as a sedimentary channel, e.g. Wave dominated, Delta dominated, etc.

name: tool control
description: Property that controls the state or operation of a tool.

name: second moment of area
description: A geometrical property of an area which reflects how its points are distributed with regard to an arbitrary axis

name: evaporite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of evaporite to total dry weight

name: wellhead flowing pressure
description: Pressure at the Wellhead with well flowing

name: flow unit
description: Unit for fluid flow data.

name: carbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of carbon with respect to the total volume.

name: water concentration
description: Water Concentration per fluid Volume

name: relaxation time
description: In nuclear magnetic resonance measurements, the time constant related to the rate at which nuclei realign to the static magnetic field after disturbance by a radio frequency pulse.

name: pi code
description: Petroleum Information Alpha-Numeric code

name: relative power
description: Ratio of two powers

name: y magnetometer
description: Magnetic Field Strength along the Y-axis.

name: gas volume per mass
description: Gas volume required to make a unit mass; the reciprocal of density

name: fracturing efficiency
description: Ratio of Fracture Volume at end of job to Total Volume Pumped. The difference between the two volumes represents the volume which leaked off into the formation.

name: volume safety factor
description: Volume in excess of what has been calculated for the job. Used to account for loss or safety margin

name: attenuation resistivity
description: Formation resistivity as measured by the attenuation of a high frequency (hundreds of KHz to several MHz) electromagnetic wave; these measurements are typically deeper than measurements based on phase shift, but their vertical resolution is less sharp and they often cannot be used reliably in high-resistivity formations.

name: local coord sys code
description: Catalog Code of a locally defined coordinate system.

name: slackoff friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient between a string and the pipe when running into the hole

name: mud filtrate resistivity
description: Resistivity of mud filtrate

name: source orientation theta
description: Horizontal angle of downhole source, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: disclaimer
description: Legal text on the front page describing the legal status of this document as regard of liability.

name: liquid flowrate per length
description: Change in liquid flowrate per length

name: linear thermal expansion
description: The change in length of a material as a fraction of its total length due to a change in temperature at a constant pressure.

name: acquisition shot time
description: Acquisition system shot time

name: source orientation phi
description: Vertical angle of downhole source, measured from the x-y plane.

name: noise coefficient
description: Noise coefficient of pressure sensor

name: tracking window bottom
description: Interval below the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type while tracking

name: group velocity
description: The velocity with which the energy in a wavetrain travels. In dispersive media, it is the velocity of the envelope of the wavetrain.

name: legal description
description: Legal description associated with a legal document or agreement, for instance, a description of the boundaries of a lease.

name: molybdenum yield
description: Elemental contribution of Molybdenum with respect to total.

name: invasion annulus resistivity
description: Resistivity of the invasion annulus, a region of the formation lying between the flushed zone and the undisturbed formation, and filled with interstitial water displaced from the flushed zone.)

name: gas line temperature gauge type
description: Gauge used to measure gas meter temperature

name: supervised flag
description: Flag indicating whether the activity was supervised (1) or unsupervised (0)

name: angle per volume
description: Rotation per volume of a fluid, like in a downhole motor

name: iadc grade outer rows
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on condition of outer rows

name: reference point offset
description: Distance from the bottom of the Equipment to the Reference Point. The Reference_Point is the origin of the From_Offset distance for an Equipment mounted in From_Mounting_Location=Outside or Inside. The default position for the Reference point is the bottom end of the Equipment. The Reference point is used in drilling to save repositioning all the sensors mounted inside a tool when the end is remachined. There is just one reference point for any equipment mounted on this To_Equipment.

name: bin porosity
description: Contribution of porosity from a given "bin" (with certain characteristics) to the total porosity; e.g., in nuclear magnetic resonance data processing, the "bins" typically correspond to different pore size ranges.

name: true source position
description: True source position

name: gas line diameter
description: Diameter of the gas line

name: vertical formation resistivity
description: Formation resistivity measured perpendicular to layering. (for "Transverse-Isotropic (TI)" rock

name: min working temperature
description: Recommended minimum temperature at which equipment can be used

name: api design
description: The API design specification that the equipment meets

name: show flow rate
description: A textual description of the rate at which fluid emerges from the rock sample. Example keywords include: dead oil, live show, streaming or bleeding.

name: displacement efficiency
description: The fraction of displaceable fluids/hydrocarbons that has been actually displaced when contacted by a displacing fluid.

name: c3h8 concentration
description: Concentration of Propane (C3H8); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 2%.

name: grain distribution
description: Textual description of the grain distribution in a rock sample.

name: bottomhole end type
description: Indicates what limits the total depth (plug back, borehole bottom, bridge plug, sump packer ...)

name: min horizontal to vertical geostress ratio
description: Ratio of minimum horizontal to vertical stress. (Normally abbreviated Sh/SV)

name: cumulative volume
description: The cumulative volume, typically of a fluid.

name: normalization factor
description: Coefficient used to normalize data for comparison or correlation.

name: sum magnitude
description: Sum of magnitudes

name: gypsum volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of gypsum with respect to the total volume.

name: key
description: In software, data used to gain access to or to enable some otherwise restricted functionality.

name: dip quality cutoff
description: The lowest dip quality taken into account for an interpretation.

name: data direction
description: Direction of data flow, e.g. Input, Output or both.

name: silicon yield
description: Elemental contribution of Silicon with respect to total.

name: fluid temperature
description: The temperature of a fluid (sample) under certain conditions.

name: flowrate per pressure per pressure
description: Root property for flow rate per pressure squared.
quantity: PWLS:volume per time per pressure per pressure

name: mass per area per time
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity MassPerAreaPerTime, which acts as an abstract parent for other property instances

name: date
description: The date, usually expressed in the format of the DBMS; e.g., Oracle date format is dd-mm-yy.

name: pump flowrate
description: Fluid flowrate through a pump such as an electric submersible pump (ESP).

name: vertical datum code
description: Code of the permanent Vertical Datum to which the local elevation reference is related. Typical Vertical Datums are "MSL" and "GL".

name: flushed zone irreducible water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of irreducible water in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: wellbore storage
description: Measure of the ability of the wellbore to store fluid ("afterflow" when a well is shut in) or unload fluid (when a well is opened to flow).

name: net reservoir clay volume fraction
description: Average volume fraction of clay in the Net Reservoir portion of the zone (thickness weighted arithmetic average).

name: neo-c5 concentration
description: Neo-pentane gas concentration as a volume fraction of the drilling fluid

name: oil probability
description: The probability that oil is present in the formation.

name: ellipsoid name
description: Name of the ellipsoid to which geodetic coordinates are referenced.

name: max concentration 4
description: Maximum concentration or proportion of fourth component

name: geothermal gradient
description: The rate of change of temperature with depth in the Earth. It averages about 30 degC/km at shallow depths.

name: compressional velocity gradient
description: A measure of the change in the compressional velocity of a medium per unit length.

name: north south distance
description: North or South distance to the boundary line indicated by North_South_Line to the survey point.

name: y gravity
description: Strength of the y-axis component of the gravitational field at some location.

name: depth gradient
description: Change of depth versus distance

name: rock genesis
description: Classification of rocks by genetic origin, e.g. Sedimentary, Igneous, etc.

name: magnetic permeability
description: The three-dimensional inductance of a material, a measure of the magnetic induction produced in a material by a given magnetic field strength. Free space (and nonmagnetic rock) has a permeability of 1.257*10-6 henrys/meter.

name: transfer duration
description: Duration of sampling operation

name: produced fluid compressibility
description: Compressibility of the Total Produced Fluid for the Hydraulic Unit. It is corrected from Reservoir_Fluid_Compressibility by taking into account the actual volume fractions produced based on the saturation of the fluid within the reservoir.

name: energy rate
description: Energy per unit time

name: transit time nominal
description: Nominal transit time

name: net load
description: Weight Indicator load minus any extra equipment weight (Injector head, Hook...)

name: stack thomsen delta
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Thomsen's delta anisotropy parameter.

name: peak trough delta amplitude
description: Amplitude difference between peak and trough.

name: min index
description: Generalized minimum value of index, typically distance or time.

name: mud filtrate volume per length
description: The measure of volume of mud filtrate lost to the formation per linear length of borehole, usually given in U.S. gal/ft.

name: leakoff height
description: Portion of the zone fracturing fluids will leakoff into. It can be an aggregate of a number of geologic formations.

name: horizontal size
description: The size of any object as measured horizontally

name: casing sliding friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient due to sliding between casing and other surface (e.g. drill string), when only sliding motion is present

name: micro spherically focused resistivity
description: A measurement of the resistivity of the formation, by a spherically focused tool, within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: electric polarization
description: was electric charge per area

name: local paleo shoreline orient
description: The orientation of a shoreline pertaining to the local paleontology.

name: log flag
description: Flag indicating the presence of a log, or that an item or event is to be included in a log.

name: max outside diameter
description: Maximum outside diameter of an equipment item.

name: epithermal neutron near far ratio
description: Ratio of the count rate of the near detector to that of the far detector in an epithermal neutron logging device

name: nom station distance
description: Nominal distance between stations on a seismic line

name: extensive heat capacity per temperature
description: Extensive heat capacity per unit temperature, see Extensive_Heat_Capacity.

name: contact symbol
description: Symbol to post on the Feature_Boundary at the intersection point with another Feature_Boundary

name: min element count
description: Minimum number of elements in a group or collection.

name: flow direction setup
description: Indicates the wellbore flow direction for which an equipment item has been configured.

name: stack bale kappa
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Bale's kappa, the mode-converted wave equivalent to eta, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout mode-converted wave velocities.

name: def currency
description: Default Currency used

name: vertical lift pressure
description: Computed pressure at some depth in tubing

name: injected fluid type
description: Type of fluid injected.

name: matrix shear slowness
description: Acoustic slowness of a shear wave in a given material or matrix.

name: material weight
description: Weight of Material

name: correlation time dip
description: Dip of seismic data, similar to Time_Dip but gradient derived from the seismic data in time)

name: longitude
description: Angle measured about the spheroid (or ellipsoid) axis from a local prime meridian to the meridian through the point. A positive value denotes East.

name: annular pressure data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for an annular pressure measurement.

name: gamma ray minus uranium
description: The measurement of the naturally occurring gamma radiation less the radiation attributed to uranium.

name: interval qs ratio
description: Interval value of the shear wave quality factor.

name: density time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a density sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: gas saturation min so 3phase
description: The gas saturation at minimum oil saturation in a three phase system. (SCAL SGM)

name: interfault angle
description: The smallest angle between two intersecting sealing faults in a wedge well test model.

name: stack number
description: Stack number

name: nom liquid capacity
description: Volume of fluid which can be contained in the vessel

name: msl source dy
description: Y coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: specific surface area per mass
description: The characteristic of a porous media which is the internal surface area of the medium per unit mass.

name: band high frequency
description: Upper limit of frequency band (range)

name: vertical section origin
description: The location and orientation of the vertical section plane in which vertical section distances are measured.

name: well to fracture element distance
description: Distance from Borehole to start of fracture element

name: eou cone surface radius
description: The radius of the ellipse of uncertainty cone at the surface location

name: avg porosity
description: Average value of the material Porosity.

name: initial reservoir pressure temperature
description: Temperature taken when initial reservoir pressure recorded

name: construct
description: Construct specifies how instances of the given Value Domain are assembled into a single Value. Together Value Domain and Construct are used to derive Value_Type. Construct can be null (for a single value), L (for List), V (for Vector) , LL (List of Lists) , VL, PL, etc.

name: active
description: Integer token indicating that something is active

name: avg compressional shear velocity ratio
description: Time average of compressional-shear velocity ratio from top to reflector.

name: email address
description: Address used for electronic mail, such as an Internet address (clinton@white_house.gov)

name: color intensity
description: A descriptive comment with respect to the intensity of color; e.g. bright, dull, powdery.

name: ellipsoid a
description: Length of the semi-major axis of the reference ellipsoid.

name: mudcake membrane stiffness
description: Characterization of the flexibility of mudcake, defined as the ratio of the stress difference across the mudcake-formation boundary to the relative displacement between the pore fluid and the solid frame.

name: constraint type
description: Type of constraint. Examples include UNCONSTRAINED, STRING_ENUM, INTEGER_ENUM, INTEGER_RANGE, FLOAT_RANGE, DATE_RANGE, ENTITY_CLASS, CATALOG_ATTR, etc.

name: gas production volume per perflength per no of fractures
description: Normalized gas cumulative per perforation length per number of fractures

name: event time 4
description: Event Time 4

name: mwd operating time
description: Operating time of the MWD equipment over the reporting period.

name: coring fluid type
description: The type of fluid that was in the borehole at the time the coring operation was in progress; e.g. water, brine, oil, mud, etc.

name: erosion state
description: Describes if the event has been partially, totally, etc. subjected to erosion.

name: magnetic declination source
description: Name of a declination survey, a vendor of declination data, a reference book, or a person supplying the value.

name: net reservoir log water saturation point match
description: Average water saturation in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from log data by point-match method.

name: termination date
description: The date on which a lease, an organization, or any legal or organizational entity was terminated.

name: dry clay volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of dry clay with respect to the total volume.

name: correction
description: Correction applicable to a measurement, to remove environmental effects or measurement errors; the unit quantity is determined by that of the data.

name: affine coeff e
description: Coefficient "E" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: micro spherically focused conductivity
description: A measurement of the conductivity of the formation, by a spherically focused tool, within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: api reference
description: The name of an API (American Petroleum Institute) reference, e.g., Bulletin D12A.

name: fracture plausibility
description: Estimate of the likelihood that a given rock body is fractured.

name: rock solubility in hcl
description: Amount of rock, normally expressed as a percentage by weight soluble in HCl

name: noise amplitude
description: The amplitude of noise or unwanted portion of a signal.

name: post cursor amplitude
description: Difference in seismic amplitude between a reference position and the corresponding deeper extreme.

name: object identifier
description: Identifier of the seismic object within the Foreign System

name: geocentric dx
description: X component of the translation of the center of a geodetic datum. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: oxygen yield
description: Elemental contribution of Oxygen with respect to total.

name: source angle
description: Source angle

name: pickup friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient between a string and the borehole when pulling out of the hole

name: volume per area per geologic time
description: Describes the volume per area per million years. E.g. the quantity of hydrocarbons generated in a particular area in a certain timeframe

name: simulation multiple count
description: Number of multiple reflections considered in the simulation

name: downstream orifice gas pressure
description: Pressure of gas separator gas line downstream of orifice plate when a sample is taken

name: array induction resistivity
description: Array Resistivity measurement using induction logging principles.

name: dune shape
description: Shape of a Dune type depositional environment, e.g. Dome, Parabolic, etc.

name: mineral hardness
description: The hardness of a rock sample expressed in units of the MOH reference standard.

name: vertical time thickness
description: Vertical time difference between layers.

name: personnel on board
description: Count of number of people on board the vessel or structure.

name: drill fluid name
description: Name given to the drill fluid

name: supplier
description: Supplier name of a Product.

name: length cocked
description: Length of an equipment item such as a mechanical jar in cocked position

name: liquid flowrate per lateral length
description: Change in liquid flowrate per lateral length

name: electrical stability
description: Measure of the emulsion stability and oil-wetting capability in oil based drilling fluids.

name: direction channel to land
description: Azimuth of the direction to land, usually pertaining to a sedimentary channel.

name: fracture face skin
description: The skin along the face of the fracture (natural or hydraulic).

name: i c4h10 concentration
description: Concentration of iso-Butane (i-C4H10); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.3%.

name: calorific value
description: The amount of heat released during the combustion of a specified amount of a specific substance.

name: sonic porosity dolomite
description: Porosity calculated using the compressional wave travel time measurement from an acoustic log with a dolomite matrix travel time.

name: shallow lateral resistivity
description: Resistivity measurement using a "lateral" electrode arrangement with a "shallow" investigation radius (several inches into the formation).

name: magnetic vector potential
description: A magnet vector field which along with a scalar potential field is used to compute an electromagnetic field.

name: source line position
description: Position in a source line.

name: quartz dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of quartz to total dry weight

name: acquisition break time
description: Acquisition system break time

name: mu rho reflectivity
description: Reflectivity computed from mu rho

name: std parallel 2
description: Second line of latitude along which scale is true, for map projections using two standard parallels; this parallel is NEAREST to the POLE.

name: dip quality
description: Induced quality of the dip value based on evaluation of the quality of the measured data. Ranges from 0 (bad) to 20 (good)

name: inertial flow correlation exponent
description: Cooke's inertial fracture flow correlation exponent (a). Empirical coefficient relating Fracture inertial flow coefficient Beta to Fracture permeability.

name: annual payment
description: Annual amount of Payment based on some contractual agreement such as a lease. This could be rental, mortgage or other.

name: mechanical specific energy
description: A drilling efficiency indicator based on calculation of the energy required to drill a formation

name: mineral concentration
description: Volume of a particular mineral per unit volume of the investigated material, such as a sample.

name: arc type
description: The type of Arc objects which bound surface regions of the Earth, e.g. State Boundary, River, etc.

name: nominal receiver dy
description: Y coordinate of nominal correction vector to receiver position.

name: treatment bottom depth
description: Depth of the borehole at the moment of the treatment

name: molecular weight
description: Ratio of the mass of a molecule of a substance to 1/12 of the mass of a Carbon12 atom; calculated as the sum of the atomic weights of the constituent atoms.

name: micro laterolog conductivity
description: A measurement of the conductivity of the formation, by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, within the first few inches of the borehole wall.

name: surface surface intersection type
description: The type of Surface-Surface intersection showing the types of the 2 intersecting surfaces.

name: downhole lateral vibration
description: Lateral pipe vibration measured by an MWD/LWD tool

name: compression pressure
description: The pressure applied to compress a body or material, as opposed to that applied by tension.

name: drill structure name
description: Name of the Rig or Drill Structure operating on the well

name: max volume
description: The maximum volume not to be exceeded for a container (Tank, Mud Pit)

name: receiver event first arrival
description: Time of arrival of first break for each receiver event

name: strain
description: Measure of the change in dimensions or shape caused by stress, generally expressed as a unitless ratio of the change of length per unit of initial length. If not otherwise specified, strain is taken to be "normal" (in the same direction as the stress).

name: bubble flow velocity
description: The rate at which a fluid bubble, gas or liquid, flows through another fluid, gas or liquid. The Velocity depends on the densities and viscosities of the fluids.

name: annulus temperature
description: Temperature of the fluid in the annulus. The annulus is the region outside the subject pipe, such as the region between drill pipe and the formation, or between casing and formation, or between tubing and casing.

name: calibration date
description: Date of calibration for the equipment; time may also be included.

name: mineral class
description: The classification of a mineral.

name: ovality
description: Degree of departure from roundness. Often measured as the ratio of large diameter over small diameter of an ellipse or an ellipsoid body

name: receiver line z
description: Z-coordinate of position in a receiver line.

name: mud temperature in
description: The temperature of mud going into the hole, usually measured in the active circulating pit

name: max calibrated value
description: Maximum value of the range for which the equipment is calibrated.

name: fluid density
description: Density of a fluid sample; e.g., from Borehole, Formations, Cores, etc. Also density of cement.

name: drill fluid code
description: Specific code of the drill fluid.

name: profile resistivity
description: Resistivity profile measurement, used primarily for pattern recognition; may or may not be calibrated.

name: relative permeability function coeff
description: Coefficients used in the function.

name: dip height
description: Height of Dip Plane Intersection with Borehole

name: rover amplitude
description: Difference between seismic amplitude and the straight line connecting the two nearest extremes (with same kick).

name: stoneley velocity
description: The velocity of a Stoneley wave; a Stoneley wave is a type of seismic wave which is propagated along an interface, such as a tube wave in a borehole.

name: ellipticity
description: The ratio of the major to minor axes of an ellipse.

name: trace elements
description: Description of the trace elements in a sample or material.

name: minus tolerance
description: Amount of negative tolerance on a measurement value; the unit quantity is determined by that of data value.

name: polynomial order
description: Order of term in a polynomial, such as in a multiple regression equation.

name: jar operating time
description: Operating time of the jar over the reporting period.

name: surface water flowrate
description: Water flowrate (surface conditions)

name: net gross thickness ratio
description: Ratio of Net_Thickness to Gross_Thickness

name: signal amplitude
description: The amplitude associated with a generic type signal.

name: avg running speed
description: Average Speed of equipment running into (counted positive) or out of the hole (counted negative).

name: central line bearing
description: Azimuth of central line of projection.

name: value type code
description: Code of value type of data

name: visibility
description: Maximum distance at which objects can still be discerned or identified visually.

name: cumulative water volume
description: Cumulative water production at standard conditions.

name: flushed zone hydrocarbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of hydrocarbon in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: business associate job title
description: The assignment of an administrative job title to a business associate in the context of a business association

name: amount of substance
description: The amount of a particular substance (e.g. chemical) expressed in units of moles.

name: chemical formula
description: A symbolic expression of the composition or constitution of a substance.

name: peak peak delta depth
description: Depth difference between successive peaks

name: kaolinite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of kaolinite to total dry weight

name: true receiver line position
description: True position in a receiver line

name: dip valid zone type
description: This property specifies whether the zone where the dips were computed corresponded to a Blank zone with no dips, a Mirror Image zone, or a borehole Washout zone.

name: section number
description: Jeffersonian Section Number

name: initial reservoir pressure date
description: Date when initial reservoir pressure data were recorded

name: adjustable choke flag
description: Flag indicating whether this flow period was performed on an adjustable choke, i.e., when set: adjustable choke, not set: fixed choke.

name: unit canonical form
description: Canonical form of defining unit for this Dimension

name: magnetic inclination
description: The vertical angle measured between the horizontal plane and the direction of magnetic north as determined by a freely suspended magnet. Sometimes known as magnetic dip. Positive values if the direction to magnetic north is below the horizon.

name: sonic porosity
description: Porosity calculated using the acoustic slowness measurement from a sonic log.

name: magnetization
description: A measure of the effect of the medium on the magnetic field, B, when subject to a magnetizing force, H; B = Mu0 * (H + M), where Mu0 is the permeability of free space.

name: layer diffusivity
description: Diffusivity (permeability divided by the product of porosity, fluid viscosity and fluid compressibility) for a reservoir layer.

name: windchill temperature
description: A measure of the combined chilling effect of wind and low temperature on living things, also named chill factor, e.g., according to US weather service table, an air temperature of 30 degF with a 10 mi/h corresponds to a "wind-chill" of 22 degF.

name: direction
description: The line or course on which something is moving or is aimed to move or along which something is pointing or facing.

name: small circle azimuth
description: The azimuth of the pole associated with a small circle.

name: qs ratio
description: Quality factor for shear waves. The ratio of 2*pi times the peak shear wave energy to the energy dissipated in a cycle.

name: magnetic declination
description: The horizontal angle measured from a meridian to the direction of magnetic north as determined by a freely suspended magnet. Positive if magnetic North is east of True North.

name: 30 minute gel test deflection
description: The maximum reading (deflection) taken from a direct-reading viscometer after the fluid has been quiescent for 30 minutes.

name: def unit system
description: Default Unit System used

name: hydraulic drive pressure
description: Pressure of the hydraulic fluid delivered to an Hydraulic motor

name: tool temperature
description: Internal temperature of the logging tool

name: dimensionless boundary distance
description: Distance to a boundary divided by wellbore radius

name: affine coeff a
description: Coefficient "A" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: engine oil temperature
description: Engine lubrication Oil Temperature

name: vert hor ratio
description: The ratio of some property measured vertically to that of the same property measured horizontally; several such property types are used to characterize formation anisotropy.

name: identifier
description: A number, label or code given to an object in an attempt to uniquely identify it.

name: trough trough delta amplitude
description: Amplitude difference between two troughs.

name: hydraulic drive temperature
description: Temperature of the hydraulic fluid delivered to an Hydraulic motor

name: optional blade height
description: Optional height of blade at gauge from the body of the equipment, such as a stabilizer (extended Andergauge); used as a supplement to Blade_Height.

name: east west distance
description: East or West distance from the boundary line indicated by East_West_Line to the survey point.

name: long term stability
description: Stability over the long term

name: response frequency
description: Instantaneous frequency at local maximum of reflection intensity

name: dimensionless layer diffusivity
description: Ratio of layer storativity ratio to layer transmissibility ratio ("etaDj")

name: internet address
description: Address by which a particular computer system may be reached over the Internet.

name: classification index
description: Index into a lookup-table describing various classifications. Typical usage is a surface representation (grid) of index values, where each value represents a particular classification.

name: total organic matter
description: Relative content of organic matter in a material, such as a rock sample. Calculated as total organic Carbon * 1.22.

name: depth
description: The perpendicular measurement downward from a surface. Also, the direct linear measurement from the point of viewing usually from front to back.

name: fluid level
description: The level of fluid in a column or vessel, normally expressed as height above (or below) some reference point.

name: tubular string component rank
description: A rank denoting the order of the element in a string of tubular drilling equipment.

name: thomsen gamma
description: Thomsen's gamma anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between Horizontally polarized Shear (SH) velocities in the vertical and horizontal directions.

name: true common midpoint position
description: Common midpoint (CMP) position

name: bend 2 angle
description: Angle of second bend in equipment item.

name: velocity alpha factor
description: Gradient factor a for Faust 6th root velocity function v(z) = a * z**(1/6)

name: source line theta
description: Horizontal angle of position in a source line, measured counter-clockwise from x-axis.

name: filter cake photoelectric factor
description: Photoelectric Factor of the filter cake (mudcake); often expressed in an approximation unit barns/electron.

name: shale volume fraction
description: Volume fraction of shale as calculated, measured or inferred from formation properties.

name: play type
description: A type or code assigned to a lease. Play codes can be internal to company and are usually based upon geographic boundaries or geologic trends.

name: top depth
description: The top depth of a borehole interval, a formation or any depth indexed representation of an data item.

name: separator line
description: Type of separator line: e.g. oil outlet, gas outlet, water outlet or inlet

name: create date
description: Date of creation of a data item in the database.

name: drill hole opener reamer code
description: Specific code of the hole opener or reamer.

name: downtime ratio
description: Non-operational time of an equipment with respect to total time in location

name: transient start time
description: Start time (t0) of the Transient

name: max borehole diameter
description: Maximum borehole diameter

name: rock code
description: Catalog code of a rock type (e.g. Limestone)

name: c7h16 concentration
description: Concentration of Heptane (C7H16)

name: classification method code
description: Classification method used in this activity.

name: interpretation origin
description: Specify where interpretation was performed on data.

name: enthalpy
description: The internal energy of a thermodynamic system plus the product of its pressure and volume.

name: holdup
description: In a producing well, the volume fraction of a specific fluid phase in the upward-moving stream. The relative quantities of fluids produced are related to the holdup and upward velocity of each phase.

name: geostress ratio
description: The ratio of any two far-field principal stresses in the earth; see subtypes.

name: weathering depth
description: Depth of the weathered layer, the near-surface low velocity layer consisting of unconsolidated material and rock in which air rather than water fills the pore space.

name: color fluorescent light
description: The color emitted by the fluid upon exposure to fluorescent light. Certain photoactive hydrocarbon molecules display characteristic color patterns under these conditions.

name: receiver orientation rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of downhole receiver.

name: proposal number
description: Customer proposal number

name: fishneck length
description: Length of the fishing neck of an equipment item.

name: monotonic flag
description: Flag indicating that the data increase or decrease monotonically along their index. A monotonic function is one whose value either never increases or never decreases as the independent variable increases.

name: mud resistivity in
description: The electrical resistivity of mud going into the hole, usually measured in the active circulating pit

name: preparation method
description: Method by which an item or sample has been prepared for subsequent operations or analysis.

name: hydraulic power
description: Power produced or available from a system due to fluid flow, such as for pumps and turbines.

name: array code
description: Catalog-controlled code of an Array

name: magnetic toolface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between North and a reference direction on the drill string (e.g. Y-Axis accelerometer); used in hole sections of low deviation. Measurement represents an Azimuth, with values from 0 to 360 degrees.

name: deviation
description: Angular departure from some reference direction. When used with wells, it is the angle between the borehole axis and the vertical (also known as the Drift Angle).

name: apparent dip angle
description: Angle between the dip plane and the plane perpendicular to the borehole

name: booster pump flow
description: The flow rate of mud from a booster pump

name: max amount
description: Maximum Quantity

name: interval length
description: The length of an interval along a path, such as a Borehole path.

name: setting force
description: Load which must be applied to set compression type packer. Typical value : 10,000 lbf

name: annotation
description: Any annotation (or annotations) pertaining to an object. For example, annotations attached to a Map object.

name: anisotropy
description: Measure of the variation of a property based upon the direction in which it is measured.

name: bowl speed
description: The bowl speed of a centrifuge.

name: aluminum yield
description: Elemental contribution of Aluminum with respect to total.

name: tbg grade broken teeth
description: TBG Drill Bit Grade based on broken teeth

name: projection quadrant
description: Quadrant in which X and Y axes are positive, 1,2,3, or 4

name: dst gauge adapter code
description: Code for the DST Gauge Adapter

name: transfer fluid type
description: Liquid displaced away during sampling

name: pad force
description: Tool pad force

name: tank code
description: Code for the tank

name: weight indicator load
description: Weight indication as measured at the sensor. In a coiled tubing unit, the sensor is located at the base of the injector head.

name: hole condition type
description: The type of a borehole condition.

name: water production volume per lateral length per no of fractures
description: Normalized water cumulative per lateral length per number of fractures

name: stress gradient
description: Change in stress magnitude over distance.

name: geocentric scale factor
description: Scale factor used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: acoustic attenuation rate
description: A measure of the rate of attenuation of an acoustic wave per unit length.

name: url
description: Address of Worldwide Web site; acronym for Universal Resource Locator

name: asap parameter
description: Private structure used by the ASAP autotracking application.

name: port diameter
description: Diameter of each individual port

name: borehole failure azimuth
description: The azimuth of the point at which borehole failure starts.

name: max allowable pressure
description: Maximum allowable pressure for the equipment

name: derived inverse flattening
description: Flag indicating that the inverse flattening value of an ellipsoid has been derived from semi-major and semi-minor axis lengths.

name: geocentric s
description: Scale factor used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: luminous intensity
description: The density of luminous flux per unit solid angle, measured in a given direction relative to the emitting source.

name: drill fluid type
description: Generic type of the fluid used during a drilling activity; e.g., chemical gel mud, crude oil, caustic (high ph), gypsum mud, native mud, air, salt water, etc.

name: tubular code
description: Specific code of the tubular goods.

name: stack polarization azimuth
description: Estimation of the polarization azimuth angle for all layers to the current dept.

name: exponent
description: A number, normally symbolized as a superscript to a term in an expression, which indicates the power to which the term is raised.

name: liquid flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures
description: Change in liquid flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures

name: nominal source correction
description: Nominal correction vector to source position

name: formation temperature
description: Temperature of the (earth) formations.

name: acquisition shot number
description: Acquisition system shot number

name: sample water oil ratio
description: Water oil ratio when a sample is taken

name: firing head type
description: Type of TCP Equipment: firing head, debris sub, shock absorber, etc.

name: stop depth
description: Depth at which a particular activity stopped.

name: molybdenum dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of molybdenum to total dry weight

name: gas flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures
description: Change in gas flowrate per perforation length per number of fractures

name: net reservoir log porosity point match
description: Average porosity in the Net Reservoir portion of the summation interval, computed from log data by point-match method.

name: turbulence coefficient
description: The coefficient that describes the additional pressure drop due to inertial effects for high velocity gas flow.

name: min thickness
description: Minimum thickness, as for a reservoir unit. Also used for stress calculation with coiled tubing, with data supplied by the manufacturer

name: water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of Water with respect to the total volume; the product of Porosity and Water_Saturation

name: heat transfer coefficient
description: Amount of heat transferred per unit time per degree per unit area.

name: threshold ratio
description: Relative measure of trace value attribute; ratio of number of samples with values greater than threshold to total number of samples.

name: shallow laterolog conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: photoelectric factor
description: A measure of the probability that scattering due the Photoelectric Effect will occur; often expressed in an approximation unit barns/electron.

name: separator temperature
description: Temperature of the separator when a sample is taken

name: aspect ratio
description: Ratio of width to length. Also the ratio of vertical to horizontal scales on a graph, or that of the shorter to longer axes for an ellipse or ellipsoid.

name: conn 2 box flag
description: Flag indicating if connection is a box (Y) or a pin (N).

name: effective permeability gas
description: The measure of the capacity of gas to flow through a rock when the pore spaces of the rock contain other fluids.

name: surface cable tension
description: Tension of the logging cable as measured at the surface.

name: static potential
description: Static (built up) pressure of a hydraulic unit, converted to pressure potential at a reference datum depth.

name: acquisition rate
description: Channel acquisition rate: number of data samples acquired per unit of time

name: expiration date
description: Expiration date of a legal document or an item.

name: avg pressure
description: Pressure averaged on a given time.

name: solution gas oil ratio
description: Measure of the degree to which a gas is soluble in oil; ratio of the dissolved gas volume to liquid hydrocarbon volume, often designated Rs Oil

name: kb source dy
description: Y coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: latitude
description: The angle between the axis of the Earth and a tangent to the ellipsoid which approximates the shape of the Earth.

name: nominal source dy
description: Y coordinate of nominal correction vector to source position.

name: explicit index
description: Token, normally an integer, which is used as a reference or pointer to a value stored in some data structure.

name: litho type
description: The classification of lithology in a stratified environment, e.g. Carbonate, Shale, Sand, etc.

name: undisturbed zone water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of water in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: scan type
description: Describes the way in which a subject is scanned to take data samples or to generate an image.

name: wheel circumference
description: Wheel Circumference

name: von mises to yield ratio
description: Ratio of the Von_Mises_Stress to the Yield Strength of the material : It helps determine whether the material has yielded (permanently damaged) by comparing to the yield_stress (greater than 1, permanently deformed).

name: avg qs ratio
description: Average (harmonic mean) value of the shear wave quality factor.

name: date format
description: Specification of how date information will be formatted.

name: storage label
description: Label found on any stored item, such as tapes, documents, etc.

name: toolface data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a toolface measurement.

name: fracture bridging factor
description: Ratio of fracture width to mean proppant diameter (Industry usage: 2.5.) below which bridging will occur (proppant cannot move through the fracture).

name: coolant temperature
description: Temperature of the cooling fluid

name: true source position x coord
description: X-coordinate of true source position.

name: orientation
description: The spatial orientation of an object. Usually defined by a vector who origin location is known relative to a coordinate system (e.g., in spherical coordinates, the Vector will be defined by the 3 angles Rho, Theta and Phi)

name: data acquisition mode
description: Software or hardware option whose selection controls some aspect of data acquisition.

name: vertical datum name
description: Name of the permanent Vertical Datum to which the local elevation reference is related. Typical Vertical Datums are "Mean Sea Level" and "Least Astronomic Tide".

name: velocity squared
description: The square of a velocity

name: amplitude ratio
description: Ratio of two amplitude values.

name: gas flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures
description: Change in gas flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures

name: spontaneous potential
description: The potential difference (DC voltage) between a movable electrode in the borehole and a distant reference electrode usually at surface. The voltage is due to currents generated by the Electrochemical and Electrokinetic potentials.

name: horizontal permeability
description: A permeability oriented horizontally along the bedding plane of the stratum. Usually abbreviated as Kx.

name: y direction permeability
description: Permeability in Y Direction

name: acoustic impedance ratio
description: Ratio of the acoustic impedance of two adjacent beds or intervals

name: noise to signal ratio
description: The ratio of noise amplitude to signal amplitude, usually expressed in dB. Note: the inverse, Signal_To_Noise_Ratio, is preferred and should be used whenever possible.

name: annulus pressure
description: Pressure of the fluid in the annulus. The annulus is the region outside the subject pipe, such as the region between drill pipe and the formation, or between casing and formation, or between tubing and casing.

name: min oil saturation 3phase
description: Minimum oil saturation in a 3 phase system. (SCAL SORM)

name: state name
description: Name of a State

name: relative permeability
description: The ratio of effective permeability divided by the absolute permeability; e.g. the relative permeability of a rock to that of any of its contained fluids.

name: interporosity flow coefficient
description: Describes the conductance of flow from matrix to fissures. Usually known as Lambda in reservoir dynamics.

name: equivalent per mass
description: The amount of a chemical equivalent contained in a unit mass

name: survey east west
description: Indicates whether survey location is East or West of reference line, such as principal meridian.

name: length
description: Linear extent of a measured distance or dimension.

name: calcium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of calcium to total dry weight

name: duty cycle
description: Amount of time it takes to start, operate, stop and idle a machine when it is used for intermittent duty; also, proportion of working time as compared to total operating time.

name: chromiumnickel yield
description: Elemental contribution of Chromiumnickel with respect to total.

name: water flowrate per number of fractures
description: Normalized water flowrate per number of fractures

name: max magnitude
description: Maximum magnitude.

name: nrm factor
description: NRM factor

name: fluid conductivity
description: The electric conductivity of a fluid

name: igneous volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of igneous rock with respect to the total volume.

name: q ratio
description: Quality factor for compressional waves. The ratio of 2*pi times the peak compressional wave energy to the energy dissipated in a cycle.

name: undisturbed zone irreducible water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of irreducible water in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: seismic offset
description: The distance between source and receiver or geophone (seismic).

name: water oil ratio
description: A measure of the volume of water which is produced with a given quantity of oil.

name: shear velocity gradient
description: A measure of the change in the shear velocity of a medium per unit length.

name: pump liner diameter
description: Diameter of the pump entry line

name: evaporite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of evaporitic rock with respect to the total volume.

name: fluid permeability factor
description: Fraction of the fracture permeability retained at in-situ conditions after taking into account the damage due to fluid residue, function of the breaker, gel concentration and temperature at closure. Has the same effect as Proppant_Permeability_Factor.

name: stoneley slowness
description: The acoustic slowness of a Stoneley wave; a Stoneley wave is a type of seismic wave which is propagated along an interface, such as a tube wave in a borehole.

name: data compression flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not downhole data compression is possible with this equipment.

name: standard pressure
description: Pressure considered to be "standard", for rates and volumes reported to be measured at Standard Conditions.

name: battery charge
description: The quantity of electric charge in a battery

name: shear impedance reflectivity
description: Reflectivity due to changes in shear impedance

name: value type
description: Code of value type of data

name: spring number
description: Spring number of a cylindrical rheometer corresponding to a particular stiffness. Fann 35 spr #1stiffness is 2.2116E-3 Nm/Rad

name: max allowable surface pressure
description: Maximum allowable mud surface pressure in annulus (drill-pipe x casing) to be used during well control operations so as not to exceed the FIT/LOT equivalent mud weight.

name: settled proppant height
description: Height of the settled bank of proppant within a fracture, otherwise named pack height.

name: water density
description: The density of water.

name: hydrogen mole fraction
description: Mole fraction of Hydrogen to total gas composition

name: critical mud density
description: The mud density that initiates formation shear or tensile failure.

name: tube nom outside diameter
description: Nominal outside diameter of body or API nominal outside diameter of tube

name: origin northing
description: The northing of the point of origin of an orthogonal grid constructed on a map projection. Often, this value is defined to be a positive number to avoid negative coordinates. Sometimes called "false northing".

name: luminous flux
description: Rate of flow of visible-wavelength radiant energy, as measured from a point source and within a unit solid angle.

name: fault heave
description: Horizontal component of separation or displacement on a fault.

name: avg amplitude
description: Average (mean) value of amplitude.

name: layer transmissibility ratio
description: Ratio of layer transmissibility to total transmissibility ("kappaj")

name: x display identifier
description: XServer Id on which application is to display output

name: longitude reference 1
description: Latitude of first reference point in projection definition.

name: liquid production volume per lateral length per no of fractures
description: Normalized liquid cumulative per lateral length per number of fractures

name: neutron data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed, for a neutron logging measurement.

name: mre latitude coefficient
description: Coefficient for a latitude term in a multiple regression equation for computing geodetic datum shifts.

name: interval anisotropic axis 1 crossline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 1 crossline direction for a layer.

name: royalty
description: Royalty received by lessor

name: working pressure
description: Pressure at which an equipment item normally operates

name: shear compressional velocity ratio
description: Ratio of velocity of Shear wave (Vs) to that of Compressional wave (Vp).

name: continuous
description: Abstract property intended to serve as a root of numeric properties with unit labels

name: initial oil saturation
description: Oil Saturation at the beginning of the test, experiment or production.

name: liquid productivity index
description: Ratio of liquid flow rate to pressure drop.

name: thin out azimuth
description: Azimuth of the thin out of a barrier type depositional environment.

name: treatment displacement volume
description: Dead volume including the surface treating lines to be pumped to move the treating fluid down to formation. In cementing it is the volume (through casing/tubing/ drillpipe) up to the landing collar; in acidizing it is the tubing volume to perforations

name: density gradient
description: A measure of the change in the density of a material per unit length.

name: fold type
description: Type of fold (e.g., Rollover)

name: effective permeability gas swi
description: Effective permeability to gas at initial water saturation.

name: bit bladed flag
description: Flag indicating that the bit is a bladed type (PDC type bit).

name: vertical section
description: Vertical Section, historical name given to the horizontal distance from the surface location to the downhole point (horizontal counterpart to True Vertical Depth).

name: map modeled time
description: Two-way time obtained through map modeling of depth surface data

name: receiver group count
description: Total number of receiver groups attached to the cable

name: kb receiver dy
description: Y coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: thorium concentration
description: Concentration of Thorium by weight

name: waveform number
description: Waveform number

name: transit time accuracy
description: The accuracy attached to the transit time measurement or computation.

name: heterogeneity cosine of phase
description: Measure of heterogeneity computed from the Cosine of Phase trace over a given interval.

name: gas flowrate per length
description: Change in gas flowrate per length

name: interval alkhalifah eta
description: Interval value of Alkhalifah's eta anisotropy parameter, describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout Compressional velocities, for each layer.

name: cement retarder type
description: Type of material used to retard the setting of the cement.

name: initial amount
description: Initial amount. Usually used to quantify the initial amount of some material.

name: matrix compressibility
description: The compressibility of a homogeneous solid material.

name: specific gravity
description: The ratio of the density of a substance to the density of some other substance taken as a standard (e.g. water, hydrogen).

name: spacing x
description: Spacing in X dimension; may be expressed as an absolute spacing with units or as a proportion of some reference X Spacing.

name: penetration depth
description: Depth to which some medium is penetrated, such as by a drill bit or probe, or by fluid invasion. (Not to be used for borehole depth.)

name: isothermal compressibility
description: Compressibility carried out isothermally

name: pore pressure
description: The pressure of the fluid contained in the pore volume.

name: oil density
description: The density of oil.

name: mud pressure gradient
description: The Mud density expressed in pressure gradient. Usually used to compare the mud induced pressure with the pore and frac pressure.

name: flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of fluid.

name: binset skew
description: Angle between Binset axes measured counterclockwise from positive X axis to positive Y axis

name: slurry density
description: Slurry density

name: magnetic field strength
description: The force per unit magnetic pole (or current per unit length). Also called Magnetizing Force or Magnetic Intensity.

name: pressure
description: The force or thrust exerted over a surface divided by its area; e.g., hydrostatic, flow, pump, etc. May be gauge or absolute.

name: delay time
description: The time difference by which one event lags another. In refraction seismic work, the additional time required to traverse a raypath over the time which would be required to traverse the horizontal component at the highest velocity encountered on the raypath.

name: relaxation time ratio
description: In nuclear magnetic resonance logging, the ratio of longitudinal to transverse relaxation time; used to determine polarization correction.

name: trough peak delta depth
description: Depth difference between trough and peak where trough occurs first in increasing depth

name: power per volume
description: Power per volume

name: radial length
description: Length measured in a radial direction.

name: unit attribute
description: Name of Object Attribute where Unit may be found if not otherwise specified

name: true source position z coord
description: Z-coordinate of true source position.

name: stack inline dip
