description: Estimation of the inline dip for all layers to the current depth.

name: ideal source position 2 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal source position 2.

name: ltlp filter cake thickness
description: Thickness of filter cake produced under low temperature, low pressure (LTLP) conditions.

name: final transfer pressure
description: Final pressure of shipping bottle

name: albite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of albite to total dry weight

name: matrix epithermal neutron porosity
description: Matrix response of an epithermal neutron porosity logging device.

name: battery type
description: Recorder battery type

name: z coordinate
description: Z-coordinate of Location

name: length recovered
description: Length of a sample recovered from some well operation (e.g. Core Sample).

name: curvature radius
description: Radius of the circle whose arc would have a given curvature.

name: reynolds number
description: The ratio of inertial force to viscous force for viscous fluid flow.

name: phase velocity
description: The velocity of any given phase (such as a trough) or a wave of single frequency; may differ from Group Velocity due to dispersion in the medium.

name: deep induction resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by an induction log, which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: address
description: The location where some entity or information may be found or contacted.

name: apparent dip azimuth top of hole
description: In the plane perpendicular to the borehole, viewed from above the tool, angle measured clockwise from the top of hole direction to the projection of the true dip azimuth.

name: sandface flowing pressure
description: The pressure in the formation immediately prior to entering any completion pressure drops.

name: dimensionless borehole radius
description: Dimensionless Borehole Radius ("rwD")

name: negative slope
description: Negative slope value.

name: transmission coefficient
description: Ratio of the amplitude of a transmitted wave to that of the incident wave; may be greater than 1.

name: water activity
description: Measure of the water concentration in aqueous solutions expressed as a decimal fraction between 0 and 1 ( = 1 for pure water)

name: siderite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of siderite with respect to the total volume.

name: grade
description: A rating of some sort given to an item (e.g., equipment) by some standards organization as the API, the IADC, etc.

name: max depth
description: Maximum Depth

name: clay volume fraction
description: Volume fraction of clay as calculated, measured or inferred from formation properties.

name: sale group
description: Within a business line, Sales services are gathered by group with technical commonalities.

name: magnesium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of magnesium to total dry weight

name: sphericity
description: A measure of the degree of how spherical an object is, such as an Lens within a subsurface Volume

name: shallow laterolog resistivity
description: The resistivity, measured by a laterolog (or guard log) resistivity device, which represents a measurement made approximately one to two feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contains fluids which are comprised primarily of mud filtrate.

name: reflection coefficient
description: Ratio of the displacement amplitude of a reflected wave to that of the incident wave. Also called Reflectivity.

name: standard document identifier
description: Standard document identifier, such as an ISBN or ISSN number.

name: recovery ratio
description: Ratio of amount of sample or material recovered to total amount recoverable.

name: reciprocal time
description: was operations per time

name: stroke rate
description: Frequency of the piston (plunger) of a pump usually expressed in number of strokes per minute

name: anhydrite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of anhydrite with respect to the total volume.

name: drill motor code
description: Specific code of the Motor or Turbine.

name: min water flowrate
description: Minimum water flowrate

name: mineral resistivity
description: Mineral Resistivity

name: slew rate
description: Highest rate of change in signal level which a device can produce; also the rate at which a device reacts to commands. In the latter case, the data are normally represented in units of time.

name: net pay thickness
description: The cumulative thickness of hydrocarbon bearing rocks which satisfy local criteria for a "pay zone"; the footage which satisfies the Net Reservoir conditions and where the water saturation cutoff, permeability cutoff and any discriminator cutoffs specified as "Net Pay" are satisfied; abbreviated "H" for a Hydraulic Unit.

name: dip detection source
description: The source of information used to detect dips (e.g., Seismic data, Structural analysis, Dipmeter log data, etc.)

name: vertical lift temperature
description: Computed temperature at some depth in tubing

name: thermal neutron porosity
description: Porosity as measured with a thermal neutron logging device.

name: mass attenuation coefficient
description: The degree to which a mass attenuates a beam through a unit length. The beam could be light or other particles.

name: gas saturation at breakthrough
description: Gas saturation at the breakthrough point. In Special Core Analysis, breakthrough is the appearance of the injected fluid at the outlet face of the rock sample.

name: distance unit
description: Unit for distance data, typically m or ft.

name: pore throat diameter
description: The measured or effective diameter of the aperture which connects pores or void spaces within a rock matrix.

name: coil tubing section
description: Number of the Coiled Tubing section used by the CoilLIFE module.

name: micro inverse resistivity
description: Micro Resistivity measurement using an "inverse" lateral electrode arrangement; traditionally combined with Micro Normal Resistivity in a Microlog survey for identifying permeable beds.

name: luminous exposure
description: Luminous exposure is the cumulative light experienced onver a unit solid angle, that is, the illuminance integrated over time.

name: gamma ray time after bit
description: In MWD/LWD logging, the time delay between the drill bit and a gamma ray sensor reaching a given point in the wellbore.

name: origin rho
description: Radial distance of the origin of a Local Coordinate System, measured with respect to the origin of the "from" coordinate system. Units, if any, are those of the "from" system.

name: outlet connection size
description: The connection size of the output line to the equipment

name: ideal source position 1 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal source position 1.

name: stack anisotropic axis 2 crossline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 2 crossline direction for all layers to the current depth.

name: specific volume
description: A measure of the volume distribution of a gas or liquid per unit mass.

name: molar mass
description: The mass of one mole of a substance

name: liquid formation volume factor
description: Ratio of total liquid volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions to the total liquid volume at surface (stock tank) conditions.

name: nozzle size
description: Diameter of the nozzle(s) used in an equipment item, such as a drill bit

name: transit time shear
description: Shear wave transit time

name: x gravity
description: Strength of the x-axis component of the gravitational field at some location.

name: loaded by
description: Name of person who loaded data

name: lag usage flag
description: When set, wavelet lag is used.

name: gas viscosity
description: The viscosity of a gas at specific temperature and pressure conditions.

name: inverse temperature
description: This is a copy of the unit quantity InverseTemperature, which acts as the parent for other SDM_Property instances

name: high mass per time
description: Mass flowrate for large quantities

name: interval sayers anellipticity
description: Interval value of Sayers' normalized anellipticity factor an alternative to eta for describing the relationship between horizontal and moveout compressional velocities, for each layer.

name: mud density out
description: The density of mud coming out of the hole, usually measured in the ditch before the shale shakers

name: indicator
description: Property which indicates presence of some entity, occurrence or condition, or which quantifies some condition, often as a proportion of some local reference value. Often called _Factor or _Coefficient.

name: stage volume
description: Volume of material pumped during a stage of an activity.

name: bubble point pressure
description: The pressure at reservoir temperature at which gas in solution in crude oil comes out of solution as free gas.

name: color
description: The aspect of objects and light sources that may be described in terms of hue, lightness, and saturation for objects and hue, brightness, and saturation for light sources.

name: damaged zone thickness
description: Thickness of the near-wellbore Damaged Zone, the sandface layer around the wellbore where permeability and mobility are impaired, generally by a damaging material (e.g. completion or drilling fluid).

name: sensor code
description: Sensor code

name: proppant concentration
description: Proppant concentration expressed as mass of proppant added per gallon of gel, legacy (LIS) unit "PPA"

name: pipe inside diameter
description: Inside diameter of pipe

name: block height
description: Position of the blocks above the drill floor reference point

name: documentation file
description: Name of file containing related documentation

name: eccentering azimuth
description: Azimuth of the line from the center of an area to an eccentered object.

name: net pay moved hc volume fraction
description: Net pay moved hydrocarbon volume fraction: moved oil saturation (Sxo-Sw) in the net pay of the zone multiplied by the net pay average porosity.

name: organization role
description: Role of organization (e.g. Business Associate)

name: bandwidth rating debias
description: Statistical estimation of bandwidth of data within window. The bandwidth rating debias D is computed from the bandwidth rating bias B as follows: D = 5/3 B - 1/(s*n), where n is the number of sampled used in the computation. Generally more stable than Bandwidth_Rating_Bias, unless window is small.

name: neutron capture cross section quality indicator
description: Property used to indicate quality or confidence of data from a neutron capture cross section survey.

name: digital file format version
description: Identification of the digital file format version (e.g., 3.0a). Note that this information is often encoded within the file.

name: volume per area
description: Describes the volume per area. E.g. the quantity of hydrocarbons generated in an area

name: poisson ratio
description: Ratio of the transverse contraction of a body to its longitudinal extension when stretched. Typical values in minerals are from 0.15 to 0.3 (Carbonates:0.15, Sandstones:0.2, Shales:0.25).

name: flow head type
description: Type of flow head

name: bob number
description: Bob number. The bob is the inner cylinder of a cylindrical rheometer. Each number corresponds to a different size. Standard bob is #1

name: bulk density
description: Density of bulk material, including any void space or other materials contained in the subject volume. In well logging, it is the density of the rock, including fluid-filled pore space, as measured with a "Gamma-Gamma" type logging device.

name: sodium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of sodium to total dry weight

name: medium resistivity
description: The resistivity which represents a measurement made approximately two to three feet into the formation; generally considered to measure the formation where it contain fluids which are a mixture of mud filtrate, connate water and possibly hydrocarbons.

name: duration unit
description: Unit for this Data

name: water salinity
description: Total salts in solution (Na, K, Cl, So4, ..). Normal sea water has around 35,000 ppm (parts per million) salinity. Less than 2,000 ppm is considered "fresh".

name: pond depth
description: For a centrifuge, Position of overflow Port relative to Inner Bowl Wall

name: volumetric heat capacity
description: Extensive heat capacity per volume, the ability of a given volume of a substance to store internal energy while undergoing a given temperature change, but without undergoing a phase change.

name: sequence lower limit type
description: The type of surface situated at the base of a sequence.

name: landing collar depth
description: Measured depth of the collar on which the cement plugs seat : this data is required to compute the displacement volume of a cementing operation.

name: casing outside diameter
description: Casing outer diameter

name: unit column
description: Database column name where Unit may be found if not otherwise indicated.

name: packer motion type
description: Internal tubular (e.g. tubing) motion allowed by the packer during an increase in pressure. Choices: Free (Packer does not restrain motion), Limited (tubular is free to shorten but not lengthen) and No Motion.

name: flushed zone bound water volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of bound water in the flushed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: curvature
description: A measure of the degree to which a path is curved relative to the length of the path along the curve.

name: thermal diffusivity
description: A measure of the rate at which heat is conducted through a medium. Typical value for rock material is ~.01 cm2/s.

name: anti collision method
description: Method used for calculating the proximity: 0 - Normal; 1 - Horizontal; 2 - Least Distance

name: running speed
description: Speed of an equipment running into (counted positive) or out of the hole (counted negative).

name: type
description: The type of any item. Applies to all items in all domains.

name: avg seismic velocity
description: Special usage of Avg_Acoustic_Velocity which deals specifically with the velocity between a reference datum near the surface and some subsurface point; often a vertical path is implied and the velocity is computed as depth divided by seismic travel time.

name: well test model type
description: Type of Well Test Model selected

name: hydrostatic pressure
description: Pressure due to the weight of a column of liquid (formation water, drilling mud, etc.) extending from the depth of interest to the liquid level.

name: beaufort scale number
description: The Beaufort wind scale is a system used to estimate and report wind speeds when no measuring apparatus is available. It was invented in the early 19th century by Admiral Sir Francis Beaufort of the British Navy as a way to interpret winds from conditions at sea, e.g. 5 on the Beaufort scale corresponds to a wind of 17-21 knots and is defined as "Fresh Breeze: Moderate waves (1.8m), many white horses."

name: tool string measure point offset
description: Distance from the Measure Point to the Tool String (not just Tool!) Reference Plane; a positive value indicates that the Measure Point is above the Reference Plane. [Traditionally referred to as "tool zero".]

name: shrinkage factor
description: A measure of the decrease in volume of the liquid phase caused by release of solution gas and/or by the thermal contraction of the liquid; the reciprocal of formation volume factor.

name: production history type
description: Type of production/Injection data set : Previous_Flow_History (Production), Injection, Previous_Flow_History (Production), Simulated_Behavior (Test), Actual_Field (Flow)

name: client representative
description: Name of the client representative or company man.

name: mud filtrate salinity
description: Salinity of mud filtrate

name: inverse penetration rate
description: Inverse of drilling penetration rate.

name: user trace selection
description: Good/bad marker

name: max concentration 2
description: Maximum concentration or proportion of second component

name: drift diameter
description: Largest diameter of a perfect cylinder of a specified length that can fit into the pipe. Because a pipe is never perfectly cylindrical but slightly oval the drift diameter is always smaller than the quoted inner diameter. The drift diameter is used to know if a given pipe or instrument will run into a pipe.

name: max tension
description: Maximum tension

name: dielectric resistivity
description: Resistivity measurement which has been compensated for the dielectric constant of the formation..

name: tension
description: The force tending to cause extension of a body, as experienced in a cable, rope, string, etc.

name: max delay time
description: Maximum Delay Time

name: eou computation method
description: Method used for calculating the ellipse of uncertainty: 0 - Wolfe and de Wardt; 1 - Conic

name: agreement interest
description: Percentage of interest held by one of the potentially many organizations holding a lease agreement.

name: receiver station datum elevation
description: Datum elevation at each station relative to sea level

name: trough peak delta amplitude
description: Amplitude difference between trough and peak.

name: logger elevation reference code
description: Code of the elevation reference for logging data

name: hemisphere
description: Code of the earth hemisphere (Northern or Southern) in which this projection is located.

name: uranium potassium ratio
description: Ratio of concentration of Uranium to that of Potassium.

name: fluid return outlet
description: Location of drilling fluid outlet of the circulating system. It is normally on the rig floor at the level of mud pit. In some offshore cases (conductor) it can be on the sea bed.

name: thorium potassium ratio
description: Ratio of concentration of Thorium to that of Potassium.

name: specific heat capacity per temperature
description: The change in specific heat capacity with temperature

name: nom pressure loss
description: The nominal pressure loss in a piece of equipment, such as a Drill_Motor or an MWD_Tool.

name: magnetic bladeface
description: In directional drilling, the angle between Magnetic North and a sensor contained in a stabilizer blade; Measurement represents an Azimuth, with values from 0 to 360 degrees.

name: resistivity anisotropy
description: Change in resistivity based upon the direction in which it is measured.

name: p wave angle
description: P-wave angle

name: mud pump monitoring purpose
description: The purpose of the mud pump monitoring. It can be either for well control or monitoring the pump parameters at working conditions.

name: serial number
description: The serial number placed on a piece of equipment.

name: slant rig angle
description: Slant rig angle

name: gas differential pressure
description: Gas differential pressure across the orifice plate when a sample is taken

name: kb receiver dz
description: Z coordinate of correction vector to receiver position relative to Kelly Bushing.

name: activation pressure
description: Pressure at which recording should begin

name: horizontal formation resistivity
description: Formation resistivity measured parallel to layering. (for "Transverse-Isotropic (TI)" rock"

name: resistivity k factor
description: K Factor, a function of the geometry of the electrode or sensor array of a resistivity measurement device.

name: pitch length
description: Measure of slope using the linear distance between two successive points: on a screw, between threads, measured parallel to the axis; for a propeller or spinner, the theoretical axial displacement corresponding to one revolution.

name: stack thomsen epsilon
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Thomsen's epsilon anisotropy parameter.

name: user evaluation code
description: Auxiliary user-defined mask

name: mineral code
description: Catalog-controlled code of a mineral.

name: reluctance
description: The resistance of a medium to a magnetic field; the magnetic equivalent of electric impedance

name: static pressure date
description: Date when Static Pressure data were recorded

name: nom cable depth
description: Nominal cable depth, such as that planned for the receiver cable in a marine seismic survey.

name: ownership amount
description: Lessor percentage ownership

name: water viscosibility
description: Normalized derivative of viscosity for water: -(dv/dp)/v where v=viscosity and p=pressure.

name: cable type
description: Type of cable.

name: bandwidth rating bias
description: Statistical estimation of bandwidth of data within window. Aids in determining appropriate spectral operators for subsequent operations. Computation: Let the autocorrelation of the trace be A[i]. Then compute M = max(A) and S = sum(A[i]**2). The bandwidth rating bias B is then : B = M**2 / r(2 S - M**2), where r is the sample rate.

name: relative permeability oil
description: Ratio of effective oil permeability to absolute permeability. Usually abbreviated as Kro.

name: time unit
description: Unit for Time data

name: crushed zone permeability
description: Permeability of the Crushed Zone around perforation

name: classification group code
description: Associates class definitions into one family: Generic, Unsupervised, Pore_Fluid, Lithologic, Seismostratigraphic, Texture, User_Defined_Mix, User_Defined_No_Mix.

name: contractor
description: The code of the contractor, usually a company.

name: ideal source position 1 z coord
description: Z-coordinate of ideal source position 1.

name: well treatment fluid type
description: Type of Fluid used in Well Treatment operation

name: bandwidth rating debias wavenumber
description: Bandwidth rating debias in depth domain. See Bandwidth_Rating_Debias

name: density
description: The density (mass per unit volume) of a material. Usually at Standard conditions (STP). Also used to indicate the frequency of occurrence.

name: cost per time
description: Amount of money per unit of time

name: true common depthpoint number
description: CDP Line Number

name: oil flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of oil component of fluid.

name: flowrate index
description: Unitless quantity proportional to flowrate within a given borehole environment. Flowrate indices are comparable only when the borehole and casing sizes are the same.

name: activity name
description: Commonly used name for an Activity.

name: density caliper
description: Borehole diameter as estimated by a density logging device.

name: i c5h12 concentration
description: Concentration of iso-Pentane (i-C5H12); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.3%.

name: contract number
description: Identifying string for contractual agreement

name: free fluid index
description: The proportion of the bulk volume of the formation which is occupied by fluids which are free to flow; commonly abbreviated FFI, measured using nuclear magnetic resonance techniques.

name: absorbed dose
description: Absorbed dose is a measure of the energy deposited in a medium by ionizing radiation.

name: irreducible water saturation
description: The fraction of the pore volume occupied by water in a reservoir at maximum hydrocarbon saturation, such that it cannot be further reduced.

name: c6h14 concentration
description: Concentration of Hexane (C6H14); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.3%.

name: trough peak delta time
description: Time difference between trough and peak

name: nom inside diameter
description: Nominal (approximate, for naming purposes only) inside diameter of an equipment item.

name: element table
description: Table containing an element of a collection.

name: pattern length
description: The length of a pattern, usually pertaining to a dip pattern or a geological feature. The length is usually an interval length like depth.

name: std parallel
description: Latitude of parallel along which scale is true.

name: oil flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures
description: Change in oil flowrate per lateral length per number of fractures

name: gas d factor
description: In non-Darcy flow, this is the deviation from the expected flow rate

name: glauconite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of glauconite with respect to the total volume.

name: snap window top
description: Interval above the picked Z to search for the Tracking Event and Snap_Type when snapping

name: lower surface relation
description: The type of relationship between a surface and the ones below (e.g. the surfaces below a Horizon are eroded).

name: dolomite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of dolomite to total dry weight

name: text
description: Textual body a document or document section, such as a contract clause.

name: contract status
description: Status of a contract.

name: absolute roughness
description: Average amplitude of rugosity, such as the variations in the radius of tubing.

name: ideal receiver position 2
description: Idealized receiver position 2

name: standard reference datum
description: Depth measured from the Standard Reference Datum

name: reservoir distance
description: The distance between two features in a reservoir, for use in modeling the reservoir.

name: separator type
description: Separator type

name: hydrogen dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of hydrogen to total dry weight

name: zirconium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Zirconium with respect to total.

name: person name
description: Name of a person

name: kb source correction
description: Correction vector to source position relative to Kelly Bushing

name: reciprocal volume
description: was per volume

name: 1 minute gel strength
description: Shear Stress required to break a gel fluid previously allowed to remain at rest for 1 minute.

name: avg magnitude
description: Average (mean) magnitude.

name: bubble size
description: Diameter of the bubbles of non-continuous production phase.

name: mud pump type
description: The type of pump used to pump drilling fluid or mud, usually into the borehole during drilling operations.

name: geocentric rx
description: Rotation of the geocentric Cartesian coordinate system about its X axis. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: net reservoir permeability thickness
description: The product of the Net Reservoir Thickness and Net Reservoir Average Permeability.

name: drill structure type
description: Generic type of drilling structure such as land rig, barge rig, submersible rig, jack-up rig, semisubmersible rig, drillships, structure rig

name: personnel count
description: Headcount of personnel satisfying role of Personnel_Role; these may be implemented as lists.

name: acquisition enable flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not acquisition is enabled for this activity.

name: oil production volume per lateral length
description: Normalized oil cumulative per lateral length

name: representation code
description: Catalog code of the Representation

name: total depth date
description: The date/time at which the drilling reached total depth.

name: origin easting
description: The easting of the point of origin of an orthogonal grid constructed on a map projection. Often, this value is defined to be a positive number to avoid negative coordinates. Sometimes called "false easting".

name: borehole neutron capture cross section
description: The macroscopic neutron capture cross section, i.e. the effective cross sectional area per unit volume, of the borehole environment; used to correct "Sigma" log measurements for borehole effects.

name: separator liquid capacity
description: Separator liquid capacity at maximum working pressure and 1 minute retention time at high liquid level

name: stack anisotropic axis 2 inline direction
description: Estimation of the anisotropic axis 2 inline direction for all layers to the current depth.

name: well spacing
description: Average distance between two wells, connected or not to regulatory petroleum laws

name: boron yield
description: Elemental contribution of Boron with respect to total.

name: phosphorus yield
description: Elemental contribution of Phosphorus with respect to total.

name: major dimension
description: Major (normally longer) dimension of an object; the actual type of measurement depends upon the shape of the object. [Used for Drilling Targets, whose shapes could be Elliptical, Circular, Rectangular...]

name: ads blocking factor
description: Blocking factor for the Array Data Server

name: bottom location
description: The location of the Bottom of any Entity with a geometric extent (e.g., Zone Interval, Borehole, Borehole Segment, Rig, Arc, Edge, etc.). It is represented by some position relative to a coordinate system.

name: pseudocritical pressure
description: The pressure needed to condense the vapor of a gas mixture at its pseudocritical temperature. Analogous to Critical_Pressure for pure components.

name: true source sensor position
description: Position of sensor placed near source, for detection of shot event.

name: reflection angle
description: The angle which the raypath of a reflected ray makes with the perpendicular to the interface. At the "reflection point" it is equal to the Incident_Angle for pressure-pressure or shear-shear reflections.

name: great circle axis
description: The pole to a plane represented by a great circle.

name: mud compressional slowness
description: Acoustic compressional slowness (Delta-T) of the drilling fluid.

name: drill sub type
description: Type of sub - bent, bent orienting, cross-over, bitsaver, kelly-saver, extension, UBHO (Universal Bottom Hole Orienting), float, saver, lift, pressure release, etc

name: cycle sample count
description: Target number of samples per hour.

name: orifice plate diameter
description: Diameter of orifice plate in gas metering system when a sample is taken

name: calcite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of calcite with respect to the total volume.

name: electric field strength
description: The force per unit charge (or voltage gradient).

name: z transverse amplitude
description: Z component of Transverse_Amplitude in multi-component seismic.

name: fluorine yield
description: Elemental contribution of Fluorine with respect to total.

name: station number
description: Depth identifier

name: adsorption
description: The adhesion in an extremely thin layer of molecules (as of gases, solutes, or liquids) to the surfaces of solid bodies or liquids with which they are in contact

name: avg penetration rate
description: Average drilling penetration rate (ROP)

name: magnesium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Magnesium with respect to total.

name: volume per length
description: The measure of volume per linear displacement, usually given in bbl/in, bbl/ft, U.S. gal/ft.

name: max x
description: Maximum X Coordinate for region

name: title
description: A formal descriptive name, such as for a publication; also used for the role of person in an organization.

name: temperature sensor resolution
description: The minimum significant temperature change that can be detected above the noise. This is measured as the standard deviation of the differences between two successive measurements.

name: bend 1 bend 2 angle
description: Angle between the planes defined by the first and second bends in the equipment string.

name: fault displacement
description: The measure of the relative movement of the 2 sides of a fault.

name: generation rate per temperature
description: Describes the generation of hydrocarbons from kerogen in dependency to temperature

name: conn torsional yield
description: Maximum torque which can be applied to the joint/connection/thread without causing permanent deformation.

name: depth value type
description: Value type of depth data

name: axial spacing
description: The spacing or distance between two locations on an equipment item; for example, between two sensors on a logging tool.

name: capillary pressure
description: The difference in pressure between two phases, air fluid, gas fluid or between two fluids, measured at points of the interconnected phases.

name: oil bubble flow velocity
description: Oil Bubble Velocity

name: wave period
description: Average elapsed time between the passing of two wave peaks.

name: legal ellipsoid
description: Code of legislated geodetic ellipsoid.

name: snap quality
description: Indicates whether the values are snapped to a sample or sub-sample

name: subsea vertical depth
description: Vertical Depth from Mean Sea Level

name: gravity
description: Strength of the gravitational field at some location. Also referred to as the acceleration of gravity, measured in units of acceleration.

name: mud nitrate concentration
description: Concentration of nitrates in mud.

name: central line x alignment
description: Alignment of central line x-coordinate: 0 if central line is x-axis, 1 if x-axis is east west

name: sodium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Sodium with respect to total.

name: origin x
description: X component of the location of the origin of a Local Coordinate System, measured with respect to the origin of the "from" coordinate system. Units, if any, are those of the "from" system.

name: spring stiffness
description: Coefficient relating spiral spring exerted force and corresponding elongation

name: mud pump discharge pressure
description: Mud pump maximum discharge pressure

name: coal volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of coal with respect to the total volume.

name: msl source dx
description: X coordinate of correction vector to source position relative to Mean Sea Level.

name: true source line position z
description: Z-coordinate of true position in a source line.

name: pattern name
description: Name of a pattern or style, such as a graphic pattern.

name: reel core width
description: Width between flanges of the drum core, such as for a coiled tubing reel

name: nmr diffusion coefficient
description: In nuclear magnetic resonance analysis, the measure of the ability of the molecule containing the polarized proton to diffuse (or move) through a medium.

name: pm titration volume
description: Amount of 0.02 normal (N/50) standard sulfuric acid required in order to turn the color of phenolphthalein indicator solution from pink to colorless when determining phenolphthalein alkalinity of the mud, Pm, API RP13 Section 8, Chemical Analysis.

name: reduced volume
description: The volume of a fluid divided by the critical volume of the fluid.

name: max threshold
description: Maximum threshold value.

name: max thickness
description: Maximum thickness, as for a reservoir unit.

name: lost time flag
description: Flag indicating whether or not an event caused a delay in operation.

name: contact throw sense
description: Specify whether contact corresponds to upthrown or downthrown portion of fault.

name: rank
description: Integer denoting the order of an element in a collection, such as the rank of a Layer participating in a Sequence or Stratigraphic Column.

name: central line pt1 latitude
description: Latitude of first point on central line of projection.

name: window start time
description: Start time of the processing window.

name: pressure loss
description: The difference between input and output pressure, usually due to friction.

name: max data set count
description: Maximum number of Data Set

name: sample count
description: Number of samples.

name: flowing fluid type
description: Type of fluid flowing into or out of a well completion: Condensate, Oil, Gas, etc.

name: recorder delay time
description: Delay time between instrument power-on time and when recording begins

name: montmorillonite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of montmorillonite to total dry weight

name: max gooseneck pressure
description: Maximum pressure observed during a Coil Tubing job at the goose neck

name: matrix neutron capture cross section
description: The macroscopic capture cross section, i.e. the effective cross-sectional area per unit volume, of the rock matrix for the capture of neutrons.

name: top dip number
description: Number of Dip (in the Dip Set) at the top of the Bed

name: energy density
description: The amount of energy per unit volume

name: cobalt yield
description: Elemental contribution of Cobalt with respect to total.

name: undisturbed zone hydrocarbon volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of hydrocarbon in the undisturbed zone with respect to the total volume.

name: deep resistivity
description: The resistivity which represents a measurement made several feet into the formation; generally considered a measurement of the undisturbed formation.

name: bottomhole pressure
description: The pressure at the bottom of a borehole generally associated with the pore pressure of the formation open to the well.

name: bottomhole shutin pressure
description: The pressure at the bottom of a borehole with the well shut in.

name: migration velocity
description: Velocity applied in seismic migration.

name: true common midpoint z coord
description: Z-coordinate of Common midpoint (CMP) position

name: formation resistivity
description: True Formation Resistivity

name: fossil group
description: Name for biological group of fossils.

name: shock rate
description: Measure of shocks or vibrations above some threshold per unit of time; used to quantify vibration severity for MWD/LWD tools.

name: max mud density
description: Maximum allowable mud density

name: element tag
description: Tag (label) used to reference an Element of a Collection.

name: pick quality
description: Pick quality measurement.

name: rock compressibility depth
description: Measured depth for which Rock Compressibility is stated.

name: cuttings diameter
description: Average diameter of drill cuttings.

name: derivative model
description: Derivative Model used in evaluating this Transient, e.g., Backward, Central, or Forward.

name: admittance
description: The reciprocal of Impedance. The property of a medium to allow for the flow of an alternating current.

name: mwd data density
description: Density of data samples per length of borehole traversed; may be expressed as samples per unit length or as a Boolean indicator of sample presence within a depth frame.

name: ordered flag
description: Flag to indicate whether the members of a set have been ordered.

name: group
description: An assemblage of related organisms - often used to avoid taxonomic connotations when the kind or degree of relationship is not clearly defined.

name: density in
description: Density of the input material, such as the drilling fluid in the mixing tank.

name: thorium dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of thorium to total dry weight

name: volumetric thermal expansion
description: The change in volume of a material as a fraction of its total length due to a change in temperature at a constant pressure.

name: anhydrite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of anhydrite to total dry weight

name: street address
description: Physical location of a business, residence, or other installation, as would be used by a courier service or visitor to locate the installation.

name: formation conductivity
description: Formation Conductivity

name: pre cursor amplitude
description: Difference in seismic amplitude between a reference position and the corresponding shallower extreme.

name: initial gas saturation
description: Gas Saturation at the beginning of the test, experiment or production.

name: running force
description: The force needed to run. For example, during a test.

name: inverse area squared
description: Base property for inverse area squared

name: qfm volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of quartz + feldspar + mica with respect to the total volume.

name: true receiver line position rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of true position in a receiver line.

name: conn 1 outside diameter
description: Outside diameter of tool joint/connection 1

name: gas fluid ratio
description: The ratio of gas within a fluid otherwise named foam quality when the gas is used to foam the fluid.

name: water rate meter type
description: Type of liquid meter used to measure the water rate

name: apparent fluid velocity
description: Apparent velocity of the fluid.

name: fractional surface area
description: The fraction of a clays specific surface area which participates in hydraulic flow.

name: super array code
description: Code of super array

name: volume fraction
description: The ratio of the volumes occupied by two components, or by one component to the total volume of the system.

name: drill stabilizer code
description: Specific code of the drill stabilizer.

name: weathering depth cdp
description: Depth of weathered layer at a CDP.

name: interval compressional shear velocity ratio
description: Value of compressional-shear velocity ratio in interval

name: efficiency
description: The ratio of the useful energy delivered by a dynamic system to the energy supplied to it.

name: trace azimuth
description: The Azimuth coordinate of a trace

name: downhole inclination
description: Inclination of the drillstring as measured downhole

name: interval shear velocity
description: Interval shear wave velocity, measured over a finite interval, with the interval usually determined by geologic layering.

name: tool deviation
description: Angle between the tool axis and the vertical.

name: baselap type
description: The type of a Baselap in the Earth subsurface, whether it is an Onlap or a Downlap

name: nom hydraulic power
description: Hydraulic (Flowrate x pressure) power that the equipment can sustain over a long period of time, as opposed to maximum working pressure which is the peak maximum

name: illite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of illite with respect to the total volume.

name: streamer length
description: The nominal length of the streamer.

name: uncertainty radius
description: Magnitude of uncertainty for a measurement being represented as a position in 2D or 3D coordinate space, such as a geographical position.

name: stack mode converted velocity
description: Stacking converted-wave velocity, for a wave traveling through layers as a Compressional wave in one direction and a Shear wave in the other. This can be computed from a combined RMS average of the Compressional and Shear interval velocities. In practice it is usually determined directly from velocity analysis on short offset converted wave data.

name: water cut
description: The percent of water per total volume of liquid over a period of time for a product flow network unit.

name: acid treatment count
description: Number of acid jobs

name: wet gas critical pressure
description: The pressure needed to condense a wet gas at its critical temperature (Wet gas : mixture of free gas plus condensate)

name: pore volume
description: The volume within a geologic volume that describes the connected void space within the matrix of rock.

name: neutron porosity limestone
description: Porosity derived from a neutron logging measurement, assuming that the rock matrix material is calcite.

name: chi square
description: Statistical test of data distribution, used to measure goodness of fit of the data to some distribution model.

name: fluid volume
description: Volume of fluid.

name: apparent mud filtrate resistivity
description: Apparent resistivity of the mud filtrate, generally from log measurements of the "flushed zone".

name: in service date
description: The date on which an equipment item or product was placed in service.

name: drill bit grade tbg
description: The TBG, Teeth-Bearing-Gauge, grading assigned to a drill bit based on particular criteria. The TBG has 5 fields: Bearing, Broken Teeth, Gauge, Gauge Out of Hole, Tooth Wear.

name: sidetrack number
description: A sequential number identifying a particular sidetrack; 0 if no sidetracks have occurred. Used for WITS Channel SKNO.

name: idle time
description: Period of time during which equipment is idle. Complement of Operating_Time.

name: pressure operation type
description: Type of pressure-operated mechanism. Certain tools are be operated by either tubing or annulus pressure. These tools frequently contain a rupture disk or break plug and are single-shot.

name: fracture geometry
description: Characterizes the geometry of a fracture: Planar or Linear.

name: pressure digit
description: Element of a representation for pressure data in which each digit in the decimal pressure (1's, 10's, 100's, etc. )is stored as a separate unitless digit. This method is obsolete, but the property is needed for mapping historical data.

name: kerogen adsorption
description: Describes the adsorption of hydrocarbon compounds on kerogen

name: mineral group
description: The group to which a mineral belongs.

name: instantaneous wavenumber
description: Instantaneous frequency measured in depth domain

name: critical volume
description: The inverse of density at the critical point of a fluid, describing the volume occupied by a fluid of unit mass.

name: geometric mean permeability
description: Mean permeability in horizontal or vertical plane, computed as the square root of the product of the normal directional permeability values (e.g. X-Y or Y-Z) in the plane.

name: layer storativity ratio
description: Ratio of layer storativity to total storativity ("omegaj")

name: gauge length
description: Length of the in-gauge portion of an equipment item.

name: stroke volume
description: Volume of a pump stroke

name: geodetic coord sys code
description: Type of a geodetic coordinate system. This property specifies whether the Geodetic coordinate system used to record position data is Cartesian or Latitude/Longitude.

name: formation name
description: Name given to a geologic formation; may be a local name or an accepted standard.

name: down load
description: Downward load exerted on an equipment item.

name: radiant intensity
description: Cumulative quantity of electomagnetc radiation emitted, reflected, transmitted or received, per unit solid angle

name: iadc grade gauge
description: IADC Drill Bit Grade based on gauge

name: zone start
description: The start depth of a zone, usually along the borehole. This may be the deeper or the shallower end of the zone.

name: image origin azimuth
description: The azimuth of a point on an object corresponding to the origin of an image of the object (left side of core image)

name: halite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of halite with respect to the total volume.

name: max water saturation
description: Maximum value of Water Saturation

name: ideal receiver position 1 y coord
description: Y-coordinate of ideal receiver position 1.

name: n2 concentration
description: Concentration of Nitrogen

name: mis tie static time correction
description: Constant time correction to apply to a seismic line to compensate for time differences.

name: scale factor latitude
description: Latitude at which scale factor is exact.

name: volume reflection spectrum
description: Volume Reflection Spectrum, i.e. spectral decomposition of the amplitude response in interval

name: elevation
description: Height of some point above a horizontal reference plane.

name: nahcolite dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of nahcolite to total dry weight

name: cement type
description: Type of cement

name: overbalance pressure
description: The difference between formation pressure and the pressure of the fluid in the borehole.

name: catalog code
description: Code of the catalog entity providing further specifications of the leaf entities of a certain entity type.

name: ideal source position 0 x coord
description: X-coordinate of ideal source position 0.

name: blade material
description: Material used in the blade, such as steel, aluminum or plastic. This material represents material of sleeve structure in sleeve type stabilizers and is the same as the body material in integral stabilizers.

name: bottom true stratigraphic thickness depth
description: True Stratigraphic Thickness Depth of Bottom of Interval

name: volume type
description: The type of an Earth subsurface region or volume, e.g. Formation, Reservoir, Tank, Bed, etc.

name: mass per geologic time
description: Mass per geologic time. E.g. the generated mass of hydrocarbons per geologic time

name: fracture storativity
description: Fracture Storativity (Porosity * Total Compressibility product) of a finite conductivity vertical fracture ("(phi*Ct)f")

name: mud temperature out
description: The temperature of mud coming out of the hole, usually measured in the ditch before the shale shakers

name: tbg grade gauge
description: TBG Drill Bit Grade based on gauge.

name: projection scale factor
description: Scale Factor which is used as a defining parameter for a projection, typically taken along the Central Meridian or along one of the major parallels

name: peak trough delta time
description: Time difference between peak and trough.

name: amplitude estimate
description: Amplitude value on one side of an intersection

name: water gravity
description: The ratio of the density of the produced or reservoir water to that of pure water at atmospheric conditions

name: perspective height
description: Height of the point of perspective; used in general perspective map projections.

name: quality indicator
description: Property which provides a relative measure of the quality or fitness-for-purpose of data, or of some item, process, or material.

name: absolute permeability
description: The permeability of porous material when completely saturated with a wetting fluid and without the influence of non-Darcy (turbulence) effects. Also called "intrinsic" permeability.

name: bearing
description: The horizontal angle between the direction to a point and the direction of some reference line, normally measured as a clockwise angle from the reference line.

name: upstream coil pressure
description: Coil working pressure upstream of the choke box

name: orthoclase volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of orthoclase with respect to the total volume.

name: nickel yield
description: Elemental contribution of Nickel with respect to total.

name: ellipsoid code
description: Code of the ellipsoid to which geodetic coordinates are referenced.

name: stiffness
description: The ratio of stress acting in a specified direction to the strain in a specified direction. Stiffness is a tensor of rank 4, but is expressible as a 6x6 matrix, the inverse of the compliance matrix.

name: dimensionless interwell distance
description: Dimensionless inter-well distance for a horizontal interference test

name: bed character
description: The Characteristic given to a Bed or layer (e.g. has sealing characteristic or is probable source rock.)

name: mass
description: The property of a body that is a measure of its inertia, that is commonly taken as a measure of the amount of material it contains, that causes a body to have weight in a gravitational field.

name: sedimentary feature type
description: The type of the sedimentation feature associated with a subsurface or surface Earth region.

name: dip type
description: The type of dipping associated with subsurface planes; e.g., CrossBedding, Fault, Fracture, BedBoundary, etc.

name: neutron capture cross section
description: The effective area within which a neutron passes in order to be captured by an atomic nucleus. Commonly called Sigma.

name: last static reservoir pressure
description: Last reservoir pressure recorded

name: data presence flag
description: An indicator which shows that some particular type of data is available.

name: unit productivity index
description: Productivity index per unit of length
quantity: PWLS:volume per time per length per pressure

name: sulfur yield
description: Elemental contribution of Sulfur with respect to total.

name: magnesium concentration
description: Magnesium concentration in a material.

name: affine coeff b
description: Coefficient "B" in an Affine transformation between two coordinate systems. The input and output coordinate systems may be local or projection systems.

name: compressive force
description: The force tending to compress or squeeze a body.

name: outer boundary condition type
description: Description of the outer boundary condition for a well test model.

name: shear slowness
description: Acoustic slowness of a shear wave (Vs); reciprocal of Shear_Velocity; a shear wave is a type of seismic wave in which the particle motion is perpendicular to the direction of propagation; also called S-wave or secondary wave.

name: electromagnetic attenuation rate
description: A measure of the rate of attenuation of an electromagnetic wave per unit length.

name: velocity beta factor
description: Gradient factor b for Faust 3rd root velocity function. v(z) = b * z**(1/3)

name: water flowrate
description: Rate of flow of water

name: seismic arc length
description: A measure of reflection heterogeneity which is used to quantify lateral changes in reflection patterns. Used as a stratigraphic sequence indicator.

name: total storativity thickness
description: Sum of the Storativity_Thickness values of all layers in the model.

name: fracture height
description: Height of a fracture.

name: segment length
description: The length of a borehole segment.

name: c4h10 concentration
description: Concentration of Butane (C4H10).

name: frame density
description: Bulk density of the solid frame of the rock. The solid frame of the rock includes the porosity but not the content of the pore spaces. Frame_Density = (1 - Porosity) * Grain_Density.

name: acoustic velocity
description: The velocity of an acoustic wave; the rate at which the wave travels from one point to another. Used generally for all elastic and seismic waves.

name: legal datum
description: Code of legislated geodetic datum

name: min allowable flowrate
description: Minimum allowable flowrate for the equipment

name: geocentric dz
description: Z component of the translation of the center of a geodetic datum. One of seven parameters used in the Bursa-Wolf transformation.

name: oil compressibility
description: The compressibility of oil at a given pressure and temperature.

name: radius
description: Radius of an entity with a spherical or cylindrical shape, such as the borehole, an item of drillstring equipment, etc.

name: central line pt2 longitude
description: Longitude of second point on central line of projection.

name: differential caliper
description: The difference between the actual borehole diameter and bit size.

name: qfm dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of quartz + feldspar + mica to total dry weight.

name: corrosion rate
description: The rate at which corrosion, a complex chemical or electrochemical process by which metal is destroyed, occurs. For example the rate at which a casing pipe rusts (corrodes).

name: relative fluorescence
description: Measure of fluorescence of a material relative to that of some standard.

name: cumulative condensate volume
description: Cumulative condensate production.

name: accident type
description: Type of Quality, Health, Safety, and Environmental accident such as Fluid Spill, Kick While Drilling, Kick While Tripping, ...

name: depth unit
description: Unit for depth data

name: surface weight on bit
description: The weight on bit calculated from surface measurements

name: mineral number
description: Index in the cumulative mineral array which are naturally indexed and not indexed by Zone_Number.

name: water compressibility
description: The compressibility of water at a given pressure and temperature.

name: cost per depth
description: Amount of money per unit of length

name: interval velocity
description: Average velocity in a layer or between two subsurface points; generally applied to a rock layer whose velocity can be considered homogeneous. May be derived from stacking velocity using the Dix equation (or a more refined variant).

name: correlation coefficient
description: Coefficient of a correlation used to determine the quality of the correlation

name: gas flow velocity
description: Flow velocity of gas component of fluid.

name: third party certification
description: Certification by third party for the sampling bottle

name: sparse 3d data
description: A data set of sparse location data in 3-space, where none or up to n Properties may be represented at each location. Example: X_Coordinate,Y_Coordinate,Z_Coordinate,Velocity.

name: linear weight
description: Weight of an equipment item per unit length; e.g. Casing weight, pipe weight, cable weight, etc.

name: casson plastic viscosity
description: Measure of the internal resistance to fluid flow attributable to the amount, type, and size of solids present in a given fluid. The Casson model equation is: SQRT(Shear_Stress) = SQRT(Yield_Stress) + SQRT(Plastic_Viscosity X Shear_Rate)

name: longitudinal amplitude
description: Amplitude of the longitudinal component in multi-component seismic.

name: rig roll angle
description: Measure of the side-to-side rotational movement of the rig due the combined effects of wind and waves; measured as the angle from vertical.

name: wellbore storage type
description: Describes Wellbore storage behavior as either constant, variable (exp), or variable (erf).

name: maturity
description: Measured maturity indicator in source rocks for calibration of petroleum systems

name: heat exchanger code
description: Code for heater used in testing and production services

name: stack schoenberg ellipticity
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Schoenberg's ellipticity factor, for each layer.

name: response parameter
description: Property which reflects the response of some measurement device or algorithm to a particular material or environment. The Unit_Quantity is determined by the type of measurement.

name: material type
description: The type or class of materials both naturally occurring or used in some activity, e.g. Hydrocarbon, Mineral, Rock, Steel, Proppant, etc.

name: well to boundary distance
description: The distance between the well trajectory and the adjacent reservoir boundary distance.

name: fluid contact type
description: The type of fluid contact between Earth subsurface regions or volumes, e.g. Oil Water Contact, Gas Water Contact, etc.

name: nom thickness
description: Nominal thickness

name: downtime
description: Time during which equipment is not operational condition or is otherwise unavailable.

name: plane angle
description: The angular displacement between two lines extending from the same point, measured in the plane of the two lines.

name: surface sensor code
description: Specific code of surface sensor.

name: mud conductivity
description: The electric conductivity of mud

name: cyclic redundancy check
description: CRC test value for this Calibration Coefficient set.

name: storage capacity
description: The ratio of the sum of layer porosity thicknesses to total system porosity thicknesses for layered porous media.

name: depositional environment type
description: The type of deposition that has created a particular Earth environment, e.g. Reef, Beachrock, Pointbar, etc.

name: specific surface area
description: The characteristic of a porous media which is the internal surface area of the medium per unit volume.

name: temperature sensor code
description: Temperature sensor code

name: neutron slowing down length
description: Average straight-line distance a neutron travels in being slowed from natural source energy to epithermal energy levels by collisions with formation nuclei.

name: gas sorption storativity ratio
description: Ratio of the stored gas in the kerogen (solid hydrocarbon) to the total gas stored in the system

name: seismic object type
description: Type of seismic data object: data or survey geometry, 2 or 3D

name: inverse liquid formation volume factor
description: Ratio of total liquid volume at surface (stock tank) conditions to the total liquid volume at specified (typically, reservoir) conditions.

name: sampling period
description: Time interval between the recording of two sequential data samples.

name: vertical mobility
description: A measure of the ease with which a fluid can be moved vertically in a specific medium (i.e. rock). The ratio of the effective vertical permeability and the viscosity of the fluid.

name: electric susceptibility
description: Ratio of electric field strength to electric polarization.

name: washout caliper diff
description: The degree of a borehole ovality beyond which caliper data becomes unreliable due to bad contact with the tool pads.

name: sequence type
description: The type of sequence, e.g. granulometry, thickness, facies, etc.

name: activity number
description: External identifier assigned to an activity (e.g. job or proposal number).

name: n c4h10 concentration
description: Concentration of Normal Butane (n-C4H10); typical volume concentration in natural gas is 0.6%.

name: min storage temperature
description: Minimum Storage Temperature

name: bottom two way time
description: Depth of Bottom of Interval in Two Way Time

name: digital encoding
description: Identification of how data are encoded digitally; e.g. ASCII, Binary, etc.

name: trona volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of trona with respect to the total volume.

name: activity code
description: The specific catalog-controlled code of an Activity performed on a Well, a Region, or an Earth subsurface component.

name: start depth
description: Depth at which an activity starts e.g. at the beginning of the Coiled tubing pumping stage, depth of the cleaning tool

name: related sample type
description: Type of related samples taken in the recombination set

name: spherical position
description: Set of coordinates specifying the position of a point in a spherical coordinate system

name: injection point
description: Indicates where a fluid is injected in the main flow e.g. Low Pressure Discharge...

name: fracture shear weakness
description: The ratio of shear compliance of the fracture to the total shear compliance of the fractured rock. It indicates how much of the total compliance of the fractured rock is due to the fractures. See Compliance.

name: rock compressibility correlation
description: Rock Compressibility Correlation (Sandstone, Carbonate)

name: manganese dry weight fraction
description: Ratio of dry weight of manganese to total dry weight

name: c5h12 concentration
description: Concentration of Pentane (n-C5H12).

name: bound water salinity
description: Salinity of the water bound to clays in the formation

name: uranium concentration
description: Concentration of Uranium by weight

name: thermal neutron decay time
description: The time for the neutron population to fall to 1/e (37%) of its original value. Commonly called Tau, it is inversely related to Neutron_Capture_Cross_Section

name: tube torsional yield
description: Maximum torque which can be applied to the tube or body without causing permanent deformation.

name: stack thomsen sigma
description: Effective value through the subsurface of Thomsen's sigma anisotropy parameter

name: driller elevation reference code
description: Code of the elevation reference for drilling data

name: cation concentration
description: The concentration of cations, the positively charged particles, in volume of material.

name: length unit
description: Unit for Length data

name: depth offset
description: Offset in depth versus some depth reference.

name: pyrite volume fraction
description: The volume fraction of pyrite with respect to the total volume.

name: run number
description: The number (or rank) associated with a particular run of a tool or activity. Use is discouraged due to ambiguity when services are combined or when complete history unavailable; time of data acquisition is more reliable.

name: fault strike
description: The azimuth of the strike of a fault.

name: casing rotation friction coefficient
description: Friction coefficient due to rotation between casing and other surface (e.g. drill string).

name: relative pumping time
description: Time it takes to pump fluid into the fracture

name: geopolitical region type
description: The type of a geopolitical region, e.g. Nation, State, County, Province, Community, etc.

name: range type
description: Specification whether the value range is inclusive[], exclusive (), or mixed: [) or (].

name: flowing condition depth
description: Depth at which bottomhole data were acquired

name: depth dip
description: Dip computed on a depth surface by measuring the difference in depths between two points compared to the horizontal distance between the points.

name: logarithmic permeability
description: The logarithmic expression of permeability usually used in petroleum systems models with a wide range of permeability values

name: penetration rate
description: Usually used to describe the rate at which a formation is penetrated during drilling operation. In general, the rate at which an equipment penetrates a surface or subsurface volume.

name: ideal receiver position 0
description: Idealized receiver position 0

name: constraint object
description: Name of Object holding descriptions of the constraints (e.g. String_Enum_Cat)

name: bound water conductivity
description: Conductivity of water bound to clay in the formations.

name: avg sequence trend
description: A coefficient that characterizes the upwards or downwards increasing conductivity trend within a given depth interval

name: reservoir type
description: Description of the reservoir type for a well test model.

name: capillary pressure function coeff
description: Coefficients used in the capillary pressure function.

name: relative apparent resistivity
description: The ratio of apparent resistivity to the true resistivity of a portion of a reservoir model (like a two-layer model).

name: gqi admission policy
description: Identifies the Geometry Query Interface (GQI) policy for maintaining the content of a geometric feature as it is edited. The most common value is POINT_SET_PRESERVING, but applications may implement others so the values are not constrained.

name: true source line position
description: True position in a source line.

name: spherically focused conductivity
description: The conductivity, measured by a spherically focused log, which represents the resistivity approximately one to two feet into the formation.

name: mud trip gas factor
description: Bottom hole drill fluid gas content spike as output by the chromatograph after stopping circulation for a significant time interval such as when tripping into the hole.

name: inlet pressure
description: Pressure at the inlet of an equipment item.

name: penetration per rotation
description: It is usually used to describe the formation penetrated distance per dill bit rotation during drilling operation.

name: barium yield
description: Elemental contribution of Barium with respect to total.

name: species
description: A category of biological classification ranking immediately below the genus or subgenus.

name: true receiver position z coord
description: Z-coordinate of true receiver position.

name: cumulative oil volume
description: Cumulative oil production at standard conditions. At constant BHP or WHP, cumulative volume is not the straightforward sum of volume by RHU but determined by Inverse Laplace transformation.

name: occurrence
description: Description of where an object, material or phenomenon may occur or be found.

name: true source line position rho
description: Horizontal (x-y) distance from origin of true position in a source line.

name: memory size
description: Memory Size, generally expressed in kilobytes or Megabytes

name: total skin
description: The sum of all formation, completion, deviation, geometric and fluid flow skin factors. It can be a function of the flowrate if a Non-Darcy skin effect is present.
